{"name":"● Summon the Simple Form","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 221","description":"<p>At this level of mastery, the conjurer may create simple, inanimate objects. The object cannot have any moving parts and may not be made of multiple materials. For example, the conjurer may summon a steel baton, a lead pipe, a wooden stake, or a chunk of granite.</p>","details":"<p>Each turn the conjurer wishes to keep the object in existence, another Willpower point must be spent or the object vanishes.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"4","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.T0SpTLOPUdr0Y356"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2d9fqjslrzb","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Conjuring","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439743474,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"00XLtotO04X0JJUP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"Feature","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_i58eczenhcp","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Quietus#/CF_SEP/Quietus (Vizier)","color":"#000000","name":"Quietus (Vizier)","children":[],"folderPath":["temp_444y5utucrj","temp_g4q0cu2l6d"],"fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":null,"sorting":"a","contents":["9tbmauW8CI3jaj0f","3ZliNQwY5KmGN8xM","D6HWtxfEG7xPBMy5","cf1gnvSZINtXLeu6","f3EieD5tewtj4dcs","f0kDnh2oPDi1uiwt"],"version":"2.5.6"}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"iscreated":false,"version":"","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"","description":"","details":"","type":"","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674221184508,"modifiedTime":1674221184843,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"06Oxd7QYjkOnSezF"}
{"name":"●● Apprentice's Brooms","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 164","description":"<p>With Apprentice&rsquo;s Brooms, the necromancer can make a dead body rise and perform a simple function. For example, the corpse could be set to carrying heavy objects, digging, or just shambling from place to place. The cadavers thus animated do not attack or defend themselves if interfered with, but instead attempt to carry out their given instructions until such time as they&rsquo;ve been rendered inanimate. Generally it takes dismemberment, flame, or something similar to destroy a corpse animated in this way.</p>","details":"<p>A roll of Wits + Occult (difficulty 7) and the expenditure of a point of both blood and Willpower are all that is necessary to animate corpses with Apprentice&rsquo;s Brooms. The number of corpses animated is equal to the number of successes achieved. The necromancer must then state the task to which he is setting his zombies. The cadavers turn themselves to their work until they finish the job (at which point they collapse) or something (including time) destroys them.<br><br>Corpses animated in this way have no initiative of their own, and are unable to make value judgments. They respond to very literal instruction. Thus, a zombie could be told &ldquo;sweep this room every day until all the dust and cobwebs are gone&rdquo; or &ldquo;transcribe this manuscript&rdquo; with an expectation of reasonable results, while a more open-ended command such as &ldquo;fix this motorcycle&rdquo; or &ldquo;research this Necromantic ritual and write down the results&rdquo; would be doomed to failure.<br><br>Bodies energized by this power continue to decay, albeit at a much slower rate than normal.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"wits","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"7","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.x7TyMvPCvX2P7IOL"},"cf":{"id":"temp_9h9qdp1h3gj","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Bone Path","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670842147642,"modifiedTime":1674221165897,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"06ShGfBTPhW1IXTP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●● Shape of the Beast","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 200","description":"<p>This endows the vampire with the legendary ability to transform into a wolf or bat. A Kindred changed in this way is a particularly imposing representative of the animal kingdom. Indeed, he is far superior to normal animals, even ones possessed by Subsume the Spirit. He retains his own psyche and temperament, but can still call upon the abilities of the beast form &mdash; increased senses for the wolf and flight for the bat. Gangrel are reputed to change to other animal forms better suited to their environment &mdash; jackals in Africa, dholes in Asia, and even enormous rats in urban environments &mdash; a feat that other Clans learning Protean cannot seem to duplicate.</p>","details":"<p>The character spends one blood point to assume the desired shape. The transformation requires three turns to complete (spending additional blood points reduces the time of transformation by one turn per point spent, to a minimum of one). The vampire remains in his beast form until the next dawn, unless he wishes to change back sooner.<br><br></p>\n<p>While in the animal&rsquo;s shape, the vampire can use any Discipline he possesses except Necromancy, Serpentis, Thaumaturgy, or Vicissitude (as well as any others the Storyteller deems unavailable). Furthermore, each form gives the character the abilities of that creature. In wolf form, the vampire&rsquo;s teeth and claws inflict Strength + 1 aggravated damage, he can run at double speed, and the difficulties of all Perception rolls are reduced by two. In bat form, the vampire&rsquo;s Strength is reduced to 1, but he can fly at speeds of up to 20 miles per our, difficulties for all hearing-based Perception rolls are reduced by three, and attacks made against him are at +2 difficulty due to his small size.<br><br>The Storyteller may allow Gangrel to assume a different animal shape, but should establish the natural abilities it grants the character.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_b0ldn2fjavv","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Protean","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670331720769,"modifiedTime":1674221181176,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"06xqK0HwxW3J6anT","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Bad Sight (1 or 3pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 481","description":"<p>Your sight is defective. The difficulties of any die rolls involving the use of your eyesight are increased by two. As a one-point Flaw, this condition can be corrected with glasses or contacts; as a three-point Flaw, the condition is too severe to be corrected.</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_d9j4thjusi","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/Multi-pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672365603221,"modifiedTime":1674221113607,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"0BDavwdF4CSfRB4t","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"The Ritual of Pochtli","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 180","description":"<p>This ritual cannot be cast by itself, but only in conjunction with another Necromantic ritual, or with the heavily ritualized use of a Necromantic path. The action of the ritual is this: Two or more Kindred necromancers restrain a mortal vessel and inflict incisions in the shape of blasphemous symbols (typically subverted Egyptian hieroglyphs or Aztec symbols). They then drink from these injuries. Each participating Necromancer must make his own cut and drink from no other cut. Thereafter, the Necromantic power the Kindred seek to employ gains the benefit of all the participants&rsquo; knowledge. This ritual makes it possible for Necromancers to create truly fearsome feats of death magic.<br><br>The player rolls to activate this ritual as normal. If the roll succeeds, the Kindred who have participated in the ritual may work together on the path or ritual the Ritual of Pochtli is intended to assist, and players share successes. Note that the primary application of Necromancy requires its own roll, and that successes (and failures) garnered by the group are pooled. All Kindred participating in the ritual must know the Ritual of Pochtli as well as the ritual or path power the group seeks to enact.<br><br>The downside of this power is that a single player&rsquo;s botch negates the successes of the entire group, resulting in a horrific failure for all the ritual workers.</p>","details":"<p>Casting times for necromantic rituals vary widely; see the description for particulars. The player rolls Intelligence + Occult (difficulty 3 + the level of the ritual, maximum 9). Success indicates the ritual proceeds smoothly, failure produces no effect, and a botch indicates something has gone horribly wrong.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"5","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_b17ggxg6joc","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 2 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670899739755,"modifiedTime":1674221173864,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"0J1d4aOhXpeIQ4kN","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Dominate","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/mainpower_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 151","description":"<p>Dominate is one of the most dreaded of Disciplines. It is a vampire&rsquo;s ability to influence another person&rsquo;s thoughts and actions through her own force of will. Dominate requires that the vampire capture her victim&rsquo;s gaze (see p. 152); as such, it may be used against only one subject at a time. Further, commands must be issued verbally, although simple orders may be made with signs &mdash; for example, a pointed finger and forceful expression to indicate &ldquo;Go!&rdquo; However, the subject won&rsquo;t comply if he can&rsquo;t understand the vampire, no matter how powerful the Kindred&rsquo;s will is.<br><br>Perhaps unsurprisingly, vampires to which Dominate comes naturally tend to be from willful, domineering Clans. The Giovanni, Lasombra, Tremere, and Ventrue all consider an iron will to be a boon, and are eager to impose that iron will on any who would move against them.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.discipline","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4wvty5nf9hd","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Dominate","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670227618172,"modifiedTime":1674221161814,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"0KRezo2WN0ZedxjH","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
