{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"Feature","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9h9qdp1h3gj","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Bone Path","color":"#000000","name":"The Bone Path","children":[],"folderPath":["temp_444y5utucrj","temp_9pmdboh96h5","temp_odkmoq9z4sc"],"fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":null,"sorting":"a","contents":["x7TyMvPCvX2P7IOL","06ShGfBTPhW1IXTP","GjxE46RzDUmDY1cG","9AXB3cpp0PEhhEc2","lYBbx98c31Lpcm4l","LGz8dWTDfJz5E0G9"],"version":"2.5.6"}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"iscreated":false,"version":"","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"","description":"","details":"","type":"","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674221166410,"modifiedTime":1674221166717,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"0QKhjpzeyZSYdJ6V"}
{"name":"●●●●●  Bloodform","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 242","description":"<p>A vampire with this power can physically transform all or part of her body into sentient vitae. This blood is in all respects identical to the vampire&rsquo;s normal vitae; she can use it to nourish herself or others, create ghouls, or establish blood bonds. If all this blood is imbibed or otherwise destroyed, the vampire meets Final Death.</p>","details":"<p>The vampire may transform all or part of herself as she deems fit. Each leg can turn into two blood points worth of vitae, as can the torso; each arm, the head, and the abdomen convert to one blood point each. The blood can be reconverted to the body part, provided it is in contact with the vampire. If the blood has been utilized or destroyed, the vampire must spend a number of blood points equal to what was originally created to regrow the missing body part.<br><br></p>\n<p>A vampire entirely in this form may not be staked, cut, bludgeoned, or pierced, but can be burned or exposed to the sun. The vampire may ooze along, drip up walls, and flow through the narrowest cracks, as though she were in Tenebrous Form (p. 190).<br><br>Mental Disciplines may be used, provided no eye contact or vocal utterance is necessary, although the vampire can perceive her surroundings just fine (but the perceptions are always centered on the largest pool of blood). If a vampire in this form &ldquo;washes&rdquo; over a mortal or animal, that mortal must make a Courage roll (difficulty 8) or fly into a panic.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3zgkxt2054","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Vicissitude","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670334173944,"modifiedTime":1674440392975,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"0QKuuqz7Uwo5erHl","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Promethean Clay (5pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 238","description":"<p>Your flesh ripples and molds itself to your preternatural will, almost before you consciously invoke the change. The difficulty to use any Vicissitude power on yourself is two less than normal, and you may activate Vicissitude powers reflexively at your full dice pool while taking other actions. Powers that require multiple turns to activate still require the usual duration. The change simply occurs without conscious direction. As a final benefit, you need no physical sculpting to use the first three levels of Vicissitude on yourself, as your flesh undulates and extrudes to its desired shape. Only characters with at least one dot of Vicissitude may purchase this Merit.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_g4msmdkn9lw","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Tzimisce#/CF_SEP/Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221099262,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"0VdUDxdUWtZpjPy1","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"Feature","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_rn1b964uihf","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Tremere","color":"#000000","name":"Tremere","children":["temp_kve07fusdp8","temp_kchlaqnn8q"],"folderPath":["temp_zbxadbcq32d","temp_xp3y5aquu4a"],"fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":null,"sorting":"a","contents":[],"version":"2.5.6"}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"iscreated":false,"version":"","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"","description":"","details":"","type":"","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674221094950,"modifiedTime":1674221097386,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"0bOyaBHJ88nBVHWc"}
{"name":"Thaumaturgy Rituals","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 230","description":"<p>Rituals are Thaumaturgical formulas, meticulously researched and prepared, that create powerful magical effects. Rituals are less versatile than paths, as their effects are singular and straightforward, but they are better suited to specific ends.<br><br>All thaumaturges have the ability to use rituals, though each individual ritual must be learned separately. By acquainting herself with the arcane practice of blood magic, the caster gains the capacity to manipulate these focused effects.<br><br>Thaumaturgical rituals are rated from 1 to 5, each level corresponding to both the level of mastery of Thaumaturgy the would-be caster must possess and the relative power of the ritual itself. Unless stated otherwise, a ritual requires five minutes per level to cast.<br><br>Casting rituals requires a successful Intelligence + Occult roll, for which the difficulty equals 3 + the level of the ritual (maximum 9). Only one success is required for a ritual to work, though certain spells may require more successes or have variable effects based on how well the caster&rsquo;s roll goes. Should a roll to activate a ritual fail, the Storyteller is encouraged to create strange occurrences or side effects, or even make it appear that the ritual was successful, only to reveal its failure at a later time. A botched ritual roll may even indicate a catastrophic failure or summon an ill-tempered demon.<br><br>Rituals sometimes require special ingredients or reagents to work &mdash; these are noted in each ritual&rsquo;s description. Common components include herbs, animal bones, ceremonial items, feathers, eye of newt, tongue of toad, etc. Acquiring magical components for a powerful ritual may form the basis for an entire story.<br><br>At the first level of Thaumaturgy, the vampire automatically gains a single Level One ritual. To learn further rituals, the thaumaturge must find someone to teach him, or learn the ritual from a scroll, tome, or other archive. Learning a new ritual can take anywhere from a few nights (Level One ritual) to months or years (Level Five ritual). Some mystics have studied individual rituals for decades, or even centuries.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"-1","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nky5ipwtj1","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671082060123,"modifiedTime":1674439749225,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"0cpo3cSX07QnSeNn","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Connoisseur (2pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 261","description":"<p>Your study of the Auspex Discipline, combined with your rarified tastes, allows you powerful insights into the character of any whose blood you taste.</p>","details":"<p>The character tastes another&rsquo;s blood (potentially risking blood bond), and player rolls Perception + Empathy (difficulty 6 for mortals or 8 for Kindred). If the blood came from a mortal, each success allows him to learn one of the following: the mortal&rsquo;s Nature, her Demeanor, any Derangements she may possess, whether she is blood bonded, and whether she carries any blood-borne diseases. If the vitae came from a vampire, he can learn all of the previous information, plus anything discoverable with the first level of the Path of Blood (see V20, p. 213). The Ventrue may taste the blood of a mortal who does not fit within his feeding restriction long enough to use this ability, but he must immediately spit it out afterwards.<br><br>Vampires that do not have Auspex &bull;&bull; cannot take this Merit.</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_v0jul49bek","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Ventrue","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221099976,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"0cwsMfXKfFycRuoY","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"The Hand of Glory","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 179","description":"<p>The Hand of Glory is a mummified hand used by the necromancer to anesthetize a home&rsquo;s residents and, thereby, allow him free rein to do what he will in the residence. To create one, the necromancer wraps the severed hand of a condemned murderer in a shroud, draws it tight to squeeze out any remaining blood, and preserves the hand in an earthenware jar with salt, saltpeter, and long peppers. After a fortnight, the vampire removes the hand and dries it in an oven with vervain and fern. At the end of this process, if the roll to activate the ritual garners any successes, the creation is viable.<br><br>To use the Hand of Glory, the vampire first coats the fingertips of the mummified hand with a flammable substance derived from the fat of a hanged man and sets the fingers alight. The necromancer then recites the phrase, &ldquo;Let all those who are asleep be asleep, and let those who are awake be awake.&rdquo; All mortals within a household who are affected fall into a deep sleep and cannot be roused (the hand has no effect on supernatural creatures). For each unaffected occupant of a home, one finger of the hand will refuse to light. Botches may result in all of the fingers being lit but no one in the home being asleep. The hand may be extinguished at any time by the necromancer who created it. Anyone else wishing to douse the hand must use milk to do so &mdash; nothing else works. Once made, the Hand of Glory may be reused indefinitely. Effects last for one scene.</p>","details":"<p>Casting times for necromantic rituals vary widely; see the description for particulars. The player rolls Intelligence + Occult (difficulty 3 + the level of the ritual, maximum 9). Success indicates the ritual proceeds smoothly, failure produces no effect, and a botch indicates something has gone horribly wrong.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"5","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_b17ggxg6joc","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 2 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670899739755,"modifiedTime":1674221173767,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"11Q5ndhiUXTv4hZM","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●● Magic of the Smith","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 221","description":"<p>The Kindred may now conjure complex objects of multiple components and with moving parts. For example, the thaumaturge can create guns, bicycles, chainsaws, or cellphones.</p>","details":"<p>Objects created via Magic of the Smith are automatically permanent and cost five blood points to conjure. Particularly complex items often require a Knowledge roll (Crafts, Science, Technology, etc.) in addition to the basic roll.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"6","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.T0SpTLOPUdr0Y356"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2d9fqjslrzb","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Conjuring","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439743673,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"1AS0WwSxpLXNdUbP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Devil's Touch","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 231","description":"<p>Thaumaturges use this ritual to place curses upon mortals who earn their ire. Using this ritual marks an individual invisibly, causing all those who come in contact with him to receive him poorly. The mortal is treated as the most loathsome individual conceivable, and all who deal with him do everything in their power to make him miserable. Even bums spit at an afflicted individual, and children taunt him and barrage him with vulgarities.</p>","details":"<p>The effects of this ritual last one night, disappearing as the sun rises. The mortal (it doesn&rsquo;t work on vampires) must be present when the ritual is invoked, and a penny must be placed somewhere on his person (in a pocket, shoe, etc.).</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"4","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_q5ajxrpsb3","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 1 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671081485306,"modifiedTime":1674439750229,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"1CSyOlJVQFmmFLwB","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Overextended (4pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 492","description":"<p>You&rsquo;ve got your fingers in too many pies, and people are starting to notice. You have too many ghouls, too many retainers, or too much influence, which means that a lot of people have a vested interest in trimming back your operations. These enemies take every opportunity to reduce your power and influence, and if that means lying, cheating, or killing, so be it. Furthermore, your enemies block every attempt you make to move into new areas of control. You&rsquo;re boxed in, and the box is getting smaller.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ry8o03n5zsc","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/4 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221110908,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"1EJBalr6MI0vIrVy","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Blood Dance","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 180","description":"<p>The Blood Dance allows a ghost to communicate with a living relative. Necromancers sometimes perform this ritual for people in exchange for money or favors.<br><br>The vampire must dance and chant for two hours, calling forth the right spirit and entreating all other ghosts to leave the area. While dancing, the vampire pours colored sands and ocean salt on the ground in a precise pattern and then makes the link between the living person and the deceased. If successful, the ghost &ldquo;appears&rdquo; within the necromancer&rsquo;s sand-sigil and the living person can communicate with her for one hour. Failure means the spirit could not be contacted.</p>","details":"<p>Casting times for necromantic rituals vary widely; see the description for particulars. The player rolls Intelligence + Occult (difficulty 3 + the level of the ritual, maximum 9). Success indicates the ritual proceeds smoothly, failure produces no effect, and a botch indicates something has gone horribly wrong.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"6","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xjookc6i33s","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 3 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670899739755,"modifiedTime":1674221174463,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"1IY0dTozRFOeziKy","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
