{"name":"Dracon's Temperament (3pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 238","description":"<p>You emulate the ideal of Azi Dahaka within and without, to levels visceral and abstract. Your psyche flows with the permutable nature of change. Like the protean Dracon, you are a whirlwind of temperaments. This is not multiple personalities. You are one identity shown through the prism of ever-shifting Natures. No anchor fetters your sense of self. You can be any you.&nbsp;<br><br>At the start of each story, you may choose one Personality Archetype to function as your Nature, spending the rest of the story perceiving the world through that perspective. You also regain Willpower according to your new Nature and may be affected by other effects or Discipline powers as per your new Nature as well.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_g4msmdkn9lw","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Tzimisce#/CF_SEP/Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221098967,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"2ICowaKFDlZO9BeB","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Medium (2pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 493","description":"<p>You possess the natural affinity to sense and hear spirits, ghosts, and shades. Though you cannot see them, you can sense them, speak to them and, through pleading or cajoling, draw them to your presence. You may call upon them for aid or advice, but there will always be a price. Also, your difficulty is reduced by two for all Awareness rolls involving the spirits of the dead.</p>","details":"<p>Supernatural</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_644ptrzk5eq","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/2 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674439884980,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"2W9HYuZvb5jt2nAD","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Short (1pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 481","description":"<p>You are well below average height &mdash; four and a half feet (1.5 meters) tall or less. You have difficulty reaching or manipulating objects designed for normal adult size, and your running speed is one-half that of an average human.</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_jwd9ok2vgth","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672365603221,"modifiedTime":1674221102727,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"2Ya7qZrfbLAAY4DI","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Bone of Lies","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 237","description":"<p>This ritual enchants a mortal bone so that anyone who holds it must tell the truth. The bone in question is often a skull, though any part of the skeleton will do &mdash; some casters use strings of teeth, necklaces of finger joints, or wands fashioned from ribs or arms. The bone grows blacker as it compels its holder to tell the truth, until it has turned completely ebony and has no magic left.<br><br>This ritual binds the spirit of the individual to whom the bone belonged in life; it is this spirit who wrests the truth from the potential liar. The spirit absorbs the lies intended to be told by the bone&rsquo;s holder, and as it compels more truth, it becomes more and more corrupt. If summoned forth, this spirit reflects the sins it has siphoned from the defeated liar (in addition to anger over its unwilling servitude). For this reason, anonymous bones are often used in the ritual, and the bone is commonly buried after it has been used to its full extent. A specific bone may never be used twice for this ritual, though different bones from the same corpse can.</p>","details":"<p>The bone imbued with this magical power must be at least 200 years old and must absorb 10 blood points on the night that the ritual is cast. Each lie the holder wishes to tell consumes one of these blood points, and the holder <em>must</em> speak the truth immediately thereafter. When all 10 blood points have been consumed, the bone&rsquo;s magic ceases to work.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"7","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SOFUQHVyXwWb4xVU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_vfl4to3461m","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 4 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671081485306,"modifiedTime":1674440372484,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"2cbvJKqRlYiOMjgR","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
