{"name":"Fire Walker","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 238","description":"<p>This ritual imbues the vampire with an unnatural resistance to fire. Only a foolish vampire would actually attempt to walk on or through fire, but this ritual does grant an advanced tolerance to flame. Some Sabbat use this ritual to show off, while other thaumaturges use it only for martial concerns. To enact the ritual, the caster must cut off the end of one of his fingers and burn it in a Thaumaturgical circle.</p>","details":"<p>Cutting off one&rsquo;s finger does not do any health levels of damage, but it hurts like hell and requires a Willpower roll to perform. This ritual may be cast on other vampires (at the expense of the caster&rsquo;s fingertips...). If the subject has no Fortitude, he may soak fire with his Stamina for the duration of this ritual. If the vampire has Fortitude, he may soak fire with his Stamina + Fortitude for the duration of the ritual. This ritual lasts one hour.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"7","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SOFUQHVyXwWb4xVU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_vfl4to3461m","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 4 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671081485306,"modifiedTime":1674440372689,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"7DcWZj5KeCUJnYvY","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Repulsed by Garlic (1pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 494","description":"<p>You cannot abide garlic, and the smallest whiff of its scent will drive you from a room unless you make a successful Willpower roll (difficulty based on the strength of the odor).</p>","details":"<p>Supernatural</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_jwd9ok2vgth","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221102630,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"7EGYesb1PI5ZBHFg","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●● Summon","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 195","description":"<p>This impressive power enables the vampire to call to herself any person whom she has ever met. This call can go to anyone, mortal or supernatural, across any distance within the physical world. The subject of the Summons comes as fast as he is able, possibly without even knowing why. He knows intuitively how to find his Summoner &mdash; even if the vampire moves to a new location, the subject redirects his own course as soon as he can. After all, he&rsquo;s coming to the vampire herself, not to some predetermined site.<br><br>Although this power allows the vampire to call someone across a staggering distance, it is most useful when used locally. Even if the desired person books the next available flight, getting to Kyoto from Milwaukee can still take far longer than the vampire needs. Obviously, the individual&rsquo;s financial resources are a factor; if he doesn&rsquo;t have the money to travel quickly, it will take him a far greater time to get there.<br><br>The subject thinks mainly of reaching the vampire, but does not neglect his own well-being. This is less of a consideration if he only has to cross a room, unless he must get through a gang of gun-wielding punks to do so. The individual retains his survival instincts, and while he won&rsquo;t shirk physical violence to reach the vampire&rsquo;s side, he won&rsquo;t subject himself to suicidal situations.<br><br>The Summoning dissipates at dawn. Unless the subject is trained to continue toward the vampire after the first call, the immortal must Summon each night until the target arrives. Still, as long as the vampire is willing and able, she is assured to greet her desired subject some night &mdash; as long as nothing happens to him along the way, of course.</p>","details":"<p>The player spends a blood point and rolls Charisma + Subterfuge. The base difficulty is 5; this increases to difficulty 7 if the subject was met only briefly. If the character used Presence successfully on the target in the past, this difficulty drops to 4, but if the attempt was unsuccessful, the difficulty rises to 8.<br><br><br>The number of successes indicates the subject&rsquo;s speed and attitude in responding:<br><br></p>\n<table border=\"1\"><colgroup><col><col></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Successes</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Botch</td>\n<td>Subject cannot be Summoned by that vampire for the rest of the story.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Failure</td>\n<td>Subject cannot be Summoned by that vampire for the rest of the night.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1 success</td>\n<td>Subject approaches slowly and hesitantly.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2 successes</td>\n<td>Subject approaches reluctantly and is easily thwarted by obstacles.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3 successes</td>\n<td>Subject approaches with reasonable speed.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4 successes</td>\n<td>Subject comes with haste, overcoming any obstacles in his way.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5 successes</td>\n<td>Subject rushes to the vampire, doing anything to get to her.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"charisma","dice2":"subterfuge","bonus":0,"difficulty":"-1","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zn2aienic6k","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Presence","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670331140648,"modifiedTime":1674221180116,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"7LDimHNTF6d1SHEs","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Black Hand Membership","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 111","description":"<p><em>This Background is for Sabbat characters only.</em><br><br>You are a member of the feared Black Hand, the body of soldiers and assassins that serves the Sabbat fervently. Having this Background indicates that you are a full-fledged member of the organization, and you have all the responsibilities and benefits that accompany membership.<br><br>You may call upon members of the Black Hand to aid you, should you ever need it. Of course, this ability is a two-way street, and other Hand members may call upon you to aid them. Thus, you may find yourself assigned to perform assassinations, lend martial aid, or even further the political ends of the Hand as a diplomat or spy. You may also be required to attend crusades that take you away from your pack. All members of the Black Hand must heed the call of another Hand member, especially the superiors of the faction.<br><br>Being a member of the Black Hand is a prestigious matter, and other members of the Sabbat respect the organization. When dealing with other Sabbat, should you choose to reveal your affiliation with the Hand, you may add your rating in this Background to any Social dice pools, even after Status or other Abilities have been taken into account. Most Hand members, however, choose not to reveal their allegiance. The Black Hand is also remarkably adept at hunting down Sabbat who claim membership in the Sect but do not truly belong &mdash; liars, beware.</p>","details":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 238px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 16.782%;\"><col style=\"width: 83.218%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">●</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">You are a grunt; you may call upon&nbsp;one Black Hand member once per&nbsp;story.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px;\">●●</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px;\">You are known and respected in the&nbsp;Black Hand; you may call upon two&nbsp;Black Hand members once per story.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px;\">●●●</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px;\">You are held in the Black Hand&rsquo;s&nbsp;regard; you may call upon five Black&nbsp;Hand members once per story.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 85px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 85px;\">●●●●</td>\n<td style=\"height: 85px;\">You are a hero among members of&nbsp;the Black Hand; you may call upon&nbsp;seven Black Hand members twice per&nbsp;story (but you&rsquo;d better have just cause&nbsp;&mdash; if it seems you&rsquo;re becoming&nbsp;soft, you may lose points in this&nbsp;Background). You may also lead large&nbsp;numbers of Hand members into action&nbsp;should it ever become necessary.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 68px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 68px;\">●●●●●</td>\n<td style=\"height: 68px;\">You are part of Black Hand legend;&nbsp;you may call upon 12 Black Hand&nbsp;members twice per story (but see the&nbsp;preceding caution). You may also lead&nbsp;large numbers of Hand members into&nbsp;action should it ever become&nbsp;necessary. The Seraphim may even &nbsp;seek your counsel on matters of &nbsp;import.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"wod.types.background","level":"","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_14tdb2ntd4k","path":"Backgrounds","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1673844458648,"modifiedTime":1674221071248,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"7NFZnG8yr0vJqx41","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
