{"name":"Lucky (3pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 493","description":"<p>You were born lucky &mdash; or else the Devil looks after his own. Either way, you may repeat any three failed rolls per story, including botches, but you may try only once per failed roll.</p>","details":"<p>Supernatural</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_tbkdk4lk1q","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674440157442,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"7ZXDXEvkN4YmwwDS","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Enemy Brood (3pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 163","description":"<p>You have made an enemy of another group of Nosferatu. Unlike your usual enemies, they know the places you like to go and aren&rsquo;t too squeamish about following you there. They keep you on the move, hunting you from sanctuary to sanctuary. The sewers themselves might not even be safe for you anymore. If you move to a new city, they use their contacts to pass on the word to their allies to keep hounding you. Sooner or later, you are going to have to take them down to rid yourself of them.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vHJSI1w1uvu5im25"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ak5eyy1egoa","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Nosferatu#/CF_SEP/Flaw","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221089727,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"7eCThBunbqr1I7A9","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"● Awe","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 193","description":"<p>Those near the vampire suddenly desire to be closer to her and become receptive to her point of view. Awe is extremely useful for mass communication. It matters little what is said &mdash; the hearts of those affected lean toward the vampire&rsquo;s opinion. The weak want to agree with her; even if the strong-willed resist, they soon find themselves outnumbered. Awe can turn a chancy deliberation into a certain resolution in the vampire&rsquo;s favor almost before her opponents know that the tide has turned.<br><br>Despite the intensity of this attraction, those so smitten do not lose their sense of self-preservation. Danger breaks the spell of fascination, as does leaving the area. Those subject to Awe will remember how they felt in the vampire&rsquo;s presence, however. This will influence their reactions should they ever encounter her again.</p>","details":"<p>The player spends a blood point and rolls Charisma + Performance (difficulty 7). The number of successes rolled determines how many people are affected, as noted on the chart below. If there are more people present than the character can influence, Awe affects those with lower Willpower ratings first. The power stays in effect for the remainder of the scene or until the character chooses to drop it.<br><br></p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 102px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 14.386%;\"><col style=\"width: 85.4386%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\"><strong>Successes</strong></td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">1 Successes</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">One person</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">2 Successes</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">Two people</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">3 Successes</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">Six people</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">4 Successes</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">20 people</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">5 Successes</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">Everyone in the vampire&rsquo;s immediate vicinity (an entire auditorium, a mob)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>Those affected can use Willpower points to overcome the effect, but must continue spending Willpower every scene for as long as they remain in the same area as the vampire. As soon as an individual spends a number of Willpower points equal to the successes rolled, he shakes off the Awe completely and remains unaffected for the rest of the night.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"charisma","dice2":"performance","bonus":0,"difficulty":"7","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zn2aienic6k","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Presence","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670331140648,"modifiedTime":1674221179816,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"7giNsVAayCLX9qIw","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Elemental Mastery","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/mainpower_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 214","description":"<p>This path allows a vampire limited control over and communion with inanimate objects. Elemental Mastery can only be used to affect the unliving &mdash; a vampire could not cause a tree to walk by using Animate the Unmoving, for instance. Thaumaturges who seek mastery over living things generally study paths such as The Green Path (p. 215).</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.disciplinepath","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":0,"isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_jxq3k0gu1p","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/Elemental Mastery","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931741505,"modifiedTime":1674439736994,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"7hKcDvYxcgjyBuEw","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●●  Cloak the Gathering","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 186","description":"<p>At this degree of power, the vampire may extend his concealing abilities to cover an area. The immortal may use any Obfuscate power upon those nearby as well as upon himself, if he wishes.<br><br>Any protected person who compromises the cloak exposes himself to view. Further, if the one who invokes the power gives himself away, the cloak falls from everyone. This power is particularly useful if thevampire needs to bring his retinue through a secure location without drawing the notice of others.</p>","details":"<p>The character may conceal one extra individual for each dot of Stealth he possesses. He may bestow any single Obfuscate power at a given time to the group. While the power applies to everyone under the character&rsquo;s cloak, his player need only make a single roll. Each individual must follow the requirements described under the relevant Obfuscate power to remain under its effect; any person who fails to do so loses the cloak&rsquo;s protection, but doesn&rsquo;t expose the others. Only if the vampire himself errs does the power drop for everyone.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_va4nd0abdk","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Obfuscate","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670294183933,"modifiedTime":1674221177697,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"7krfrgTeTfrXPEme","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Dead Inside (4pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 142","description":"<p>You feel nothing but pain and numbness. While others find ways to make their lives worth living, you sometimes don&rsquo;t get that thrill. Once per session, the Storyteller may cancel any gain of Willpower you made by playing to your Nature or Demeanor</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.FKqLbQ8kxdSwfS2e"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1bn0ry0013fi","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Malkavians","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221087863,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"7qYEy97AE7fvVZ8M","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●● Gift of the Corpse","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 169","description":"<p>This power, one of the most potent on the Corpse in the Monster path, enables a necromancer to ignore most of her race&rsquo;s inherent weaknesses for a short time. A dead body is not particularly vulnerable to sunlight, holy artifacts, frenzy, or being staked through the heart, after all, and so it is with a vampire using the Gift of the Corpse. As with the Cold of the Grave, above, the character using this power takes on an even more deathlike mien. It lasts for less than a minute, typically, but that time may be enough to enable a character to charge through a burning building without fearing frenzy or instant death.</p>","details":"<p>The player spends one Willpower and rolls Stamina + Occult (difficulty 8). For every success, the character can spend one turn in a state in which he is more akin to an animated corpse than a vampire. Holy artifacts and sanctified ground have no effect, and the character is immune to frenzy and R&ouml;tschreck. Sunlight does only bashing damage, and then only if bare skin is exposed on a clear day. Being staked through the heart is only as much of a danger as getting stabbed through his dead spleen would be. Fire harms him only as it would a mortal &mdash; causing lethal damage instead of aggravated.<br><br>Should the character end the power&rsquo;s duration while exposed to any of the aforementioned harmful things, he immediately takes their full effect. If he is staked, he become immobilized; if he is on or near fire, he begins to take the damage a Cainite should take, and he must immediately roll against R&ouml;tschreck.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"stamina","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"8","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.wvvCBIDykkBenEtI"},"cf":{"id":"temp_reojxpqrhd","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Corpse in the Monster","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670842147642,"modifiedTime":1674221168127,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"80ZDQF0ZytpQ4rSd","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Class 2 (armor T-shirt)","type":"Armor","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/armor.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 280","description":"Armor adds its rating to the character’s soak dice pool against bashing damage, lethal damage, and aggravated damage from fangs and claws. It does not protect against fire or sunlight. However, armor also subtracts a number of dice from dice pools related to bodily coordination and agility (most Dexterity-based dice pools). This is reflected in the penalty listing. Attackers may make targeting rolls to hit unprotected portions of a defender and thus ignore the armor (Storyteller assigns difficulty penalty — typically +1 or +2).","details":"","isequipped":false,"ismagical":false,"isweapon":false,"soak":{"bashing":2,"lethal":2,"aggravated":2,"chimerical":{"bashing":0,"lethal":0,"aggravated":0}},"dexpenalty":1,"forms":{"hashomid":true,"hasglabro":false,"hascrinos":false,"hashispo":false,"haslupus":false}},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_626ifvdetzi","path":"Items#/CF_SEP/Armor","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674291929378,"modifiedTime":1674440436115,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"82HF1Yh3Zk4ZtMRc","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●● Rigor Mortis","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 171","description":"<p>One of the first changes that comes over a dead body is rigidity; the corpse becomes stiff as a board, frozen in a single pose. The Cainite who wields Rigor Mortis is able to push a living or undead body to that frozen point using only his will and understanding of the forces of decay. She forces her target to become rigid and unable to move without enormous effort of will, as his very muscles betray him.</p>","details":"<p>The player spends a point of Willpower and rolls Intelligence + Medicine (difficulty 7). Each success freezes the target in place for one turn. A failure simply indicates the loss of the Willpower point, while a botch renders the target immune to powers in the Grave&rsquo;s Decay path for the next 24 hours. The target must be visible and within about 25 yards or meters for this ability to take effect. A frozen target is treated as though he has been staked (see p. 280). With a Willpower roll (difficulty 7) and two successes, the target can break out of the rigor on her turn. Failure causes her a level of bashing damage and means another turn wasted and frozen.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"medicine","bonus":0,"difficulty":"7","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.OK43YIMy3WJt8zRf"},"cf":{"id":"temp_29xrm8dfvtq","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Grave's Decay","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670842147642,"modifiedTime":1674221168936,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"839WFpgqwYavR7aa","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"Feature","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_jgyzexzzmb","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Chimerstry","color":"#000000","name":"Chimerstry","children":[],"folderPath":["temp_444y5utucrj"],"fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":null,"sorting":"a","contents":["V28jw3vP4H8gsUm6","HPJsEwlquaVxm3yq","JybH4gUxVJeWXaw4","u3tA2tsOI9FXkmhI","sxo1dROxtMyyZnQ1","SCdwJCfyiKc434iW"],"version":"2.5.6"}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"iscreated":false,"version":"","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"","description":"","details":"","type":"","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674221159638,"modifiedTime":1674221159946,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"86pITDhHijLQKGwC"}
{"name":"Hold","type":"Melee Weapon","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/naturalweapons.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 276","description":"Hold: This attack inflicts no damage, as the intent is to immobilize rather than injure the subject. On a successful roll, the attacker holds the target until the subject’s next action. At that time, both combatants roll resisted Strength + Brawl actions; the subject remains immobilized (able to take no other action) until she rolls more successes than the attacker does.\n\nTraits: Strength + Brawl\nDifficulty: Normal\nAccuracy: Normal\nDamage: None","details":"","isequipped":false,"ismagical":false,"isweapon":false,"attack":{"attribute":"strength","ability":"brawl","secondaryabilityid":"","accuracy":0,"isrollable":true},"damage":{"attribute":"","bonus":0,"type":"","isrollable":false},"difficulty":"6","conceal":"NA","istwohanded":false,"isnatural":true},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2f06ozkysk3","path":"Items#/CF_SEP/Natural Weapons","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674291063687,"modifiedTime":1674440439758,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"88xxvZD76Bl4qjVd","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●● Burnout","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 225","description":"<p>It is usually easier to destroy than to create, and sensitive electronics are no exception to this rule. Burnout is used to cause a device&rsquo;s power supply (either internal or external) to surge, damaging or destroying the target. Burnout cannot be used to directly injure another individual, although the sudden destruction of a pacemaker or a car&rsquo;s fuel injection control chip can certainly create a health hazard.</p>","details":"<p>A character can use this power at a range of up to 10 times her Willpower in yards or meters, although a +1 difficulty is applied if she is not touching the target item. The number of successes determines the extent of the damage:<br><br></p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 238px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 25.0877%;\"><col style=\"width: 74.7368%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\"><strong>Successes</strong></td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 51px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 51px;\">1 Success</td>\n<td style=\"height: 51px;\">Momentary interruption of operation (one turn), but no permanent damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 51px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 51px;\">2 Successes</td>\n<td style=\"height: 51px;\">Significant loss of function; +1 difficulty to use using the device for the rest of the scene.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px;\">3 Successes</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px;\">The device breaks and is inoperable until repaired.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 51px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 51px;\">4 Successes</td>\n<td style=\"height: 51px;\">Even after repairs, the device&rsquo;s capabilities are diminished (permanent +1 difficulty to use).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px;\">5 Successes</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px;\">The equipment is a total write-off; completely unsalvageable.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>Large enough systems, such as a server cluster or a passenger aircraft, impose a +2 to +4 difficulty (at Storyteller discretion) to affect with this power. Additionally, some systems, such as military and banking networks, may be protected against power surges and spikes, and thus possess one to five dice (Storyteller discretion again) to roll to resist this power. Each success on this roll (difficulty 6) takes away one success from the Thaumaturgy roll.<br><br>Burnout may be used to destroy electronic data storage, in which case three successes destroy all information on the target item, and five erase it beyond any hope of non-magical recovery.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"5","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.20G6Olc0WGsmZpYU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w0iir3wpc8q","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Technomancy","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439746666,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"8Fk2Xkn1KwRQ8mIM","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Tackle (pt. 2)","type":"Melee Weapon","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/naturalweapons.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 277","description":"The attacker rushes her opponent, tackling him to the ground. The attack roll is at +1 difficulty, and the maneuver inflicts Strength +1 damage. Additionally, both combatants must roll Dexterity + Athletics (difficulty 7) or suffer a knockdown (see “Maneuver Complications,” p. 279). Even if the target’s Athletics roll succeeds, he is unbalanced, suffering +1 difficulty to his actions for the next turn.\n\nTraits: Strength + Brawl\nDifficulty: +1\nAccuracy: Normal\nDamage: Strength +1","details":"","isequipped":false,"ismagical":false,"isweapon":false,"attack":{"attribute":"dexterity","ability":"athletics","secondaryabilityid":"","accuracy":0,"isrollable":true},"damage":{"attribute":"strength","bonus":1,"type":"","isrollable":false},"difficulty":"7","conceal":"NA","istwohanded":false,"isnatural":true},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2f06ozkysk3","path":"Items#/CF_SEP/Natural Weapons","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674291445891,"modifiedTime":1674440440243,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"8coZ1s1ydce7krQ6","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●● Verdant Haven","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 216","description":"<p>This power weaves a temporary shelter out of a sufficient amount of plant matter. In addition to providing physical protection from the elements (and even sunlight), the Verdant Haven also establishes a mystical barrier which is nearly impassable to anyone the caster wishes to exclude. A Verdant Haven appears as a six-foot-tall (two-meter-tall) hemisphere of interlocked branches, leaves, and vines with no discernible opening, and even to the casual observer it appears to be an unnatural construction. Verdant Havens are rumored to have supernatural healing properties, hut no Kindred have reported experiencing such benefits from a stay in one.</p>","details":"<p>A character must be standing in a heavily vegetated area to use this power. The Verdant Haven springs up around the character over the course of three turns. Once the haven is established, anyone wishing to enter the haven without the caster&rsquo;s permission must achieve more than the caster&rsquo;s original number of successes on a single roll of Wits + Survival (difficulty equal to the caster&rsquo;s Willpower). The haven lasts until the next sunset, or until the caster dispels or leaves it. If the caster scored four or more successes, the haven is impenetrable to sunlight unless physically breached.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"7","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.KTQqbyzHjXSAk9f0"},"cf":{"id":"temp_khzqb46fpao","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Green Path","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439741090,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"8lRX9hUtps8kKGjm","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Resources","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 115","description":"<p>Resources are valuable goods whose disposition your character controls. These assets may be actual cash, but as this Background increases, they&rsquo;re more likely to be investments, property, or earning capital of some sort &mdash; land, industrial assets, stocks and bonds, commercial inventories, criminal infrastructure, contraband, even taxes or tithes. Remember that vampires don&rsquo;t need to arrange for any food except blood and their actual needs (as opposed to wants) for shelter are very easily accommodated. Resources for vampires go mostly to pay for luxuries and the associated expenses of developing and maintaining Status, Influence, and other Backgrounds. A character with no dots in Resources may have enough clothing and supplies to get by, or she may be destitute and squatting in a refrigerator box under an overpass.<br><br>You receive a basic allowance each month based on your rating, so be certain to detail exactly where this money comes from, be it a job, trust fund or dividends. (Storytellers, decide for your locality and any relevant time period what an appropriate amount of cash this monthly allowance is.) After all, a Kindred&rsquo;s fortune may well run out over the course of the chronicle, depending on how well he maintains it. You can also sell your less liquid resources if you need the cash, but this can take weeks or even months, depending on what exactly you&rsquo;re trying to sell. Art buyers don&rsquo;t just pop out of the woodwork, after all.<br><br><br></p>","details":"<p>Players may purchase Resources for their characterswith pooled Background points.<br><br></p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 16.782%;\"><col style=\"width: 83.218%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>●</td>\n<td>Sufficient. You can maintain a typical&nbsp;residence in the style of the working&nbsp;class with stability, even if spending&nbsp;sprees come seldom.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>●●</td>\n<td>Moderate. You can display yourself&nbsp;as a member in good standing of the&nbsp;middle class, with the occasional gift&nbsp;and indulgence seemly for a person&nbsp;of even higher station. You can&nbsp;maintain a servant or hire specific&nbsp;help as necessary. A fraction of your&nbsp;resources are available in cash,&nbsp;readily portable property (like jewelry&nbsp;or furniture), and other valuables&nbsp;(such as a car or modest home) that&nbsp;let you maintain a standard of living&nbsp;at the one-dot level wherever you&nbsp;happen to be, for up to six months.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>●●●</td>\n<td>Comfortable. You are a prominent&nbsp;and established member of your&nbsp;community, with land and an owned&nbsp;dwelling, and you have a reputation&nbsp;that lets you draw on credit at very&nbsp;generous terms. You likely have more&nbsp;tied up in equity and property than&nbsp;you do in ready cash. You can&nbsp;maintain a one-dot quality of&nbsp;existence wherever you are without&nbsp;difficulty, for as long as you choose.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>●●●●</td>\n<td>Wealthy. You rarely touch cash, as&nbsp;most of your assets exist in tangible&nbsp;forms that are themselves more&nbsp;valuable and stable than paper&nbsp;money. You hold more wealth than&nbsp;many of your local peers (if they can&nbsp;be called such a thing). When&nbsp;earning your Resources doesn&rsquo;t&nbsp;enjoy your usual degree of attention,&nbsp;you can maintain a three-dot&nbsp;existence for up to a year, and a two-&nbsp;dot existence indefinitely.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>●●●●●</td>\n<td>Extremely Wealthy. You are the&nbsp;model to which others strive to&nbsp;achieve, at least in the popular mind.&nbsp;Television shows, magazine spreads,&nbsp;and gossip websites speculate about&nbsp;your clothing, the appointments of&nbsp;your numerous homes, and the luxury&nbsp;of your modes of transportation. You have vast and widely distributed&nbsp;assets, perhaps tied to the fates of&nbsp;nations, each with huge staffs and&nbsp;connections to every level of&nbsp;society through a region. You&nbsp;travel with a minimum of three-dot&nbsp;comforts, more with a little effort.&nbsp;Corporations and governments&nbsp;sometimes come to you to buy into&nbsp;stocks or bond programs.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"wod.types.background","level":"","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_14tdb2ntd4k","path":"Backgrounds","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1673844458648,"modifiedTime":1674221072047,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"8q3NbEVh3RRa9HCj","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
