{"name":"Fury's Focus (3pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 48","description":"<p><em><strong>Prerequisite: Path of Entelechy</strong></em><br><br>Brujah who have devoted themselves to mastering their frenzies through the Path of Entelechy sometimes find tangible benefits resulting from their efforts. A Brujah with this Merit may briefly delay the full onset of frenzy</p>","details":"<p>The player spends a Willpower point at the onset of frenzy and then rolls the Brujah&rsquo;s Entelechy rating. The difficulty is one higher than the original roll to resist frenzy. The Brujah still frenzies, but the player controls her character&rsquo;s actions for one turn per success. Furthermore, when the period of partial control ends and the Brujah loses control, the difficulty of any degeneration rolls triggered by sins committed during the frenzy are reduced by the number of successes rolled, to a minimum difficulty of 4.</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.DbmgdklRlnpv3TJg"},"cf":{"id":"temp_xu302tg7wm7","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Brujah","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221081739,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"8yTHNma02XmBSwxD","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Tackle (pt. 1)","type":"Melee Weapon","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/naturalweapons.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 277","description":"The attacker rushes her opponent, tackling him to the ground. The attack roll is at +1 difficulty, and the maneuver inflicts Strength +1 damage. Additionally, both combatants must roll Dexterity + Athletics (difficulty 7) or suffer a knockdown (see “Maneuver Complications,” p. 279). Even if the target’s Athletics roll succeeds, he is unbalanced, suffering +1 difficulty to his actions for the next turn.\n\nTraits: Strength + Brawl\nDifficulty: +1\nAccuracy: Normal\nDamage: Strength +1","details":"","isequipped":false,"ismagical":false,"isweapon":false,"attack":{"attribute":"dexterity","ability":"brawl","secondaryabilityid":"","accuracy":0,"isrollable":true},"damage":{"attribute":"strength","bonus":1,"type":"","isrollable":true},"difficulty":"7","conceal":"NA","istwohanded":false,"isnatural":true},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2f06ozkysk3","path":"Items#/CF_SEP/Natural Weapons","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674291445891,"modifiedTime":1674440440148,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"92MiE58odr8UP23m","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●● Mesmerize","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 153","description":"<p>With this power, a vampire can verbally implant a false thought or hypnotic suggestion in the subject&rsquo;s subconscious mind. Both Kindred and target must be free from distraction, since Mesmerize requires intense concentration and precise wording to be effective. The vampire may activate the imposed thought immediately or establish a stimulus that will trigger it later. The victim must be able to understand the vampire, though the two need to maintain eye contact only as long as it takes to implant the idea.<br><br>Mesmerize allows for anything from simple, precise directives (handing over an item) to complex, highly involved ones (taking notes of someone&rsquo;s habits and relaying that information at an appointed time). It is not useful for planting illusions or false memories (such as seeing a rabbit or believing yourself to be on fire). A subject can have only one suggestion implanted at any time.</p>","details":"<p>The player rolls Manipulation + Leadership (difficulty equal to the target&rsquo;s current Willpower points). The number of successes determines how well the suggestion takes hold in the victim&rsquo;s subconscious. If the vampire scores one or two successes, the subject cannot be forced to do anything that seems strange to her (she might walk outside, but is unlikely to steal a car). At three or four successes, the command is effective unless following it endangers the subject. At five successes or greater, the vampire can implant nearly any sort of command.<br><br>No matter how strong the Kindred&rsquo;s will, his command cannot force the subject to harm herself directly or defy her innate Nature. So, while a vampire who scored five successes could make a 98-pound weakling attack a 300-pound bouncer, he could not make the mortal shoot herself in the head.<br><br>If a vampire tries to Mesmerize a subject before the target fulfills a previously implanted directive, compare the successes rolled to those gained during the implanting of the first suggestion. Whichever roll had the greater number of successes is the command that now governs in the target&rsquo;s behavior; the other suggestion is wiped clean. If the successes rolled are equal, the newer command supplants the old one.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"manipulation","dice2":"leadership","bonus":0,"difficulty":"-1","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4wvty5nf9hd","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Dominate","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670227736590,"modifiedTime":1674221161400,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"96FA9PzH9rvOe889","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●● Soul Stealing","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 164","description":"<p>This power affects the living, not the dead. It does, however, temporarily turn a living soul into a sort of wraith, as it allows a necromancer to strip a soul from a living body. A mortal exiled from his body by this power becomes a wraith with a single tie to the real world: his now-empty body.</p>","details":"<p>The player spends a point of Willpower and then makes a contested Willpower roll against the intended victim (difficulty 6). Successes indicate the number of hours during which the original soul is forced out of its housing. The body itself remains autonomically alive but catatonic.<br><br>This power can be used to create suitable hosts for Daemonic Possession. It has no effect on Kindred or other supernatural creatures (except ghouls) until such creatures are dead &ndash; in the case of vampires, this means Final Death.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"6","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.x7TyMvPCvX2P7IOL"},"cf":{"id":"temp_9h9qdp1h3gj","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Bone Path","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670842147642,"modifiedTime":1674221166117,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"9AXB3cpp0PEhhEc2","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Heartless (4pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 67","description":"<p>You have lost your heart. Either you removed it via The Heart of Darkness (see V20, p. 210), or an elder did it to you, but either way you no longer have easy access to it. The heart might be in the possession of a foe, or simply missing. If it turns out that a Cainite possesses the heart (say a Setite elder, or your sire) you must obey their every command. If it&rsquo;s merely missing, the anxiety and obsession to find it interferes with your nightly existence, and may increase the difficulty of Willpower rolls by +1 at Storyteller discretion.&nbsp;</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.28JiCemvASqixsXE"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8mau8cmb57t","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Followers of Set","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221083199,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"9DwjT3BjOiiK5HAp","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●● Dependence","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 223","description":"<p>Many former pawns of Clan Tremere claim to have felt a strange sensation similar to depression when not in the presence of their masters. This is usually attributed to the blood bond, but is sometimes the result of the vampire&rsquo;s mastery of Dependence. The final power of the Path of Corruption enables the vampire to tie her victim&rsquo;s soul to her own, engendering feelings of lethargy and helplessness when the victim is not in her presence or acting to further her desires.</p>","details":"<p>The character engages the target in conversation. The player rolls normally. The victim rolls Self-Control/Instinct (difficulty equals the number of successes scored by the caster + 3). Failure means that the victim&rsquo;s psyche has been subtly bonded to that of the thaumaturge for one night per success rolled by the caster.<br><br>A bonded victim is no less likely to attack his controller, and feels no particular positive emotions toward her. However, he is psychologically addicted to her presence, and suffers a one-die penalty to all rolls when he is not around her or performing tasks for her. Additionally, he is much less resistant to her commands, and his dice pools are halved when he attempts to resist her Dominate, Presence (or other mental or emotional control powers), or mundane Social rolls. Finally, he is unable to regain Willpower when he is not in the thaumaturge&rsquo;s presence.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"8","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_lcnzlnkbov","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Corruption","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439744886,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"9E6akUkM8fmk95bk","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Eyes of the Grave","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 179","description":"<p>This ritual, which takes two hours to cast, causes the target to experience intermittent visions of her death over the period of a week. The visions come without warning and can last up to a minute. The caster of the ritual has no idea what the visions contain, as only the victim sees them. Each time a vision manifests, the target must roll Courage (difficulty 7) or be reduced to quivering panic. The visions, which come randomly, can also interfere with activities such as driving, studying, shooting, and so on.<br><br>Eyes of the Grave requires a pinch of soil from a fresh grave.</p>","details":"<p>Casting times for necromantic rituals vary widely; see the description for particulars. The player rolls Intelligence + Occult (difficulty 3 + the level of the ritual, maximum 9). Success indicates the ritual proceeds smoothly, failure produces no effect, and a botch indicates something has gone horribly wrong.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"5","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_b17ggxg6joc","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 2 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670899739755,"modifiedTime":1674221173473,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"9bPIw3wetCtO9vJa","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"● Silence of Death (Vizier)","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 26","description":"<p>Many Assamites claim never to have heard their targets&rsquo; death screams. Silence of Death imbues the vampire with a mystical silence that radiates from her body, muting all noise within a certain vicinity. No sound occurs inside this zone, though sounds originating outside the area of effect may be heard by anyone in it. Rumors abound of certain skilled Assamite viziers who have the ability to silence a location rather than a circumference that follows them, but no proof of this has been forthcoming.</p>","details":"<p>Once the zone of silence is activated, the vizier can decide whom, if anyone, can hear him when he speaks. Thus, while the power is active, he can allow one or more people to hear him while no one else can. More importantly, he can deliver instructions backed by Presence or Dominate without anyone else noticing.<br><br><em><strong>Original - Warrior Version:</strong></em><br>This power (which costs one blood point to activate) maintains a 20-foot (6-meter) radius of utter stillness around the Kindred for one hour.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.aJQ4CALXjDITPxbR"},"cf":{"id":"temp_i58eczenhcp","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Quietus#/CF_SEP/Quietus (Vizier)","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670332666414,"modifiedTime":1674221183909,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"9tbmauW8CI3jaj0f","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Critters (2pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 182","description":"<p>You&rsquo;re excellent with animals &mdash; so much so that they constantly seek to befriend you. Wherever you go, the animals are happy to see you, and more often than not, happy to help you when you ask for their aid. You receive a bonus die on Social rolls to affect small animals. Further, animal companions who have had continual interaction with you see you as something of a pet, and occasionally bring you small useful things. Once per game session, animals will bring you a useful piece of information or a small item relevant to events. This item might occasionally play into the individual Ravnos&rsquo; particular vice, as the animals quickly pick up on what pleases their friend.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.iGFbYRukWee1s96g"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ah1xgfy02pt","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Ravnos","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221092694,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"ADFtquzqDi9rL8kX","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●● Subsume the Spirit","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 131","description":"<p>By locking his gaze with that of an animal, the vampire may mentally possess the creature. Some elders believe that since animals don&rsquo;t have souls but spirits, the vampire can move his own soul into the animal&rsquo;s body. Many younger vampires think it a matter of transferring one&rsquo;s consciousness into the animal&rsquo;s mind. In either case, it&rsquo;s agreed that the beast&rsquo;s weaker spirit (or mind) is pushed aside by the Kindred&rsquo;s own consciousness. The vampire&rsquo;s body falls into a motionless state akin to torpor while his mind takes control of the animal&rsquo;s actions, remaining this way until the Kindred&rsquo;s consciousness returns.<br><br>Some haughty Tzimisce eschew this power, considering it debasing to enter the body of a lesser creature. When they do stoop to using it, they possess only predators. Conversely, Gangrel revel in connecting to the natural world in this way. They delight in sampling different animals&rsquo; natures.</p>","details":"<p>The player rolls Manipulation + Animal Ken (difficulty 8) as the character looks into the animal&rsquo;s eyes (see sidebar on p. 152). The number of successes allows the character to employ some mental Disciplines while possessing the animal, as noted below.</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 187px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 20.3509%;\"><col style=\"width: 79.4737%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\"><strong>Successes</strong></td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">1 Success</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">Cannot use Disciplines</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">2 Successes</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">Can use Auspex and other sensory powers</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px;\">3 Successes</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px;\">Can also use Presence and other powers of emotional manipulation</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 51px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 51px;\">4 Successes</td>\n<td style=\"height: 51px;\">Can also use Dementation, Dominate, and other powers of mental manipulation</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 51px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 51px;\">5 Successes</td>\n<td style=\"height: 51px;\">Can also use Chimerstry, Necromancy, Thaumaturgy, and other mystical powers</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>This power entwines the character&rsquo;s consciousness closely with the animal&rsquo;s spirit, so much so that the character may continue to think and feel like that animal even after breaking the connection. This effect continues until the character spends a total of seven nights or three Willpower points to resist and finally overcome the animal nature. This should be roleplayed, though the character will be affected to a lesser degree if the player chooses to spend Willpower.<br><br>At the end of any particularly exciting incident during possession, the player rolls Wits + Empathy (difficulty 8) for the character to retain his own mind. Failure indicates that the character&rsquo;s mind returns to his own body, but still thinks in purely animalistic terms. A botch returns the character to his body, and also sends him into frenzy.<br><br>The character may travel as far from his own physical body as he chooses while possessing the animal. The character retains no conscious connection with his vampire body during this time, though. The vampire may also venture out during the day, albeit in the animal&rsquo;s body. However, the character&rsquo;s own body must be awake to do so, requiring a successful roll to remain awake (see p. 262). If the character leaves the animal&rsquo;s body (by choice, if his body falls asleep, or after sustaining significant injury), the vampire&rsquo;s consciousness returns to his physical form instantaneously.<br><br>Although the vampire has no conscious link to his body while possessing the animal, he does form a sympathetic bond. Anything the animal feels, the vampire also experiences, from pleasure to pain. In fact, any damage the animal&rsquo;s body sustains is also applied to the character&rsquo;s body, though the Kindred body may soak as normal. If the animal dies before the vampire&rsquo;s soul can flee from the body, the character&rsquo;s body falls into torpor. Presumably this is in sympathetic response to the massive trauma of death, but some Kindred believe that the vampire&rsquo;s soul is cast adrift during this time and must find its way back to the body.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"manipulation","dice2":"animalken","bonus":0,"difficulty":"8","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_iu0zv3lhu5i","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Animalism","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670225214947,"modifiedTime":1674221156710,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"ADPnzI0R9b8IC5qc","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Early Riser (1pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 480","description":"<p>No one can explain it, but you seem to have the ability to work on less rest than your fellow vampires. You always seem to be the first to rise and the last to go to bed even if you&rsquo;re been out until dawn. Your Humanity or Path score is considered to be 10 for purposes of deciding when you rise each evening. Vampires with this Merit cannot take the Deep Sleeper Flaw.</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1a3wwhsmx3r","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672364948802,"modifiedTime":1674439880577,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"AE4eb4YhRFnBKodq","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●● Torment","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 162","description":"<p>It is through the use of this power that powerful necromancers convince bound ghosts to behave &mdash; or else.<br><br>Torment allows the vampire to strike a wraith as if he himself were in the lands of the dead, inflicting damage on the wraith&rsquo;s ectoplasmic form. The vampire remains in the real world, however, so he cannot be struck in return.</p>","details":"<p>The player rolls Stamina + Empathy (difficulty equal to the wraith&rsquo;s current Willpower points), and the vampire reaches out to strike the wraith. Each success inflicts a level of lethal damage on the wraith. Should the wraith lose all health levels, it immediately vanishes into what appears to be a doorway to some hideous nightmare realm. Ghosts &ldquo;destroyed&rdquo; thus cannot reappear in or near the real world for a month.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"stamina","dice2":"empathy","bonus":0,"difficulty":"-1","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6fvqbb4wn0f","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Sepulchre Path","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670842147642,"modifiedTime":1674221170255,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"ALEXxE8YMwfZBpb4","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●● The Crone's Pride","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 227","description":"<p>This power inflicts the curse of the crone, who bound Caine to her as he fled his wife&rsquo;s spurning. Hideously ugly, the crone had to resort to trickery to get others to help or serve her.</p>","details":"<p>This power reduces the target&rsquo;s Appearance to zero. All Social rolls during this time generally fail, unless the character attempts to intimidate or browbeat the subject. This power lasts for one night.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"5","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.zLeChDr3fyZSMX8g"},"cf":{"id":"temp_cnqt60rshz","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of the Father's Vegeance","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439747691,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"AMZgKjv0leT97ytc","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Tic/Twitch (1pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 481","description":"<p>You have some sort of repetitive motion that you make in times of stress, and it&rsquo;s a dead giveaway as to your identity. Examples include a nervous cough, constantly wringing your hands, cracking your knuckles, and so on. It costs one Willpower to refrain from engaging in your tic.</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_jwd9ok2vgth","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672365603221,"modifiedTime":1674221103514,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"AMoYL3nJSICvm1UA","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
