{"name":"The Path of Corruption","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/mainpower_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 221","description":"<p>The origins of this path are hotly debated among those who are familiar with its intricacies. One theory holds that its secrets were taught to the Tremere by demons and that use of it brings the practitioner dangerously close to the infernal powers. A second opinion has been advanced that the Path of Corruption is a holdover from the days when Clan Tremere was still mortal. The third theory, and the most disturbing to the Tremere, is that the path originated with the Followers of Set, and that knowledge of its workings was sold to the Tremere for an unspecified price. This last rumor is vehemently denied by the Tremere, which automatically makes it a favorite topic of discussion when the matter comes up.<br><br>The Path of Corruption is primarily a mentally and spiritually oriented path centered on influencing the psyches of other individuals. It can be used neither to issue commands like Dominate nor to change emotions in the moment like Presence. Rather, it produces a gradual and subtle twisting of the subject&rsquo;s actions, morals, and thought processes. This path deals intimately with deception and dark desires, and those who work through it must understand the hidden places of the heart. Accordingly, no character may have a higher rating in the Path of Corruption than he has in Subterfuge.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.disciplinepath","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":0,"isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_lcnzlnkbov","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Corruption","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671026215029,"modifiedTime":1674439745020,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"AOzmsx09C5W6SmBM","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Sympathizer (1pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 490","description":"<p>You have publicly expressed sympathy for some of the goals and policies of the enemies of your Sect. Your outspoken views on the subject have made you suspect in the eyes of the city&rsquo;s hierarchy, and you may be suspected of (or arrested for) treason.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_jwd9ok2vgth","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221103415,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"AZ4qzWxggYNk6f8i","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●● Theft of Vitae","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 214","description":"<p>A thaumaturge using this power siphons vitae from her subject. She need never come in contact with the subject &mdash; blood literally streams out in a physical torrent from the subject to the Kindred (though it is often mystically absorbed and need not enter through the mouth).</p>","details":"<p>The number of successes determines how many blood points the caster transfers from the subject. The subject must be visible to the thaumaturge and within 50 feet (15 meters). Using this power prevents the caster from being blood-bound, but otherwise counts as if the vampire ingested the blood herself. This power is spectacularly obvious, and Camarilla princes justifiably consider its public use a breach of the Masquerade.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"7","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_v3rmtx67pm","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Blood","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670930910577,"modifiedTime":1674439742775,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"Aa9ORd3I60VkoYS3","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Hunted (4pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 491","description":"<p>You are pursued by a fanatical witch-hunter who believes (perhaps correctly) that you are a danger to humanity. All those with whom you associate, be they mortal or Kindred, may be hunted as well.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ry8o03n5zsc","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/4 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221110577,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"AcqLnvR1jnjKZknM","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
