{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"Feature","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_81150czgfr","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000","name":"3 pt. Flaws","children":[],"folderPath":["temp_zbxadbcq32d","temp_hv8df9kilvf"],"fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":null,"sorting":"a","contents":["o6v2QHLY80jL8SCv","6S0qTtSgJTrGoDdF","3gG0rtevjJjtlykG","LjsRXbbQ23YSV24l","UaOlfHRQVwGPmGPq","s1FQODFajA6ZVp1i","ssljhPJTUEvdikCl","kwZoRodshQZgygXU","Q1KbRWjXM3n21ACE","HEqBK0rvl9hDztCA","CaWlciOyfQQTdg9d","d5AzMAyahzF4sdCk","ECswcee7IkO0pC62","kgiHEHJQInznFCLo","lxmiJfzv0i7tIn1x","thuYSMkb2DPvxXtm","jfZpvnDQaeD0ZAfJ","AOmMqEScAM3jeFbf","cZFEczCCHA4TOnSS"],"version":"2.5.6"}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"iscreated":false,"version":"","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"","description":"","details":"","type":"","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674221109358,"modifiedTime":1674221109695,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"D17hOJ1xoeeR6TkQ"}
{"name":"●●● Dagon's Call (Vizier)","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 27","description":"<p>The sorcerer and vizier equivalents for Dagon&rsquo;s Call both work the same. Instead of ravaging the target&rsquo;s body, the Assamite harrows the mind.&nbsp;<br><br><em><strong>Original - Warrior Version:</strong></em><br>This terrible power allows a vampire to drown her target in his own blood. By concentrating, the Kindred bursts her target&rsquo;s blood vessels and fills his lungs with vitae that strangles him from within. The blood actually constricts the target&rsquo;s body from the inside as it floods through his system; thus, it works even on unbreathing Kindred. Until the target collapses in agony or death throes, this power has no visible effect, and many Kindred like it because it leaves no trace of their presence.</p>","details":"<p>Mechanically, this power works the same as the warrior version except as follows: First, the roll is the Assamite&rsquo;s Manipulation versus the target&rsquo;s Intelligence. The difficulty for both rolls is the other&rsquo;s permanent Willpower. Second, instead of inflicting lethal damage, each net success for the Assamite strips the target of temporary Willpower. If the Assamite spends a Willpower point and continues to roll even after the target has lost all her temporary Willpower, additional successes strip the target of one dot of permanent Willpower. This represents the most damage that this power can inflict in a single night regardless of successes, but a target who has lost all of her Willpower dots through use of Dagon&rsquo;s Call on successive nights is reduced to a mindless husk.<br><br>As with the warrior version, the Assamite need not be within the target&rsquo;s presence to trigger this attack.<br><br><em><strong>Original - Warrior Version:</strong></em><br>The vampire must touch her target prior to using Dagon&rsquo;s Call. Within an hour thereafter, the vampire may issue the call, though she need not be in the presence or even in the line of sight of her target.<br><br></p>\n<p>Invoking the power costs one Willpower point. The Kindred&rsquo;s player makes a contested Stamina roll against the target&rsquo;s Stamina; the difficulty of each roll is equal to the opponent&rsquo;s permanent Willpower rating. The number of successes the vampire using Dagon&rsquo;s Call achieves is the amount of lethal damage, in health levels, the victim suffers. For an additional point of Willpower spent in the next turn, the vampire may continue using Dagon&rsquo;s Call by engaging in another contested Stamina roll. So long as the Kindred&rsquo;s player continues to spend Willpower, the character may continue rending her opponent from within.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"stamina","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"-1","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.TqIPmjRHbcbwU46y"},"cf":{"id":"temp_i58eczenhcp","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Quietus#/CF_SEP/Quietus (Vizier)","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670332666414,"modifiedTime":1674221184110,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"D6HWtxfEG7xPBMy5","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"● Decay","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 217","description":"<p>This power accelerates the decrepitude of its target, causing it to wither, rot, or otherwise break down. The target must be inanimate, though dead organic matter can be affected.</p>","details":"<p>If the roll is successful, the inanimate object touched by the thaumaturge ages 10 years for every minute the Kindred touches it. If the vampire breaks physical contact and wishes to age the object again, another blood point must be spent and another roll must be made. This power does not affect vampires.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"4","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qrx4b8dkuga","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/Hands of Destruction","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439737510,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"DBIV1w1yzXd9s6NV","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Infectious (3pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 142","description":"<p>Madness flows within your blood, but your bite carries a taint as well. Mortals take a temporary derangement for every three points of blood you take from them. The derangements stay until the mortal restores the lost blood.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.FKqLbQ8kxdSwfS2e"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1bn0ry0013fi","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Malkavians","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221088057,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"DCyCdmVUnyTfImqA","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Bruiser (1pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 480","description":"<p>Your appearance is sufficiently thug-like to inspire fear (or at least disquiet) in those who see you. While you&rsquo;re not necessarily ugly, you do radiate a quiet menace, to the point where people cross the street to avoid passing near you. All Intimidation rolls against those who have not demonstrated their physical superiority to you are at -1 difficulty.</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1a3wwhsmx3r","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672364948802,"modifiedTime":1674439879446,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"DG4c1gjiVhfp078X","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●●  Majesty","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 196","description":"<p>At this stage, the vampire can augment her supernatural mien a thousandfold. The attractive become paralyzingly beautiful; the homely become hideously twisted. Majesty inspires universal respect, devotion, fear &mdash; or all those emotions at once &mdash; in those around the vampire. The weak scramble to obey her every whim, and even the most dauntless find it almost impossible to deny her.<br><br>People affected find the vampire so formidable that they dare not risk her displeasure. Raising their voices to her is difficult; raising a hand against her is unthinkable. Those few who shake off the vampire&rsquo;s potent mystique enough to oppose her are shouted down by the many under her thrall, before the immortal need even respond.<br><br>Under Majesty&rsquo;s influence, hearts break, power trembles, and the bold shake. Wise Kindred use this power with caution against mortal and immortal alike. While Majesty can cow influential politicians and venerable Primogen, the vampire must be careful that doing so doesn&rsquo;t come back to haunt her. After all, a dignitary brought<br>low before others loses his usefulness quickly, while a humiliated Kindred has centuries to plan revenge.</p>","details":"<p>No roll is required on the part of the vampire, but she must spend a Willpower point. A subject must make a Courage roll (difficulty equal to the vampire&rsquo;s Charisma + Intimidation, to a maximum of 10) if he wishes to be rude or simply contrary to the vampire. Success allows the individual to act normally for the moment, although he feels the weight of the vampire&rsquo;s displeasure crushing down on him. A subject who fails the roll aborts his intended action and even goes to absurd lengths to humble himself before the vampire,<br>no matter who else is watching. The effects of Majesty last for one scene.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_zn2aienic6k","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Presence","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670331140648,"modifiedTime":1674221180215,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"DGhJHNYzQmHsj5Df","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Dynamic Personality (5pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 48","description":"<p>Your natural charisma draws mortals to you like groupies to a rock star. Consequently, it is easier for you to acquire certain Backgrounds related to mortals.&nbsp;</p>","details":"<p>&nbsp;In addition to any Backgrounds acquired at character creation or through roleplay, you can purchase new Backgrounds with experience points at the end of each story. The available Backgrounds are Allies, Contacts, Herd, Retainers, and each new dot costs the current rating in experience points.&nbsp;</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xu302tg7wm7","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Brujah","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221081637,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"DbmgdklRlnpv3TJg","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Bioluminescence (1pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 238","description":"<p>Perhaps through biological expertise, or perhaps by unlocking something primordial within, you have accessed the secrets of bioluminescence. Using the Vicissitude, you may grant yourself (through Malleable Visage) or others (via Fleshcraft &mdash; both as per V20, p. 241) the ability to emit a soft glow. With muscle control and practice, you can control the color and pattern of the illumination. This can light a soft glow in the dark, create beautiful displays, or even act as a primal form of communication. Some Fiends grant their ghouls or childer bioluminescence, developing an eerily nuanced and wordless language with their thralls and broods. Only characters with at least one dot of Vicissitude may purchase this Merit.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_g4msmdkn9lw","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Tzimisce#/CF_SEP/Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221098871,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"DfqXMuuiPM1CBqSB","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Domino of Life","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 231","description":"<p>A vampire wanting or needing to simulate a human characteristic can do so once Domino of Life is cast. For one entire night, the vampire can eat, breathe, maintain a normal body temperature, assume a human flesh tone, or display some other single trait of humankind she desires. Note that only one trait can be replicated in this fashion. The vampire must have a vial of fresh human blood on his person to maintain this ritual.</p>","details":"<p>Using this ritual adds one die to the caster&rsquo;s dice pools when attempting to pass as human. Unless onlookers are especially wary, the Domino of Life should fool them into thinking the caster is mortal &mdash; not that they should have any reason to suspect otherwise.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"4","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_q5ajxrpsb3","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 1 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671081485306,"modifiedTime":1674439750325,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"DlGcYlB3kzsEZ2hU","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Daredevil (3pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 480","description":"<p>You are good at taking risks, and even better at surviving them. When attempting exceptionally risky non-combat actions (such as leaping from one moving car to another), characters with this Merit add an additional three dice to their rolls, and negate a single botch die that may result from such a roll. Generally, such actions must be at least difficulty 8 and have the potential to inflict at least three health levels of damage if failed. (3pt. Merit)</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tbkdk4lk1q","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672364948802,"modifiedTime":1674440156476,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"DzaRVp57BIXqXIQS","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Inoffensive to Animals (1pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 493","description":"<p>With rare exceptions, animals usually despise the Kindred. Some flee, others attack, but all dislike being in the presence of a vampire. You have no such problem. Animals may not enjoy being in your company, but they don&rsquo;t actively flee from you.</p>","details":"<p>Supernatural</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1a3wwhsmx3r","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674439881896,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"E4kJnIj052KttRCy","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Dead Man's Hand","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 183","description":"<p>The necromancer takes a rag stained in the blood, sweat, or tears of the intended victim. She takes a freshly severed human hand (which can come either from a corpse or a living &ldquo;donor&rdquo;) and closes it around the rag. As the hand decomposes, so does the victim. His flesh bloats, turns gray and then green, then starts to slough off. The victim&rsquo;s brain remains fresh until the very end, so he can see the maggots writhe in the putrescent rack of meat that once was his healthy body.<br><br>The necromancer makes the standard roll and spends two blood points for each point of Stamina (and Fortitude) possessed by the victim. The victim loses health levels according to the timetable below. Only the removal of the rag from the hand can stop the process. If this happens, health levels return, also according to the chart below.<br><br><br></p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 31.5682%;\"><col style=\"width: 68.4318%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Health Level</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Time Until Next Loss</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Bruised</td>\n<td>12 hours</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Hurt</td>\n<td>12 hours</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Injured</td>\n<td>Six hours</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Wounded</td>\n<td>Three hours</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mauled</td>\n<td>One hour</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Crippled</td>\n<td>30 minutes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Incapacitated</td>\n<td>&nbsp;12 hours</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>Mortal characters who suffer more than 12 hours of incapacitation die, while Kindred who remain Incapacitated for more than 12 hours succumb to torpor.</p>","details":"<p>Casting times for necromantic rituals vary widely; see the description for particulars. The player rolls Intelligence + Occult (difficulty 3 + the level of the ritual, maximum 9). Success indicates the ritual proceeds smoothly, failure produces no effect, and a botch indicates something has gone horribly wrong.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"8","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0bc6awa1kzcg","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 5 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670899739755,"modifiedTime":1674221176584,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"EBPU89GD73t6zYnU","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Short Fuse (2pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 486","description":"<p>You are easily angered. Difficulties to avoid frenzy are two greater. Brujah vampires cannot take this Flaw, as they already suffer from a similar weakness.</p>","details":"<p>Mental</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vuUhXjpBnaswkR2e"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2wewy46vpbx","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/2 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221106174,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"EBQeqSvKaxP5COWj","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Narc (3pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 492","description":"<p>You are known to be a snitch, an informer firmly planted in the pocket of the vampires in charge. Those on whom you might yet inform loathe you as a result, feeding you misinformation when they can in an attempt to discredit you. Given the opportunity, they might do you mischief. Regardless, your reputation as a weasel precedes you, putting you at +1 difficulty on all Social rolls against those who don&rsquo;t agree with your politics.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_81150czgfr","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221108529,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"ECswcee7IkO0pC62","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"○ Eye Contact","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 152","description":"<p>Many myths and stories exist about a vampire&rsquo;s mystical ability to put people under her spell by looking deeply into her victim&rsquo;s eyes. The persistence of such stories through the ages isn&rsquo;t surprising, since a number of Kindred Disciplines powers (most notably Dominate) require eye contact in order to work. Other vampires, learning of this requirement, have attempted everything from wearing mirrored sunglasses to gouging out their own eyes in order to prevent an elder from exerting his will upon them.<br><br>But Kindred are not so easily thwarted.<br><br>The need for eye contact stems from the aggressor Kindred&rsquo;s need to see his victim&rsquo;s soul, and the eyes are the traditionally known as the windows to the soul. While the vampire needs to capture his target&rsquo;s attention, the target&rsquo;s eyes need not be present for such a power to work (although the arts of the Tzimisce make this somewhat challenging at times) &mdash; they only need to find the soul of his victim laid bare.</p>","details":"<p>A target trying to avoid eye contact can make a Willpower roll against a difficulty equal to Dominate user&rsquo;s Manipulation + Intimidation (or other appropriate combination for other Disciplines or specific situations, at the Storyteller&rsquo;s discretion). The difficulty may be reduced for mitigating factors: -1 in the case of the target obscuring his eyes slightly (such as closing her eyes or wearing dark sunglasses) up to a -3 for the eyes being completely unseen (such as with a thick blindfold or having her eyes torn out). Ultimately, however, it is up to the Storyteller to decide whether eye contact is established in a particular case.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4wvty5nf9hd","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Dominate","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670227736590,"modifiedTime":1674221161097,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"EH3ILP0On7jEfmyE","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Heart of Stone","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 238","description":"<p>A vampire under the effect of this ritual experiences the transformation suggested by the ritual&rsquo;s name: his heart is completely transmuted to solid rock, rendering him virtually impervious to staking. The subsidiary effects of the transformation, however, seem to follow the Hermetic laws of sympathetic magic: The vampire&rsquo;s emotional capacity becomes almost nonexistent, and his ability to relate to others suffers as well.</p>","details":"<p>This ritual requires nine hours (reduced by one hour for every success). It can only be cast on oneself. The caster lies naked on a flat stone surface and places a bare candle over his heart. The candle burns down to nothing over the course of the ritual, causing one aggravated health level of damage (difficulty 5 to soak with Fortitude).&nbsp;<br><br>At the end of the ritual, the caster&rsquo;s heart hardens to stone. The caster gains a number of additional dice equal to twice his Thaumaturgy rating to soak any attack that aims for his heart and is completely impervious to the effects of a Shaft of Belated Quiescence (see p. 237). Additionally, the difficulty to use all Presence or other emotionally manipulative powers on him is increased by three due to his emotional isolation. The drawbacks are as follows: the caster&rsquo;s Conscience/Conviction and Empathy scores drop to 1 (or to 0 if they already were at 1) and all dice pools for Social rolls except those involving Intimidation are halved (including those required to use Disciplines). All Merits that the character has pertaining to positive social interaction are neutralized. Heart of Stone lasts as long as the caster wishes it to.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"7","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SOFUQHVyXwWb4xVU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_bj41evktjdm","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 4 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671081485306,"modifiedTime":1674439754304,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"EIPO6PsJ9J9cgNX5","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Call of the Sea (2pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 122","description":"<p>There is something about the sea that makes you feel at home. You are in tune with the tides and rhythm of the ocean. When on a boat in the ocean or on a river, you may add a die to all your dice pools except for Disciplines.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.BonXhY7P5YxFV8YT"},"cf":{"id":"temp_gevrsr5xe9","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Lasombra","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221086295,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"ESjoRjvMKfhjqc2l","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Masquerade Breaker (2pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 491","description":"<p>In your first nights as a vampire, you accidentally broke the Masquerade &mdash; and were spotted doing so. Someone else covered for your mistake, but holds the favor over you. Now you exist in fear that your error will be revealed. In the meantime, your &ldquo;savior&rdquo; takes pitiless advantage of you. This Flaw can only be taken by vampires in Sects or Clans that respect the Masquerade.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2wewy46vpbx","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/2 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221105659,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"EUQD3WUQlq1bAI0V","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Hard of Healing (1pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 480","description":"<p>Your hearing is defective. The difficulties of any rolls involving the use of hearing are increased by two</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_jwd9ok2vgth","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672365603221,"modifiedTime":1674221101635,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"EVEU0ylirU5Jj6Vq","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Ward versus Spirits","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 240","description":"<p>This warding ritual functions exactly as Ward versus Ghouls, but it inflicts injury upon spirits. Several other versions of this ward exist, each geared toward a particular type of non-physical being.<br><br><br>From Ward vs. Ghouls:<br>[Wary Tremere created this ritual to protect themselves from the minions of vengeful rivals. By invoking this ritual, the caster creates a glyph that causes great pain to any ghouls who come in contact with it. The Kindred pours a point&rsquo;s worth of blood over the object he wishes to ward (a piece of parchment, a coin, a doorknob, etc.), and recites the incantation, which takes 10 minutes. In 10 hours, the magical ward is complete, and will inflict excruciating pain on any ghoul unfortunate enough to touch the warded object.]</p>","details":"<p>Ward versus Spirits behaves exactly as does Ward versus Ghouls, but it affects spirits (including those summoned or given physical form by Thaumaturgy Paths such as Elemental Mastery). The material component for Ward versus Spirits is a handful of pure sea salt.<br><br>The other versions of this ward, also Level Five rituals, are Ward versus Ghosts and Ward versus Demons. Each of these three Level Five wards affects its respective target on both the physical and spiritual planes. Ward versus Ghosts requires a handful of powdered marble from a tombstone, while Ward versus Demons requires a vial of holy water.<br><br><br>From Ward vs. Ghouls:<br>[Ghouls who touch warded objects suffer three dice of lethal damage. This damage occurs again if the ghoul touches the object further; indeed, a ghoul who consciously wishes to touch a warded object must spend a point of Willpower to do so.<br><br>This ritual wards only one object &mdash; if inscribed on the side of a car, the ward affects only that door or fender, not the whole car. Wards may be placed on weapons, even bullets, though this usually works best on small-caliber weapons. Bullets often warp upon firing, however, and for a ward to remain intact on a fired round, the player needs five successes on the Firearms roll.]</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"8","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SOFUQHVyXwWb4xVU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4r55auipjzn","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 5 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671081485306,"modifiedTime":1674440282341,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"EVXlgHidJ9tc1QuS","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Light-Sensitive (5pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 495","description":"<p>You are even more sensitive to sunlight than other vampires are. Sunlight causes double normal damage, and the light of the moon can cause lethal damage in a manner similar to the sun, though it must shine directly upon you. Even bright lights hurt your eyes, requiring the use of sunglasses. Followers of Set and related bloodlines cannot take this Flaw, as they already have a worse version of it.</p>","details":"<p>Supernatural</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_kwv40m9392i","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/5 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221112013,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"Ec0GcYdwg7VlXk0L","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Precocious (3pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 485","description":"<p>You learn quickly. The time for you to pick up a particular Ability (or Abilities, at Storyteller discretion) is cut in half, as is the experience cost.</p>","details":"<p>Mental</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ry5dLpQH14whw2cH"},"cf":{"id":"temp_tbkdk4lk1q","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672390956649,"modifiedTime":1674440158093,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"EqNIj6Pw49CbTzuY","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●●  The Heart of Darkness","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 210","description":"<p>A Kindred with mastery of Serpentis may pull her heart from her body. She can even use this ability on other Cainites, although this requires several hours of gruesome surgery. This power can only be invoked during a new moon. If performed under any other moon, the rite fails. Upon removing her heart, the vampire places it in a small clay urn, and then carefully hides or buries the urn. While her heart is hidden, she cannot be staked by any wood that pierces her breast. Moreover, because the heart is the seat of emotion, the difficulties of all her rolls to resist frenzy are two lower while this power is in effect.<br><br>Cainites are careful to keep their hearts safe from danger. If someone seizes her heart, the vampire is completely at that person&rsquo;s mercy. The heart can be destroyed only by casting it into a fire or exposing it to sunlight. If this happens, the Kindred dies where she stands, boiling away into a blistering heap of ash and blackened bone. Plunging a wooden stake into an exposed heart drives the vampire into instant torpor.<br><br>A vampire may carry her heart with her, or have several false hearts buried in different places. A smart Kindred often avoids her heart&rsquo;s hiding place, to deter discovery. Those wise in Setite lore whisper that the corrupt elders of the Clan often hold their underlings&rsquo; hearts as yet another method of control.</p>","details":"<p>This power requires no roll. Those who witness a vampire pull his heart from his breast (or cut the heart from another vampire) must make Courage rolls. Failure indicates anything from strong uneasiness to complete revulsion, possibly even R&ouml;tschreck.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pqy5koxd4a","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Serpentis","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670333270322,"modifiedTime":1674439709149,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"EwxJLCMcEvxY6ZZ3","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
