{"name":"Mentor","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 115","description":"<p>This Trait represents a Kindred or group of Kindred who looks out for you, offering guidance or aid once in a while. A mentor may be powerful, but his power need not be direct. Depending on the number of dots in this Background, your mentor might be nothing more than a vampire with a remarkable information network, or might be a centuries-old creature with tremendous influence and supernatural power. He may offer advice, speak to the Prince or Archbishop on your behalf, steer other elders clear of you, or warn you when you&rsquo;re walking into situations you don&rsquo;t understand.&nbsp;<br><br>Most often your mentor is your sire, but it could well be any Cainite with an interest in your wellbeing. A high Mentor rating could even represent a group of like-minded vampires, such as the elders of the city&rsquo;s Tremere chantry or a Black Hand cell.<br><br>Bear in mind that this Trait isn&rsquo;t a &ldquo;Get out of Jail Free&rdquo; card. Your mentor won&rsquo;t necessarily arrive like the cavalry whenever you&rsquo;re endangered (and if she does, you&rsquo;re likely to lose a dot or more in this Background after rousing her ire). What&rsquo;s more, she might occasionally expect something in return for her patronage, which can lead to a number of interesting stories. A mentor typically remains aloof, giving you useful information or advice out of camaraderie, but will abandon you without a thought if you prove an unworthy or troublesome prot&eacute;g&eacute;.&nbsp;</p>","details":"<table style=\"width: 100%;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 16.782%;\"><col style=\"width: 83.218%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>●</td>\n<td>Mentor is an ancilla of little&nbsp;influence, or a Ductus or Pack Priest.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>●●</td>\n<td>Mentor is respected: an elder or&nbsp;highly-decorated veteran,&nbsp;for instance.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>●●●</td>\n<td>Mentor is heavily influential, such as&nbsp;a member of the Primogen or&nbsp;a Bishop.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>●●●●</td>\n<td>Mentor has a great deal of power over&nbsp;the city: a Prince or Archbishop,&nbsp;for example.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>●●●●●</td>\n<td>Mentor is extraordinarily powerful,&nbsp;perhaps even a Justicar or Cardinal.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"wod.types.background","level":"","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_14tdb2ntd4k","path":"Backgrounds","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1673844458648,"modifiedTime":1674221071941,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"F6c01oRJlV6vTbC9","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Aura of Command (3pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 122","description":"<p>Whether you are good at barking orders or simply have a commanding tone, people tend to do what you tell them to do. You are not so much a natural leader as a born commander. When using the Leadership skill to get others to obey you, the difficulty is reduced by two.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.BonXhY7P5YxFV8YT"},"cf":{"id":"temp_gevrsr5xe9","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Lasombra","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221086102,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"F6urX1RfyQvrnHuX","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Paper Trail (2pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 142","description":"<p>You&rsquo;ve spent some time in state institutions like prisons or asylums, likely before your Embrace. Most people have some sort of information that relays date of birth and other bits of fact. This information is hard to eliminate, and may endanger the Masquerade. Enemies with the right influence may be able to track down the information and use it against you. It may lead to vulnerable targets or clue hunters to where your haven is located.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1bn0ry0013fi","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Malkavians","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221088253,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"FKqLbQ8kxdSwfS2e","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Lord of the Flies (2pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 495","description":"<p>Buzzing harbingers of decay swirl around you everywhere. Their constant presence makes it difficult for you to interact socially (+1 difficulty when appropriate) and nearly impossible to sneak up on someone or hide effectively. The buzzing of the flies inevitably gives you away &mdash; all Stealth rolls are at +2 difficulty.</p>","details":"<p>Supernatural</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2wewy46vpbx","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/2 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221105438,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"FSfpMjZ4k7istldl","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●●  Total Insanity","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 149","description":"<p>The vampire coaxes the madness from the deepest recesses of her target&rsquo;s mind, focusing it into an overwhelming wave of insanity. This power has driven countless victims, vampire and mortal alike, to unfortunate ends.</p>","details":"<p>The Kindred must gain her target&rsquo;s undivided attention for at least one full turn to enact this power. The player spends a blood point and rolls Manipulation + Intimidation (difficulty of her victim&rsquo;s current Willpower points). If the roll is successful, the victim is afflicted with five derangements of the Storyteller&rsquo;s choice (see p. 290). The number of successes determines the duration.<br><br></p>\n<table border=\"1\"><colgroup><col><col></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Successes</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1 Success</td>\n<td>One turn</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2 Successes</td>\n<td>One night</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3 Successes</td>\n<td>One week</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4 Successes</td>\n<td>One month</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5 Successes</td>\n<td>One year</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>On a botch... well, the Storyteller can decide what a vampire inflicts upon herself by attempting to incite the primal hells lurking within the darkest recesses of a victim&rsquo;s mind.<br><br>The victim (or the target of a botch) can spend a number of Willpower points equal to the successes rolled to end the duration prematurely. The Storyteller decides when such Willpower points can be spent (such as after a therapy session or after a friend has managed to prove a particular delusion to be false).</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"manipulation","dice2":"intimidation","bonus":0,"difficulty":"-1","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_us1ho2ufuwm","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Dementation","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670227211287,"modifiedTime":1674221160450,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"FXDvmhGlXVgA0zj0","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Peek Past the Shroud","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 182","description":"<p>This hour-long ritual enchants a handful of ergot fungi mold to act as a catalyst for second sight. By eating a pinch of the mold, a subject gains the benefits of Shroudsight (p. 163 ) for a number of hours equal to the necromancer&rsquo;s Stamina score. Three doses of the enchanted ergot are created for every success on the roll. Ergot is normally poisonous to some degree; this ritual removes its toxic properties. However, a botch renders the ergot highly and instantaneously toxic, inflicting eight dice of lethal damage on any subject who ingests it &mdash; including vampires.</p>","details":"<p>Casting times for necromantic rituals vary widely; see the description for particulars. The player rolls Intelligence + Occult (difficulty 3 + the level of the ritual, maximum 9). Success indicates the ritual proceeds smoothly, failure produces no effect, and a botch indicates something has gone horribly wrong.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"7","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2r4138smwse","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 4 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670899739755,"modifiedTime":1674221175838,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"FgC3immU7P1bVPKg","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
