{"name":"●●●● Ex Nihilo","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 163","description":"<p>Ex Nihilo allows a necromancer to enter the Underworld physically. While in the lands of the dead, the vampire is essentially a particularly solid ghost. He maintains his normal number of health levels, but can be hurt only by things that inflict aggravated damage on ghosts (weapons forged from souls, certain ghostly powers, etc.). A vampire physically in the Underworld can pass through solid objects in the real world (at the cost of one health level) and remain &ldquo;incorporeal&rdquo; for a number of turns equal to her Stamina rating. On the other hand, vampires present in the Underworld are subject to all of the Underworld&rsquo;s perils, including ultimate destruction. A vampire killed in the realm of the dead is gone forever, beyond even the reach of other necromancers.</p>","details":"<p>Using Ex Nihilo takes a tremendous toll on the necromancer. To activate this power, the vampire must first draw a doorway with chalk or blood on any available surface. (The vampire may draw doors ahead of time for exactly this purpose.) The player must then expend two points of Willpower and two points of blood before making a Stamina + Occult roll (difficulty 8) as the vampire attempts to open the chalk door physically. If the roll succeeds, the door opens and the vampire steps through into the Underworld.<br><br>When the vampire wishes to return to the real world, he merely needs to concentrate (and the player spends another Willpower point and rolls Stamina + Occult, difficulty 6). At Storyteller discretion, a vampire who is too deeply immersed in the Underworld may need to journey to a place close to the lands of the living in order to cross over. Vampires who wander too far into the lands of the dead may be trapped there forever.<br><br>Vampires in the Underworld cannot feed upon ghosts without the use of another power; their only sustenance is the blood they bring with them.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"stamina","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"8","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.mEaM9Y6XAzPaTpox"},"cf":{"id":"temp_kq4unp858o","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Ash Path","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670842147642,"modifiedTime":1674221165011,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"HBQ83wsltWXuZyjn","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Lame (3pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 482","description":"<p>Your legs are damaged, which prevents you from running or walking easily. You are forced to walk with a cane or possibly leg braces, and you have a pronounced limp to your stride. Your walking speed is one-quarter that of a normal human, and running is impossible.</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_81150czgfr","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672365603221,"modifiedTime":1674221108231,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"HEqBK0rvl9hDztCA","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●● The Forgetful Mind","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 154","description":"<p>After capturing the subject&rsquo;s gaze, the vampire delves into the subject&rsquo;s memories, stealing or re-creating them at his whim. The Forgetful Mind does not allow for telepathic contact; the Kindred operates much like a hypnotist, asking directed questions and drawing out answers from the subject. The degree of memory alteration depends on what the vampire desires. He may alter the subject&rsquo;s mind only slightly (quite effective for eliminating memories of the victim meeting or even being fed upon by the vampire) or utterly undo the victim&rsquo;s memories of her past.<br><br>The degree of detail used has a direct bearing on how strongly the new memories take hold, since the victim&rsquo;s subconscious mind resists the alteration. A simplistic or incomplete false memory (&ldquo;You went to the movies last night&rdquo;) crumbles much more quickly than does one with more attention to detail (&ldquo;You thought about texting your girlfriend while you were in line at the new movie theater, but you knew you&rsquo;d have to turn your phone off once you got inside. You liked the movie well enough, but the plot seemed weak. You were tired after it ended, so you went home, watched a little late-night television, and went to bed.&rdquo;).<br><br>Even in its simplest applications, The Forgetful Mind requires tremendous skill and finesse. It&rsquo;s a relatively simple matter to rifle through a victim&rsquo;s psyche and rip out the memories of the previous night without knowing what the subject did that evening. Doing so leaves a gap in the victim&rsquo;s mind, however &mdash; a hole that can give rise to further problems down the road. The Kindred may describe new memories, but these recollections seldom have the same degree of realism that the subject&rsquo;s original thoughts held.<br><br>As such, this power isn&rsquo;t always completely effective. The victim may remember being bitten, but believe it to be an animal attack. Greater memories may return in pieces as dreams, or through sensory triggers like a familiar odor or spoken phrase. Even so, months or years may pass before the subject regains enough of her lost memories to make sense of the fragments.<br><br>A vampire can also sense when a subject&rsquo;s memories were altered through use of this power, and even restore them, as a hypnotist draws forth suppressed thoughts.</p>","details":"<p>The player states what sorts of alteration he wants to perform, then rolls Wits + Subterfuge (difficulty equal to the target&rsquo;s current Willpower points). Any success pacifies the victim for the amount of time it takes the vampire to perform the verbal alteration, provided the vampire does not act aggressively toward her. The table below indicates the degree of modification possible to the subject&rsquo;s memory. If the successes rolled don&rsquo;t allow for the extent of change the character desired, the Storyteller reduces the resulting impact on the victim&rsquo;s mind.<br><br></p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 136px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 20.3509%;\"><col style=\"width: 79.4737%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\"><strong>Successes</strong></td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">1 Success</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">May remove a single memory; lasts one day.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">2 Successes</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">May remove, but not alter, memory permanently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">3 Successes</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">May make slight changes to memory.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px;\">4 Successes</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px;\">May alter or remove entire scene from subject&rsquo;s memory. 5 successes&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 34px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 34px;\">5 Successes</td>\n<td style=\"height: 34px;\">May reconstruct entire periods of subject&rsquo;s life.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>To restore removed memories or sense false ones in a subject, the character&rsquo;s Dominate rating must be equal to or higher than that of the vampire who made the alteration. In that situation, the player must make a Wits + Empathy roll (difficulty equal to the original vampire&rsquo;s permanent Willpower rating) and score more successes than his predecessor did. However, the Kindred cannot use The Forgetful Mind to restore his own memories if they were stolen in such a way.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"wits","dice2":"subterfuge","bonus":0,"difficulty":"-1","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4wvty5nf9hd","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Dominate","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670227736590,"modifiedTime":1674221161499,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"HF7DmjB2xyknE5yC","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●● Fata Morgana","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 144","description":"<p>The Cainite can now create illusions that appeal to all the senses, though they remain static. For example, the vampire could make a filthy cellar appear as an opulent ballroom, though she could not create a glittering chandelier or a score of graceful dancers. Again, the illusion has no solid presence, though it&rsquo;s easy enough to fool an enraptured visitor with suggestions of what she might expect. A bucket of brackish water is as cool as chilled champagne, after all.</p>","details":"<p>The player spends a Willpower point and a blood point to create the illusion. These static images remain until dispelled, in much the same way that an Ignis Fatuus illusion does.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_jgyzexzzmb","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Chimerstry","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670226749831,"modifiedTime":1674221159135,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"HPJsEwlquaVxm3yq","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●●  Mist Form","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 200","description":"<p>This truly unsettling power enables the vampire to turn into mist. His physical shape disperses into a hazy cloud, but one still subject entirely to the immortal&rsquo;s will. He floats at a brisk pace and may slip under doors, through screens, down pipes, and through other tiny openings. Although strong winds can blow the vampire from his chosen course, even hurricane-force winds cannot disperse his mist shape.<br><br>Some Kindred feel that this power is an expression of the vampire&rsquo;s ultimate control over the material world, while others believe that it is the immortal&rsquo;s soul made manifest (damned though it may be).</p>","details":"<p>No roll is required, although a blood point must be spent. The transformation takes three turns to complete, although the character may reduce this time by one turn for each additional blood point spent (to a minimum of one turn). Strong winds may buffet the character, although Disciplines such as Potence may be used to resist them. Vampires in Mist Form can perceive their surroundings normally, although they cannot use powers that require eye contact.<br><br>The vampire is immune to all mundane physical attacks while in mist form, although supernatural attacks affect him normally. Also, the vampire takes one fewer die of damage from fire and sunlight. The character may not attack others physically while in this state &mdash; this includes encountering another vampire in mist form. He may use Disciplines that do not require physical substance, however.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_b0ldn2fjavv","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Protean","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670331720769,"modifiedTime":1674221181273,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"HQYiuyvs77EcnxRy","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
