{"name":"●●●● Fearless Heart","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 224","description":"<p>The vampire temporarily augments his abilities as a warrior. Through the mystical powers of blood magic, the character becomes a potent fighting force.</p>","details":"<p>Fearless Heart grants the vampire an extra point in each of the Physical Attributes (Strength, Dexterity, and Stamina). These Traits may not exceed their generational maximums, though the player may use blood points to push the character&rsquo;s Traits even higher. The effects last for one scene, and a character may gain its benefits only once per scene. The vampire must spend two hours in a calm and restful state following the use of Fearless Heart, or lose a blood point every 15 minutes until he rests.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"7","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.xs9y10bdAQRkgcNU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4yk16ojy6jl","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Mars","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439745862,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"HhpDxPPGLKBhD33h","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●● Feral Claws","type":"Melee Weapon","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/naturalweapons.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 199 // V20 276","description":"Claw: This attack is available to vampires with claws, such as those from the Protean power of Feral Claws or bone spurs constructed with the Vicissitude power of Bonecraft. A few other supernatural creatures, such as werewolves, also have claws. A claw attack inflicts aggravated damage (if Feral Claws) or lethal damage (if a Vicissitude-constructed weapon).\n\nTraits: Dexterity + Brawl\nDifficulty: Normal\nAccuracy:\nNormal Damage: Strength +1\n","details":"","isequipped":false,"ismagical":false,"isweapon":false,"attack":{"attribute":"dexterity","ability":"brawl","secondaryabilityid":"","accuracy":0,"isrollable":true},"damage":{"attribute":"strength","bonus":1,"type":"aggravated","isrollable":true},"difficulty":"6","conceal":"NA","istwohanded":false,"isnatural":true,"type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2f06ozkysk3","path":"Items#/CF_SEP/Natural Weapons","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674290507431,"modifiedTime":1674440439260,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"HjFTJQnppVDm3fnD","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Parasitic Infestation (2pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 162","description":"<p>Living in the dark has made you a home to all manner of creepy crawlies and bloodsuckers. Your skin is crawling with ticks, lice, and leeches of all descriptions. They constantly bite and burrow, and having fed on your vitae, they have become very hard to kill. Not only can you not command them, you have tried everything to get rid of them and still they persist. Whatever the reason, they find you so succulent they reduce your blood pool by the result of one die divided by 3 (round down) each time you rise. The constant itch also keeps you on edge, increasing the difficulty of any Self-Control or Instinct rolls by 1.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vHJSI1w1uvu5im25"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ak5eyy1egoa","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Nosferatu#/CF_SEP/Flaw","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221089936,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"HmerFIkcGFNGuJVX","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Rat in a Cage (2pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 87","description":"<p>Anytime you are penned in or physically restrained (such as by a cage, or with handcuffs), you suffer acute anxiety. The difficulties of any rolls made under such circumstances are increased by two.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.UlU0IIyvjGePBEoG"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1nj44zxegwk","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Gangrel","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221084379,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"HxRnmtL1HSfPVvpD","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●● Scorpion's Touch","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 203","description":"<p>By changing the properties of her blood, a vampire may create powerful venom that strips her prey of his resilience. This power is greatly feared by other Kindred, and all manner of hideous tales concerning methods of delivery circulate among trembling coteries. Kindred with Quietus are known to deliver the poison by coating their weapons with it, blighting their opponents with a touch, or spitting it like a cobra. An apocryphal account speaks of a proud Prince who discovered an Assamite plotting her exsanguination and began to diablerize her would-be assassin. Halfway through the act, she learned that she had ingested a dire quantity of tainted blood and was then unable to resist the weakened hashashiyyin&rsquo;s renewed attack.</p>","details":"<p>To convert a bit of her blood to poison, the Kindred&rsquo;s player spends at least one blood point and rolls Willpower (difficulty 6). If this roll is successful, and the vampire successfully hits (but not necessarily damages) her opponent, the target loses a number of Stamina points equal to the number of blood points converted into poison &mdash; vampires attempting to drink the blood of the Kindred with Scorpion&rsquo;s Touch are automatically considered to be &ldquo;successfully hit.&rdquo;<br><br>The victim may resist the poison with a Stamina + Fortitude roll (difficulty 6); successes achieved on the resistance roll subtract from the vampire&rsquo;s successes. The maximum number of blood points a Kindred may convert at any one time is equal to her Stamina. The number of successes scored indicates the duration of the Stamina loss.<br><br></p>\n<table border=\"1\"><colgroup><col><col></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong> Successes</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1 Successes</td>\n<td>One Turn</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2 Successes</td>\n<td>One Hour</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3 Successes</td>\n<td>One Day</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4 Successes</td>\n<td>One Month</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5 Successes</td>\n<td>Permanently (though Stamina may be bought back up with experience)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>If a mortal&rsquo;s Stamina falls to zero through use of Scorpion&rsquo;s Touch, she becomes terminally ill and loses any immunity to diseases, her body succumbing to sickness within the year unless she somehow manages to increase her Stamina again. If a Kindred&rsquo;s Stamina falls to zero, the vampire enters torpor and remains that way until one of her Stamina points returns. If a Kindred is permanently reduced to zero Stamina, she may recover from torpor only through mystical means.<br><br></p>\n<p>To afflict someone with the poison, the Cainite must touch her target&rsquo;s flesh or hit him with something that carries the venom. Many Assamites lubricate their weapons with the excretion, while others pool the toxin in their hands (or fleck their lips with the poison, for a &ldquo;kiss of death&rdquo;) and press it to their opponents. Weapons so envenomed must be of the melee variety &mdash; arrows, sling stones, bullets, thrown weapons, and the like cannot carry enough of the stuff to do damage, or it drips off in flight. Players whose vampires wish to spit at their targets must make a Stamina + Athletics roll (difficulty 6). No more than two blood points&rsquo; worth of poison may be expectorated, and a Kindred may spit a distance of 10 feet (3 meters) for each point of Strength (and Potence) the character possesses. Vampires with Quietus are immune to their own poison, but not the blood-venom of other Kindred with this power.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"6","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_g4q0cu2l6d","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Quietus","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670332666414,"modifiedTime":1674221181979,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"I4qyZZcxSL0xxlkB","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Nine Lives (6 pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 494","description":"<p>Fate has granted you the opportunity to come as close to Final Death as anyone can get and still survive. When a roll occurs that would result in your death, the roll is made again. If the next roll succeeds, then you live &mdash; and one of your nine lives is used up. If that subsequent roll fails, then another reroll is made, until either a successful roll occurs or your nine lives are used up. The Storyteller should keep careful count of how many lives the character has remaining.</p>","details":"<p>Supernatural</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"6","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_qb81qn0u0ti","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/6 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674439997811,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"IEXhUL0BXx98IAwr","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Two Centimes","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 180","description":"<p>The necromancer ceremonially &ldquo;kills&rdquo; a mortal, laying him out on a pallet and putting pennies on his eyes. The mortal&rsquo;s soul journeys to the Underworld, which he perceives, initially at least, as a way-station. The mortal can interact with the souls of the dead and travel elsewhere in the Underworld, while also retaining the power to speak to the vampire and describe what he&rsquo;s experiencing. While in the Underworld, however, the subject&rsquo;s soul cannot affect the environment. Although he may talk to other spirits, he may not physically interact with them or their surroundings &mdash; he is a &ldquo;ghost among ghosts,&rdquo; as it were. Minions may voluntarily undergo the ritual to assist necromancers, or the vampire may use Two Centimes to terrify unwilling victims.</p>","details":"<p>Casting times for necromantic rituals vary widely; see the description for particulars. The player rolls Intelligence + Occult (difficulty 3 + the level of the ritual, maximum 9). Success indicates the ritual proceeds smoothly, failure produces no effect, and a botch indicates something has gone horribly wrong.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"5","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_b17ggxg6joc","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 2 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670899739755,"modifiedTime":1674221173963,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"IEg5cAZazWtDLcOJ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Claws","type":"Melee Weapon","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/naturalweapons.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 276","description":"Claw: This attack is available to vampires with claws, such as those from the Protean power of Feral Claws or bone spurs constructed with the Vicissitude power of Bonecraft. A few other supernatural creatures, such as werewolves, also have claws. A claw attack inflicts aggravated damage (if Feral Claws) or lethal damage (if a Vicissitude-constructed weapon).\n\nTraits: Dexterity + Brawl\nDifficulty: Normal\nAccuracy:\nNormal Damage: Strength +1\n","details":"","isequipped":false,"ismagical":false,"isweapon":false,"attack":{"attribute":"dexterity","ability":"brawl","secondaryabilityid":"","accuracy":0,"isrollable":true},"damage":{"attribute":"strength","bonus":1,"type":"lethal","isrollable":true},"difficulty":"6","conceal":"NA","istwohanded":false,"isnatural":true},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2f06ozkysk3","path":"Items#/CF_SEP/Natural Weapons","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674290507431,"modifiedTime":1674440439556,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"IGUWlezscNTtfXgM","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Quietus","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/mainpower_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 203","description":"<p>The Discipline of silent death, Quietus is practiced by those of Clan Assamite. Based on elements of blood, poison, vitae control, and pestilence, Quietus focuses on the destruction of a target through a variety of means. This Discipline doesn&rsquo;t always cause a quick death, but the Assamites rely on its lethality to hide their involvement with their victims.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.discipline","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_g4q0cu2l6d","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Quietus","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670332638945,"modifiedTime":1674221182369,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"IMZTrK0LLsjzA9k6","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Warding Circle vs. Lupines","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 234","description":"<p>This ritual is enacted in a manner similar to that of Ward versus Ghouls, but creates a circle centered on the caster into which a [werewolf] cannot pass without being burned. The circle can be made as large and as permanent as the caster desires, as long as she is willing to pay the necessary price. Many Tremere chantries and havens are protected by this and other Warding Circle rituals.</p>","details":"<p>The ritual requires [\"larger amount\" of a handful of silver dust]. The caster determines the size of the warding circle when it is cast; the default radius is 10 feet/3 meters, and every 10-foot/3-meter increase raises the difficulty by one, to a maximum of 9 (one additional success is required for every increase past the number necessary to raise the difficulty to 9). The player spends one blood point for every 10 feet/3 meters of radius and rolls. The ritual takes the normal casting time if it is to be short-term (lasting for the rest of the night) or one night if it is to be long-term (lasting a year and a day).<br><br>Once the warding circle is established, any [werewolf] who attempts to cross its boundary feels a tingle on his skin and a slight breeze on his face &mdash; a successful Intelligence + Occult roll (difficulty 8) identifies this as a warding circle. If the [werewolf] attempts to press on, he must roll more successes on a Willpower roll (difficulty of the caster&rsquo;s Thaumaturgy rating + 3) than the caster rolled when establishing the ward. Failure indicates that the ward blocks his passage and inflicts three dice of bashing damage, and his next roll to attempt to enter the circle is at +1 difficulty. If the [werewolf] leaves the circle and attempts to enter it again, he must repeat the roll. Attempts to leave the circle are not blocked.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"6","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SOFUQHVyXwWb4xVU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ux26or4j83","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 3 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671081485306,"modifiedTime":1674439753584,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"ISHjGfxY81eOXXoQ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
