{"name":"Eerie Presence (2pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 495","description":"<p>Mortals have an unconscious awareness of your undead nature, which makes then anxious and ill at ease in your presence. Because of this, difficulties of all rolls relating to social interaction with mortals are increased by two.</p>","details":"<p>Supernatural</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2wewy46vpbx","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/2 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221104901,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"OEN7oJwYXwoY1LAc","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"● Destroy the Husk","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 171","description":"<p>Cainites who kill their victims, rather than just feeding upon them, frequently find themselves in need of a quick way to dispose of a corpse. While there are many ways to make sure that a corpse is not found &mdash; feed it to a pack of hounds or weigh it down and throw it in a river &mdash; many of these methods do involve risk to the vampire and are not guaranteed to succeed. Destroy the Husk, by contrast, is foolproof. Use of this power simply turns one human corpse to a pile of about 30 pounds (13 kilograms) of unremarkable dust, roughly the size and shape of that body.</p>","details":"<p>The player spends one blood point as the vampire drips her vitae onto the corpse. The player then rolls Intelligence + Medicine (difficulty 6). One success is all that is needed to render the corpse into dust, although the process takes a number&nbsp; of turns equal to five minus the successes.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"medicine","bonus":0,"difficulty":"6","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_29xrm8dfvtq","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Grave's Decay","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670842147642,"modifiedTime":1674221168835,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"OK43YIMy3WJt8zRf","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"○ Disarm","type":"Melee Weapon","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/meleeweapons.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 278","description":"Disarm: To strike an opponent’s weapon, the attacker must make an attack roll at +1 difficulty. If successful, the attacker rolls damage normally. If successes\nrolled exceed the opponent’s Strength rating, the opponent takes no damage but is disarmed. A botch usually means the attacker drops her own weapon or is\nstruck by her target’s weapon.\n\nTraits: Dexterity + Melee\nDifficulty: +1\nAccuracy: Normal\nDamage: Special","details":"","isequipped":false,"ismagical":false,"isweapon":false,"attack":{"attribute":"dexterity","ability":"melee","secondaryabilityid":"","accuracy":0,"isrollable":true},"damage":{"attribute":"","bonus":0,"type":"","isrollable":false},"difficulty":"7","conceal":"NA","istwohanded":false,"isnatural":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tyg371ggunf","path":"Items#/CF_SEP/Melee Weapons","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674290963833,"modifiedTime":1674440437810,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"OTOSbgNXSNXhhPEt","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Blood Hunted (4 or 6pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 493","description":"<p>You have been made the target of a blood hunt, and for you to return to your home city is death. For four points, this Flaw means that only your home city is offlimits to you. For six, it means that the entire Camarilla is howling for your vitae. This Flaw can only be taken by Camarilla vampires.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_d9j4thjusi","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/Multi-pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221113707,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"OTvvnMOscp26il0B","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
