{"name":"Class 1 (reinforced clothing)","type":"Armor","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/armor.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 280","description":"Armor adds its rating to the character’s soak dice pool against bashing damage, lethal damage, and aggravated damage from fangs and claws. It does not protect against fire or sunlight. However, armor also subtracts a number of dice from dice pools related to bodily coordination and agility (most Dexterity-based dice pools). This is reflected in the penalty listing. Attackers may make targeting rolls to hit unprotected portions of a defender and thus ignore the armor (Storyteller assigns difficulty penalty — typically +1 or +2).","details":"","isequipped":false,"ismagical":false,"isweapon":false,"soak":{"bashing":1,"lethal":1,"aggravated":1,"chimerical":{"bashing":0,"lethal":0,"aggravated":0}},"dexpenalty":0,"forms":{"hashomid":true,"hasglabro":false,"hascrinos":false,"hashispo":false,"haslupus":false}},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_626ifvdetzi","path":"Items#/CF_SEP/Armor","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674291929378,"modifiedTime":1674440436013,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"Sabo9X9oIYIhTAmv","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Illuminate the Trail of Prey","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 231","description":"<p>This ritual causes the path of the subject&rsquo;s passing to glow in a manner that only the vampire can see. The tracks shine distinctly, but only to the eyes of the caster. Even airplane trajectories and animal tracks shine with unhealthy light. The ritual is nullified if the target wades through or immerses himself in water, or if he reaches the destination of his journey. The caster must burn a length of white satin ribbon that has been in her possession for at least 24 hours for this ritual to take effect.</p>","details":"<p>The thaumaturge must have a mental picture of or know the name of her prey. The individual&rsquo;s wake glows with a level of brightness dependent on how long it has been since he passed that way &mdash; old tracks burn less brightly, while fresh tracks blaze.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"4","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_q5ajxrpsb3","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 1 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671081485306,"modifiedTime":1674439750523,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"SbZs73N7XgHD5Xzf","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"SMG, Large (Spray)","type":"Ranged Weapon","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/rangedweapons.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 281","description":"Strafing: Instead of aiming at one target, fully-automatic weapons can be fired across an area. Strafing adds 10 dice to accuracy on a standard attack roll, and empties the clip. A maximum of three yards/meters can be covered with this maneuver.\n\nThe attacker divides any successes gained on the attack roll evenly among all targets in the covered area (successes assigned to hit an individual are added to that target’s damage dice pool, as well). If only one target is within range or the area of effect, only half the successes affect him. The attacker then assigns any leftover successes as she desires. If fewer successes are rolled than there are targets, only one may be assigned per target until they are all allocated.\n\nDodge rolls against strafing are at +1 difficulty","details":"","isequipped":false,"ismagical":false,"isweapon":false,"attack":{"attribute":"dexterity","ability":"firearms","secondaryabilityid":"","accuracy":10,"isrollable":true},"damage":{"attribute":"","bonus":4,"type":"lethal","isrollable":true},"difficulty":"8","conceal":"T","istwohanded":false,"range":50,"rate":3,"mode":{"hasreload":false,"hasburst":false,"hasfullauto":false,"hasspray":true},"clip":{"value":0,"max":30}},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6yghfiu9569","path":"Items#/CF_SEP/Ranged Weapons","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674287371409,"modifiedTime":1674440442289,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"SsgHd9tQi7q7XFvS","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●● Power over Life","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 221","description":"<p>This power cannot create true life, though it can summon forth impressive simulacra. Creatures (and people) summoned with this power lack the free will to act on their own, mindlessly following the simple instructions of their conjurer instead. People created in this way can be subject to the use of the Dominate power Possession (p. 155), if desired.</p>","details":"<p>The player spends 10 blood points. Imperfect and impermanent, creatures summoned via this path are too complex to exist for long. Within a week after their conjuration, the simulacra vanish into insubstantiality.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"8","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2d9fqjslrzb","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Conjuring","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439743869,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"T0SpTLOPUdr0Y356","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"SMG, Small (3-Round Burst)","type":"Ranged Weapon","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/rangedweapons.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 281","description":"Three-Round Burst: The attacker gains two additional dice on a single attack roll, and expends three shots from the weapon’s clip. Only certain weapons may perform this maneuver; see the Ranged Weapons Chart for particulars. Attacks are made at +1 difficulty due to recoil. As with automatic fire, the damage dice pool is based on one bullet from the weapon in question.","details":"","isequipped":false,"ismagical":false,"isweapon":false,"attack":{"attribute":"dexterity","ability":"firearms","secondaryabilityid":"","accuracy":2,"isrollable":true},"damage":{"attribute":"","bonus":4,"type":"lethal","isrollable":true},"difficulty":"7","conceal":"J","istwohanded":false,"range":20,"rate":3,"mode":{"hasreload":false,"hasburst":true,"hasfullauto":false,"hasspray":false},"clip":{"value":0,"max":17}},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6yghfiu9569","path":"Items#/CF_SEP/Ranged Weapons","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674287371409,"modifiedTime":1674440442491,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"T0kYEE7XTfQMCKYf","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●● Blood to Water","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 219","description":"<p>The thaumaturge has now attained enough power over water that she can transmute other liquids to this basic element. The most commonly seen use of this power is as an assault; with but a touch, the victim&rsquo;s blood transforms to water, weakening vampires and killing mortals in moments.</p>","details":"<p>The character must touch her intended victim. The player rolls Willpower normally. Each success converts one of the victim&rsquo;s blood points to water. One success kills a mortal within minutes. Vampires who lose blood points to this power also suffer dice pool penalties as if they had received an equivalent number of health levels of injury. The water left in the target&rsquo;s system by this attack evaporates out at a rate of one blood point&rsquo;s worth per hour, but the lost blood does not return.<br><br>At the Storyteller&rsquo;s discretion, other liquids may be turned to water with this power (the difficulty for such an action is reduced by one unless the substance is particularly dangerous or magical in nature). The character must still touch the substance or its container to use this power.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"6","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.RFll2tsRz778pPrL"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8yl7px52c34","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/Neptune's Might","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439739349,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"T1z3xpkHf3mcZNLr","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Thin Blood (4pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 483","description":"<p>Your blood is thin, weak, and does not sustain you well. All blood point costs are doubled (e.g., using blood-related Disciplines or healing damage), although you only lose one blood upon rising in the evening. Furthermore, you are unable to create a blood bond, and efforts to sire other vampires succeed only one in five times.</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ry8o03n5zsc","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/4 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672365603221,"modifiedTime":1674221111110,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"T3ZkMaCrEKlTgxA9","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Tempesta Scudo","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 181","description":"<p>Unlike most rituals, <em>Tempesta Scudo</em> can be cast speedily. The necromancer performs a short and awkward dance that ends with her biting through her own lip and spitting the blood in a circle around her. All ghosts&rsquo; actions within the circle of blood are made at +2 difficulty.<br><br>To cast this ritual successfully, the necromancer must spend one combat turn performing the dance. At the end of the turn, she makes a Dexterity + Performance roll against difficulty 7 (if done outside of combat, the difficulty is only 6). During the next combat turn, she bites through her own lips (taking a level of bashing damage) and spits (spending one blood point). Then the normal ritual roll is made to see whether the power takes effect.</p>","details":"<p>Casting times for necromantic rituals vary widely; see the description for particulars. The player rolls Intelligence + Occult (difficulty 3 + the level of the ritual, maximum 9). Success indicates the ritual proceeds smoothly, failure produces no effect, and a botch indicates something has gone horribly wrong.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"dexterity","dice2":"performance","bonus":0,"difficulty":"-1","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xjookc6i33s","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 3 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670899739755,"modifiedTime":1674221174957,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"TJ9qYDipSJz6k8MO","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Deflection of Wooden Doom","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 231","description":"<p>This ritual protects the caster from being staked, whether she is resting or active. While this ritual is in effect, the first stake that would pierce the vampire&rsquo;s heart disintegrates in the attacker&rsquo;s hand. A stake merely held near the caster is unaffected; for this ritual to work, the stake must actively be used in an attempt to impale the vampire.</p>","details":"<p>System: The caster must surround herself with a circle of wood for a full hour. Any wood will work: furniture, sawdust, raw timber, 2&rsquo; x 4&rsquo;s, whatever. The circle must remain unbroken, however. At the end of the hour, the vampire places a wooden splinter under her tongue. If this splinter is removed, the ritual is nullified. This ritual lasts until the following dawn or dusk.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"4","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_q5ajxrpsb3","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 1 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671081485306,"modifiedTime":1674439750134,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"TNs4yHFsz7VBA7br","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"Feature","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_w0iir3wpc8q","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Technomancy","color":"#000000","name":"The Path of Technomancy","children":[],"folderPath":["temp_444y5utucrj","temp_26bm5shk25q","temp_g6lsl2i5ymg"],"fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":null,"sorting":"a","contents":["S3EYSrq0ugBRCs7q","8Fk2Xkn1KwRQ8mIM","ybBYaSfAzBm9lk3p","IZx6bXbox2Njq1UD","20G6Olc0WGsmZpYU","wUzBnLqcQuAAdTtL"],"version":"2.5.6"}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"iscreated":false,"version":"","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"","description":"","details":"","type":"","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674439747161,"modifiedTime":1674439747498,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"TVPbZjP4nIHESczf"}
{"name":"Deaf (4pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 483","description":"<p>You cannot hear. While you may be more resistant to some applications of Dominate, you also may not listen to electronic or vocal media, and the difficulties of many Perception rolls are increased by three.</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ry8o03n5zsc","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/4 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672365603221,"modifiedTime":1674221110007,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"TpBEkofAu7iEhjSS","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●● Dagon's Call (Sorcerer)","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 27","description":"<p>The sorcerer and vizier equivalents for Dagon&rsquo;s Call both work the same. Instead of ravaging the target&rsquo;s body, the Assamite harrows the mind.&nbsp;<br><br><br><em><strong>Original - Warrior Version:</strong></em><br>This terrible power allows a vampire to drown her target in his own blood. By concentrating, the Kindred bursts her target&rsquo;s blood vessels and fills his lungs with vitae that strangles him from within. The blood actually constricts the target&rsquo;s body from the inside as it floods through his system; thus, it works even on unbreathing Kindred. Until the target collapses in agony or death throes, this power has no visible effect, and many Kindred like it because it leaves no trace of their presence.</p>","details":"<p>Mechanically, this power works the same as the warrior version except as follows: First, the roll is the Assamite&rsquo;s Manipulation versus the target&rsquo;s Intelligence. The difficulty for both rolls is the other&rsquo;s permanent Willpower. Second, instead of inflicting lethal damage, each net success for the Assamite strips the target of temporary Willpower. If the Assamite spends a Willpower point and continues to roll even after the target has lost all her temporary Willpower, additional successes strip the target of one dot of permanent Willpower. This represents the most damage that this power can inflict in a single night regardless of successes, but a target who has lost all of her Willpower dots through use of Dagon&rsquo;s Call on successive nights is reduced to a mindless husk.<br><br>As with the warrior version, the Assamite need not be within the target&rsquo;s presence to trigger this attack.<br><br><br><em><strong>Original - Warrior Version:</strong></em><br>The vampire must touch her target prior to using Dagon&rsquo;s Call. Within an hour thereafter, the vampire may issue the call, though she need not be in the presence or even in the line of sight of her target.<br><br></p>\n<p>Invoking the power costs one Willpower point. The Kindred&rsquo;s player makes a contested Stamina roll against the target&rsquo;s Stamina; the difficulty of each roll is equal to the opponent&rsquo;s permanent Willpower rating. The number of successes the vampire using Dagon&rsquo;s Call achieves is the amount of lethal damage, in health levels, the victim suffers. For an additional point of Willpower spent in the next turn, the vampire may continue using Dagon&rsquo;s Call by engaging in another contested Stamina roll. So long as the Kindred&rsquo;s player continues to spend Willpower, the character may continue rending her opponent from within.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"stamina","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"-1","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u1wajwfwbf","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Quietus#/CF_SEP/Quietus (Sorcerer)","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670332666414,"modifiedTime":1674221183079,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"TqIPmjRHbcbwU46y","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●● Turn to Dust","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 218","description":"<p>This fearsome power accelerates decrepitude in its victims. Mortals literally age at the mere touch of a skilled thaumaturge, gaining decades in moments.</p>","details":"<p>Each success on the roll ages the victim by 10 years. A potential victim may resist with a Stamina + Courage roll (difficulty 8), but must accumulate more successes than the caster&rsquo;s activation roll &mdash; it&rsquo;s an all-or-nothing affair. If the victim succeeds, he does not age at all. If he does not acquire more successes than the thaumaturge, he ages the full amount. Obviously, this power, while it affects vampires, has no detrimental effect on them (they&rsquo;re immortal). At most, a Kindred victim grows paler and withers slightly (-1 to Appearance) for one night.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"8","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.DBIV1w1yzXd9s6NV"},"cf":{"id":"temp_qrx4b8dkuga","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/Hands of Destruction","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439737914,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"TqYpZUMbMikZedoq","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Mirror of Second Sight","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 236","description":"<p>This object is an oval mirror no less than four inches (10 cm) wide and no more than 18 inches (45 cm) in length. It looks like a normal mirror, but once created, the vampire can use it to see the supernatural: It reflects the true form of Lupines and faeries, and enables the owner to see ghosts as they move though the Underworld. The caster creates the mirror by bathing an ordinary mirror in a quantity of her own blood while reciting a ritual incantation.</p>","details":"<p>The ritual requires one point of the vampire&rsquo;s blood. Thereafter, the mirror reflects images of other supernatural creatures&rsquo; true forms &mdash; werewolves appear in their hulking man-wolf shapes, magi glow in a scintillating nimbus, ghosts become visible (in the mirror), and so on. Sometimes, the mirror also reveals those possessed of True Faith in clouds of golden light.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"6","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SOFUQHVyXwWb4xVU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ux26or4j83","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 3 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671081485306,"modifiedTime":1674439753089,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"TrIkl5TnyQscwEYW","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Legerdemain (1pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 182","description":"<p>You&rsquo;re extremely good at sleight of hand and other physical tricks. Difficulties when using Subterfuge for physical trickery, shell games, card tricks, and so forth, are decreased by two.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.iGFbYRukWee1s96g"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ah1xgfy02pt","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Ravnos","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221093087,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"U2IWuG6lVYlpfSwd","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Old Pal (2pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 488","description":"<p>An acquaintance from your breathing days was Embraced at the same time you were. Fortunately, your friendship has endured even death and unlife, and you find a constant source of support and aid in your old friend. She expects the same of you, which isn&rsquo;t always convenient, but at least you each have someone to hang onto who remembers the good old nights &mdash; and days. The Storyteller should play the Old Pal as a very loyal Ally.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_644ptrzk5eq","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/2 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674439885175,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"U3YRBam8nGMkESYE","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
