{"name":"●●●● Corrupt the Undead Flesh","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 172","description":"<p>Corrupt the Undead Flesh blurs the line between life and undeath, turning an undead creature into something just living enough to carry and suffer from disease. The disease inflicts the target, causing lethargy, dizziness, loss of strength, clumsiness, and the inability to keep blood in his system. This pernicious influence is extremely virulent among mortals. They pick the disease up simply by spending a few hours near the victim. Other vampires have a harder time acquiring the disease. They must consume the victim&rsquo;s blood to do so, but afterward, they suffer just as much as the original target &mdash; including passing the affliction on to others.<br><br>The disease fades after roughly a week.</p>","details":"<p>The player chooses a target within her character&rsquo;s line of sight and no more than 20 yards or meters away. She rolls Intelligence + Medicine (difficulty 6) and spends a point of Willpower. The victim&rsquo;s player must roll Stamina (+ Fortitude, if appropriate) against a difficulty equal to the attacker&rsquo;s Willpower. If the player scores more successes than the victim, he acquires a virulent disease immediately. The disease has the following effects:<br><br>&bull; The victim&rsquo;s Strength and Wits are halved (round down).<br><br>&bull; The victim loses one point of Dexterity.</p>\n<p><br>&bull; The victim&rsquo;s player must spend one additional blood point every evening for the vampire to rouse himself to consciousness. Mortals lose one health level per day instead.</p>\n<p><br>&bull; The victim&rsquo;s player must roll Self-Control or Instinct each time the character feeds (difficulty 8). On a failure, the vampire cannot keep the blood he just ingested inside his body, and he vomits it up in great horrifying gouts of gore, losing any benefit the blood might have provided. Humans vomit up food.<br><br>Every evening at sunset, the victim has a chance to throw off the plague. The victim&rsquo;s player rolls Stamina, with a difficulty equal to 10 minus the number of sunsets since acquiring the plague. On a successful roll, the character fights the disease to a standstill and begins to recover. He instantly regains his ability to manage blood, and he heals back one lost Attribute point per hour until all have returned.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"medicine","bonus":0,"difficulty":"6","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.OK43YIMy3WJt8zRf"},"cf":{"id":"temp_29xrm8dfvtq","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Grave's Decay","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670842147642,"modifiedTime":1674221169134,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"UEXnKNFYwkuDm58L","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Concentration (1pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 484","description":"<p>You have the ability to focus your mind and shut out any distractions or annoyances. Characters with this Merit are unaffected by any penalties stemming from distracting circumstances (e.g., loud noises, strobe lights, or hanging upside down).</p>","details":"<p>Mental</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.3c69WsogpTzqkk2t"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1a3wwhsmx3r","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672390956649,"modifiedTime":1674439880182,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"UFfaj5LPLhUrbdll","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Enchanting Voice (2pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 480","description":"<p>There is something about your voice that others cannot ignore. When you command, they are cowed. When you seduce, they swoon. Whether thundering, soothing, persuading, or simply talking, your voice commands attention. The difficulties of all rolls involving the use of the voice to persuade, charm, or command are reduced by two.</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_644ptrzk5eq","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/2 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672364948802,"modifiedTime":1674439884609,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"UJ7jnenNHHxxUifZ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Clinch","type":"Melee Weapon","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/naturalweapons.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 276","description":"Clinch: On a successful attack roll, the attacker goes into a clinch with the target. In the first turn, the attacker may roll Strength damage. In each subsequent turn, combatants act on their orders in the initiative. A combatant can inflict Strength damage automatically or attempt to escape the clinch. No other actions are allowed until one combatant breaks free. To escape a clinch, make a resisted Strength + Brawl roll against the opponent. If the escaping character has more successes, she breaks free; if not, the characters continue to grapple in the next turn.\n\nTraits: Strength + Brawl\nDifficulty: Normal\nAccuracy: Normal\nDamage: Strength","details":"","isequipped":false,"ismagical":false,"isweapon":false,"attack":{"attribute":"strength","ability":"brawl","secondaryabilityid":"","accuracy":0,"isrollable":true},"damage":{"attribute":"strength","bonus":0,"type":"bashing","isrollable":true},"difficulty":"6","conceal":"NA","istwohanded":false,"isnatural":true},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2f06ozkysk3","path":"Items#/CF_SEP/Natural Weapons","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674290690608,"modifiedTime":1674440439658,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"UJJZe262jdePAY3Z","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Oathbreaker (2pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 182","description":"<p>Making an oath ties one person&rsquo;s svadharma to another, linking the two spirits until the oath can be fulfilled. With this in mind, a Ravnos never breaks her word once given in good faith, and so long as it was done with proper ceremony. If the Ravnos spits into her palm and shakes on her word, then the oath cannot be broken without negatively impacting the vampire&rsquo;s svadharma (or so Ravnos superstition dictates).&nbsp;<br><br>The oathbreaker will lose her way, falling into vice and worthlessness, until the broken oath can be redeemed. Anyone who looks at your aura can see a sickly red slash indicating the broken oath. You may not spend Willpower to ignore your Ravnos vice, and you do not gain Willpower from fulfilling your Nature.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.zUU0GMx54Wg5U2FH"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ah1xgfy02pt","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Ravnos","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221093378,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"UR95KzInImeovpwZ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Multiple Curses (3pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 26","description":"<p>In addition to the normal curse imposed upon you by your caste or sect, you suffer one additional one associated with the Assamite Clan. Most likely, you are a rare vizier or sorcerer within the Sabbat who suffers the Baali Curse in addition to your normal caste-imposed curse, but at the Storyteller&rsquo;s discretion, other combinations may be possible.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_naefi5ko57","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Assamite","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221080836,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"UXzaX3hlbO5mf2bC","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Disgrace to the Blood (3pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 492","description":"<p>Your sire regards the fact that he Embraced you to be a titanic mistake, and has let everyone know it. You are mocked at gatherings, taunted by your peers, and actively despised by the one who should be giving you guidance. Any request or petition you make is likely to be looked down upon by friends of your sire, and your achievements are likely to be discounted.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_81150czgfr","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221107746,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"UaOlfHRQVwGPmGPq","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●● Weather Control","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 228","description":"<p>Command over the weather has long been a staple power of wizards both mortal and immortal, and this path is said to predate the Tremere by millennia. The proliferation of usage of this path outside the Clan tends to confirm this theory; Weather Control is quite common outside the Tremere, and even outside the Camarilla. Lower levels of this path allow subtle manipulations, while higher stages of mastery allow a vampire to call up raging storms. The area affected by this power is usually rather small, no more than three or four miles (five to six kilometers) in diameter, and the changes the power wreaks are not always immediate.</p>","details":"<p>The number of successes rolled indicates how long it takes the weather magic to take effect. One success indicates an entire day may pass before the weather changes to the thaumaturge&rsquo;s liking, while a roll with five successes brings an almost instant effect.<br><br>The difficulty of the Willpower roll necessary to invoke this power may change depending on the current local weather conditions and the weather the character is attempting to create. The Storyteller should impose a bonus (-1 or -2 difficulty) for relatively minor shifts, such as clearing away a light drizzle or calling lightning when a severe thunderstorm is already raging. Conversely, a penalty (+1 or +2 difficulty) should be applied when the desired change is at odds with the current conditions, such as summoning the same light drizzle in the middle of the Sahara Desert or calling down lightning from a cloudless sky.<br><br>If the character tries to strike a specific target with lightning, the player must roll Perception + Occult (difficulty 6 if the target is standing in open terrain, 8 if he is under shelter, or 10 if he is inside but near a window) in addition to the base roll to use Thaumaturgy. Otherwise the bolt goes astray, with the relative degree of failure of the roll determining where exactly the lightning strikes.<br><br>Effects of the power default to the maximum area available unless the caster states that he&rsquo;s attempting to affect a smaller area. At Storyteller discretion, an additional Willpower roll (difficulty 6) may be required to keep the change in the weather under control.<br><br>Weather Control is not the sort of power that lends itself well to indoor application. While certain of the path&rsquo;s uses (changes of temperature, high winds, and possibly even fog) do make a certain amount of sense in interior settings, others (precipitation of any sort, lightning) don&rsquo;t. The difficulty for all rolls to use Weather Control indoors is at +2, and the Storyteller should feel free to disallow any proposed uses that don&rsquo;t make sense.<br><br>Individual power descriptions are not provided for this path, as the general principle is fairly consistent. Instead, the strongest weather phenomenon possible at each level is listed.<br><br>&bull; <strong>Fog:</strong> Vision is slightly impaired and sounds are muffled; a +1 difficulty is imposed on all Perception rolls that involve sight and hearing, and the effective range of all ranged attacks are halved.</p>\n<p><strong>Light breeze:</strong> A +1 difficulty is imposed on all Perception rolls that involve smell.<br>Minor temperature change: It is possible to raise or lower the local temperature by up to 10 degrees Fahrenheit or 5 degrees Celsius.<br><br>&bull;&bull; <strong>Rain or snow:</strong> As Fog, but Perception rolls are impaired to a much greater extent; the difficulty modifier for all such rolls rises to +2. In addition, the difficulty on all Drive rolls increases by two.<br><br>&bull;&bull;&bull; <strong>High Winds: </strong>The wind speed rises to around 30 miles per hour or 50 kilometers per hour, with gusts of up to twice that. Ranged attacks are much more difficult: + 1 to firearm attacks and +2 to thrown weapons and archery. In addition, during fierce gusts, Dexterity rolls (difficulty 6) may be required to keep characters from being knocked over by the winds. When gale-force winds are in effect, papers go flying, objects get picked up by the winds and hurled with abandon, and other suitably cinematic effects are likely. Moderate temperature change: The local temperature can be raised or lowered by up to 20 degrees Fahrenheit or 10 degrees Celsius.<br><br>&bull;&bull;&bull;&bull; <strong>Storm: </strong>This has the effects of both Rain and High Winds.<br><br>&bull;&bull;&bull;&bull;&bull;<strong> Lightning Strike: </strong>This attack inflicts 10 dice of lethal damage. Body armor does not add to the target&rsquo;s dice pool to soak this attack.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"-1","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_f49edd5304p","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/Weather Control","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439748600,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"Uc7CUuQMnD5yBP5Y","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Member of the Pack (2pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 87","description":"<p>You can only summon, speak to, and command a specific type of animal &mdash; ravens, rats, and so forth &mdash; with Animalism. Your Storyteller is the best adjudicator of what types of animal are appropriate for this Flaw, but the choice should be fairly limiting. Other animals do not respond to your uses of Animalism at all.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1nj44zxegwk","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Gangrel","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221084283,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"UlU0IIyvjGePBEoG","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●● The Form of the Cobra","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 210","description":"<p>The Cainite may change his form into that of a huge black cobra. The serpent weighs as much as the vampire&rsquo;s human form, stretches over 10 feet or three meters long, and is about 20 inches (50 cm) around. The Form of the Cobra grants several advantages, including a venomous bite, the ability to slither through small spaces, and a greatly enhanced sense of smell. The character may use any Disciplines while in this form save those that require hands (such as Feral Claws).</p>","details":"<p>The vampire spends one blood point; the change is automatic, but takes three turns. Clothing and small personal possessions transform with the vampire. The vampire remains in serpent form until the next dawn, unless he desires to change back sooner. The Storyteller may allow the Setite bonus dice on all Perception rolls related to smell, but the difficulties for all hearing rolls are increased by two. The cobra&rsquo;s bite inflicts damage equal to the vampire&rsquo;s, but the vampire does not need to grapple his victim; furthermore, the poison delivered is fatal to mortals.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pqy5koxd4a","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Serpentis","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670333270322,"modifiedTime":1674439708872,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"UlY5vJMAwcNXqDeW","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"● Passion","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 148","description":"<p>The vampire stirs his victim&rsquo;s emotions, either heightening them to a fevered pitch or blunting them until the target is completely desensitized. The Cainite may not choose which emotion is affected; she may only amplify or dull emotions already present in the target. In this way, a vampire can inflame mild irritation into quivering rage or atrophy true love into casual interest.</p>","details":"<p>The character talks to her victim, and the vampire&rsquo;s player rolls Charisma + Empathy (difficulty equals the victim&rsquo;s Humanity or Path rating). The number of successes determines the duration of the altered state of feeling. Effects of this power might include one- or two-point additions or subtractions to difficulties of frenzy rolls, Virtue rolls, rolls to resist Presence powers, etc.<br><br></p>\n<table border=\"1\"><colgroup><col><col></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Successes</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1 Success</td>\n<td>One turn</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2 Successes</td>\n<td>One hour</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3 Successes</td>\n<td>One night</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4 Successes</td>\n<td>One week</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5 Successes</td>\n<td>One month</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6+ Successes</td>\n<td>Three months</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"charisma","dice2":"empathy","bonus":0,"difficulty":"-1","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_us1ho2ufuwm","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Dementation","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670227211287,"modifiedTime":1674221160050,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"UlbG9olBFw0LKfPk","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Mage Blood (5pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 219","description":"<p>Your blood is so tied to magic that you find you are unable to use any Discipline apart from Thaumaturgy (and for Kindred who are not Tremere, it is still paid for at out-of-Clan rates). While no path or ritual is barred to you, you may not gain any dots in any other Discipline.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_kchlaqnn8q","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Tremere#/CF_SEP/Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221095831,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"Uo774Qjiwm3VsIoG","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"● Ignis Fatuus","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 144","description":"<p>The vampire may conjure a minor, static mirage that confounds one sense. For instance, he may evoke a sulfurous stench, the appearance of stigmata, or the shatter of broken glass. Note that though tactile illusions can be felt, they have no real substance; an invisible but tactile wall cannot confine anyone, and invisible razor-wire causes no real damage. Similarly, the vampire must know the characteristics of what he&rsquo;s creating. While it&rsquo;s easy enough to estimate what a knife wound might look like, falsifying a person&rsquo;s voice or a photograph of a childhood home requires knowledge of the details.</p>","details":"<p>The player spends a point of Willpower for the vampire to create this illusion. The volume of smells, ambient lighting, smoke clouds, and the like are limited to roughly 20 cubic feet (half a cubic meter) per dot the vampire has in Chimerstry. The illusion lasts until the vampire leaves its vicinity (such as stepping out of the room) or until another person sees through it somehow. The Cainite may also end the illusion at any time with no effort.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_jgyzexzzmb","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Chimerstry","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670226749831,"modifiedTime":1674221159039,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"V28jw3vP4H8gsUm6","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●● Arms of the Abyss","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 189","description":"<p>Refining his control over darkness, the Kindred can create prehensile tentacles that emerge from patches of dim lighting. These tentacles may grasp, restrain, and constrict foes.</p>","details":"<p>The player spends a blood point and makes a simple (never extended) Manipulation + Occult roll (difficulty 7); each success enables the creation of a single tentacle. Each tentacle is six feet (two meters) long and possesses Strength and Dexterity ratings equal to the invoking vampire&rsquo;s Obtenebration Trait &mdash; Potence and Celerity dots are added to these Strength and Dexterity ratings, respectively. If the vampire chooses, she may spend a blood point either to increase a single tentacle&rsquo;s Strength or Dexterity by one or to extend its length by another six feet or two meters. Each tentacle has four health levels, is affected by fire and sunlight as if it were a vampire, and soaks bashing and lethal damage using the vampire&rsquo;s Stamina + Fortitude. Aggravated damage may not be soaked.<br><br>Tentacles may constrict foes, inflicting (Strength +1) lethal damage per turn. Breaking the grasp of a tentacle requires the victim to win a resisted Strength roll against the tentacle (difficulty 6 for each). However, tentacles cannot be used for any kind of manipulation, such as typing or driving.<br><br>All tentacles need not emanate from the same source &mdash; so long as there are multiple patches of suitable darkness, there are sources for the Arms of the Abyss. Controlling the tentacles does not require complete concentration; if the Kindred is not incapacitated or in torpor, she may control tentacles while carrying out other actions.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"manipulation","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"7","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_vi4zrg6o2vi","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Obtenebration","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670300067813,"modifiedTime":1674221178509,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"V2ot8kn4Rx7a2Rrd","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Occhio d’Uomo Morto","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 179","description":"<p>To cast this ritual, the necromancer needs an eye from a corpse whose absent soul became a ghost or Spectre. The eye is ritually prepared in a process involving incense, the new moon, and a period of midnight chanting. The chanting climaxes when the necromancer removes one of her own eyes and replaces it with the one from the corpse (fresher is better). Kindred healing takes over at that point, sealing the eye within the socket.<br><br>If the ritual succeeds, the Necromancer permanently gains the Shroudsight ability (see p. 163). This ability is always active and does not require a roll.<br><br>Furthermore, if it was a Spectre&rsquo;s corpse, the vampire can hear the vague murmuring of any Spectres in the area. This ability isn&rsquo;t very precise; rather than mind reading, it&rsquo;s more like trying to overhear a low-voiced conversation in the next room. With a Perception + Occult roll, the Necromancer can glean a very vague impression of what nearby Spectres are up to. Botching this roll may well earn the necromancer a new derangement (at the Storyteller&rsquo;s discretion), as the whispers creep into the caster&rsquo;s subconscious.<br><br>This ritual has some major drawbacks, the first being that its proper result is hideously ugly. Unless the vampire wears sunglasses or finds some other way to conceal her eye, her Appearance is reduced by one dot.<br><br>Also, dead or rotted tissue is not the best for normal perception. Any mundane visual Perception rolls are at +1 difficulty (possibly more if the corpse had bad eyesight in life). On the other hand, since the eye offers a window into a different soul than the necromancer, it offers some protection against powers requiring eye contact. These Disciplines are used against the deadeyed necromancer at +1 difficulty.<br><br>Most importantly, however, the ghost whose body was desecrated knows it, and very likely<em> hates</em> it. The ghost can find the necromancer possessing his eye anywhere, and all ghostly powers used against the necromancer by that particular ghost are at &ndash;1 difficulty.</p>","details":"<p>Casting times for necromantic rituals vary widely; see the description for particulars. The player rolls Intelligence + Occult (difficulty 3 + the level of the ritual, maximum 9). Success indicates the ritual proceeds smoothly, failure produces no effect, and a botch indicates something has gone horribly wrong.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"5","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_b17ggxg6joc","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 2 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670899739755,"modifiedTime":1674221173572,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"VREgegUKdMUBvlVE","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●● Soul Feast","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 175","description":"<p>Just as the necromancer can release entropic energies from within, she may also pull them into herself as a source of power. Soul Feasting allows the caster to either draw on the ambient death energies around her or to actively feed on a ghost, stealing the wraith&rsquo;s substance and mystically transforming that energy into sustenance.</p>","details":"<p>The player spends one Willpower point to allow the vampire to feed on the negative energies of the dead. If the character is drawing the energies from the atmosphere, she must be in a place where death has occurred within the hour or in a place where death is common, such as a cemetery, a morgue, or the scene of a recent murder. Generally, the necromancer can draw anywhere from one to four points of entropy from such a location, although the difficulty in using all Necromancy and similar deathly powers within the area increases by an equal amount for a number of nights equal to the points taken. The energies of such an area may only be drained once until the area&rsquo;s entropy replenishes.<br><br>In cases when the necromancer feeds on a ghost, the vampire must actually attack the wraith as if feeding normally. Wraiths have up to 10 &ldquo;blood points&rdquo; that may be taken from them, and they become less and less substantial as their spirit essence drains away. The character is vulnerable to any attack the ghost might make, even those that do not normally affect the physical world; while feeding, the vampire is essentially in a half-state, existing in both the living lands and the Underworld simultaneously. The wraith so attacked is considered immobilized and cannot run or escape unless it can defeat the vampire in a resisted Willpower roll (difficulty 6 for both sides). This power may also be used in conjunction with Ash Path Necromancy, allowing the vampire to drain power (though not sustenance) from ghosts while traveling in the lands of the dead.<br><br>This soul energy may be used just like blood in every respect except for when the vampire rises for the night. It can activate Disciplines, heal wounds, boost Attributes, etc. Botching this power renders the vampire unable to feed through the Shroud for the rest of the night. However, she remains susceptible to the assaults of ghosts and spirits for several turns (generally, a number of turns equal to the amount of energy that could have been drawn from the area, or one turn if attacking a ghost) as she hovers between worlds, unable to function effectively in either.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"6","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.h3miymUUqu7RKygI"},"cf":{"id":"temp_wle9pw2x1y","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/Vitreous Path","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670842147642,"modifiedTime":1674221171147,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"VRwIctneqajyPFZS","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"Feature","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2d9fqjslrzb","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Conjuring","color":"#000000","name":"The Path of Conjuring","children":[],"folderPath":["temp_444y5utucrj","temp_26bm5shk25q","temp_g6lsl2i5ymg"],"fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":null,"sorting":"a","contents":["00XLtotO04X0JJUP","lFP6npICouusQGqX","1AS0WwSxpLXNdUbP","ZoO5qNY4wBwGxmHY","T0SpTLOPUdr0Y356","PyMm9EP65yBENb1z"],"version":"2.5.6"}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"iscreated":false,"version":"","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"","description":"","details":"","type":"","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674439744070,"modifiedTime":1674439744391,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"Vcz1Mo0N0SFbZOO6"}
{"name":"●● Subvert","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 222","description":"<p>This power follows the same principle as does Contradict, the release of a subject&rsquo;s dark, self-destructive side. However, Subvert&rsquo;s effects are longer-lasting than the momentary flare of Contradiction. Under the influence of this power, victims act on their own suppressed temptations, pursuing agendas that their morals or self-control would forbid them to follow under normal circumstances.</p>","details":"<p>This power requires the character to make eye contact (see p. 152) with the intended victim. The player rolls normally. The target resists with a roll of Perception + Subterfuge (difficulty equal to the target&rsquo;s Manipulation + Subterfuge). If the thaumaturge scores more successes, the victim becomes inclined to follow a repressed, shameful desire for the length of time described below.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table border=\"1\"><colgroup><col><col></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Successes</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1 Success</td>\n<td>Five minutes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2 Successes</td>\n<td>One hour</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3 Successes</td>\n<td>One night</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4 Successes</td>\n<td>Three nights</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5 Successes</td>\n<td>One week</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>The Storyteller determines the precise desire or agenda that the victim follows. It should be in keeping with the Psychological Flaws that she possesses or with the negative aspects of her Nature (for example, a Loner desiring isolation to such an extent that she becomes violent if forced to attend a social function). The subject should not become fixated on following this new agenda at all times, but should occasionally be forced to spend a Willpower point if the opportunity to succumb arises and she wishes to resist the impulse.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"5","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.9E6akUkM8fmk95bk"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lcnzlnkbov","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Corruption","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439744586,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"Vel08XhsLYAC0MAN","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Prey Exclusion (1pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 485","description":"<p>You refuse to hunt a certain class of prey. You might refuse to feed on drug dealers, policemen, accountants, or rich people &mdash; if you accidentally feed upon such an individual, you automatically frenzy and must make a roll to prevent Humanity or Path loss (difficulty 7). Witnessing other Kindred feeding on the object of your exclusion might also provoke a frenzy, at the Storyteller&rsquo;s discretion. Ventrue, owing to the limitations already imposed on their feeding by their Clan weakness, may not take this Flaw.</p>","details":"<p>Mental</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vpU7tfPjRILQuAc4"},"cf":{"id":"temp_jwd9ok2vgth","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221102427,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"VjIRNA0UzZZ81L95","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
