{"name":"Bastone Diabolico","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 181","description":"<p>Casting this ritual is tricky because it requires the removal of a leg bone from a living person. The donor must survive the removal, at least for a little while. The bone is then submerged in molten lead. Once it cools, the thin lead coating is inscribed with various runes. The necromancer then uses this metal-shod bone to beat its donor to death while repeating a droning Greek chant.<br><br><br></p>\n<p>With a successful roll, this ritual produces a <em>bastone</em><br><em>diabolico</em> or &ldquo;devil stick.&rdquo; The stick can be activated by<br>anyone who holds it and expends a point of Willpower.<br>Activation lasts for a scene, and during that time any</p>\n<p>ghost hit with the devil stick loses a point from its Pas-<br>sion pool (see p. 385). In addition to its normal effects,</p>\n<p>this club does an additional die of damage when used<br>against the walking dead (not vampires), and such<br>damage is aggravated.<br><br><br>Unfortunately for the necromancer, ghosts can sense<br>that the<em> bastone diabolico</em> is bad news, even if they don&rsquo;t<br>know exactly what the thing does. They tend to stay<br>away from anybody carrying one, which means that all<br>rolls for such a character to use powers that summon or<br>attract ghosts occur at +1 difficulty.</p>","details":"<p>Casting times for necromantic rituals vary widely; see the description for particulars. The player rolls Intelligence + Occult (difficulty 3 + the level of the ritual, maximum 9). Success indicates the ritual proceeds smoothly, failure produces no effect, and a botch indicates something has gone horribly wrong.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"7","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2r4138smwse","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 4 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670899739755,"modifiedTime":1674221175619,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"c3KJZ8akY1uYIugy","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Recure of the Homeland","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 234","description":"<p>The vampire calls on the power of the earth to heal grave wounds she may have received. The thaumaturge must use at least a handful of dirt from the city or town of her mortal birth and recite a litany of her mortal family tree as she casts this ritual.</p>","details":"<p>The Cainite must mix the earth with two points of her own blood to make a healing paste. One handful will heal one aggravated wound, and only one handful can be used per night. This ritual can only be used on the vampire who knows it.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"5","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SOFUQHVyXwWb4xVU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_b8aps3s6gl","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 2 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671081485306,"modifiedTime":1674439752059,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"cKDUPN7UgtJdeoqI","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"● A Taste for Blood","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 213","description":"<p>This power was developed as a means of testing a foe&rsquo;s might &mdash; an extremely important ability in the tumultuous early nights of Clan Tremere. By merely touching the blood of his subject, the caster may determine how much vitae remains in the subject and, if the subject is a vampire, how recently he has fed, his approximate Generation and, with three or more successes, whether he has ever committed diablerie.</p>","details":"<p>The number of successes achieved on the roll determines how much information the thaumaturge gleans and how accurate it is.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"4","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_v3rmtx67pm","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Blood","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670930910577,"modifiedTime":1674439742465,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"cRRcKGVuPpsQ2lKx","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
