{"name":"One Eye (2pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 481","description":"<p>You have only one eye &mdash; which eye is missing is up to you. The difficulties of all Perception rolls involving eyesight are increased by two, and the difficulties of all die rolls requiring depth perception are increased by one (this includes ranged combat).</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2wewy46vpbx","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/2 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672365603221,"modifiedTime":1674221105877,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"k4Wodp2xXJaTiaes","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Warding Circle vs. Ghosts","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 234","description":"<p>This ritual is enacted in a manner similar to that of Ward versus Ghouls, but creates a circle centered on the caster into which a [ghosts] cannot pass without being burned. The circle can be made as large and as permanent as the caster desires, as long as she is willing to pay the necessary price. Many Tremere chantries and havens are protected by this and other Warding Circle rituals.</p>","details":"<p>The ritual requires [\"larger amount\" of a handful of powdered marble from a tombstone]. The caster determines the size of the warding circle when it is cast; the default radius is 10 feet/3 meters, and every 10-foot/3-meter increase raises the difficulty by one, to a maximum of 9 (one additional success is required for every increase past the number necessary to raise the difficulty to 9). The player spends one blood point for every 10 feet/3 meters of radius and rolls. The ritual takes the normal casting time if it is to be short-term (lasting for the rest of the night) or one night if it is to be long-term (lasting a year and a day).<br><br>Once the warding circle is established, any [ghosts] who attempts to cross its boundary feels a tingle on his skin and a slight breeze on his face &mdash; a successful Intelligence + Occult roll (difficulty 8) identifies this as a warding circle. If the [ghosts] attempts to press on, he must roll more successes on a Willpower roll (difficulty of the caster&rsquo;s Thaumaturgy rating + 3) than the caster rolled when establishing the ward. Failure indicates that the ward blocks his passage and inflicts three dice of bashing damage, and his next roll to attempt to enter the circle is at +1 difficulty. If the [ghosts] leaves the circle and attempts to enter it again, he must repeat the roll. Attempts to leave the circle are not blocked.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"8","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SOFUQHVyXwWb4xVU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4r55auipjzn","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 5 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671081485306,"modifiedTime":1674440282537,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"k80aWOJuO3xjmnr7","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Forked Tongue (2pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 67","description":"<p>Your tongue is forked, flickering, and inhumanly reptilian. Upholding the Masquerade becomes difficult for you. Note that this tongue does not inflict aggravated damage, nor draw blood.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.28JiCemvASqixsXE"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8mau8cmb57t","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Followers of Set","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221083102,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"k8FRgOVzX7xAjD4z","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●● Wind Dance","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 224","description":"<p>The thaumaturge invokes the power of the winds, moving in a blur. She gains a preternatural edge in avoiding her enemies&rsquo; blows, moving out of their way before the enemy has a chance to throw them.</p>","details":"<p>The player can dodge any number of attacks with her full dice pool in a single turn. This advantage applies only to dodges &mdash; if the character wishes to attack and dodge, the player must still split her dice pool. This power lasts for one scene.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"6","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.xs9y10bdAQRkgcNU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4yk16ojy6jl","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Mars","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439745766,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"kAFKnnixsTCnScbS","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"● Witness of Death","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 160","description":"<p>Before it is possible to control the dead, one must perceive them. This power allows just that, attuning a vampire&rsquo;s unliving senses to the presence of the incorporeal.<br><br>Under its effects, a necromancer sees ghosts as translucent phantoms gliding among the living and hears their whispers and moans. She feels the spectral cold of their touch and smells their musty hint of decay. Yet one cannot mistake the dead for the living, as they lack true substance, and appear dimmer and less real than creatures of flesh and blood. When a vampire uses this power, her eyes flicker with pale blue fire that only the dead can see.<br><br>Ghosts resent being spied upon, and more powerful shades may use their own powers to inflict their displeasure on the incautious.</p>","details":"<p>The player rolls Perception + Awareness (difficulty 5). Success allows the vampire to perceive ghosts as described for the rest of the scene (in the mortal world &mdash; seeing ghosts in the land of the dead requires Shroudsight, on p. 163). Failure has no special effect, but a botch means the vampire can see only the dead for the scene; everything else appears as shapeless, dim shadows. While the vampire&rsquo;s other senses remain attuned to the living, he is all but blind in this state and suffers a +3 difficulty to most vision-based Perception rolls and attacks. Ghosts notice the glowing eyes of a vampire using this power only with a successful Perception + Alertness roll (difficulty 7).</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"perception","dice2":"awareness","bonus":0,"difficulty":"5","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6fvqbb4wn0f","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Sepulchre Path","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670842147642,"modifiedTime":1674221169853,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"kBHS9H9pK7TlpEsW","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"The Sepulchre Path","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/mainpower_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 160","description":"<p>Through the Sepulchre path, the vampire can witness, summon, and command the spirits of the dead. At higher levels, the necromancer can force the ghost to remain in a particular place or object, or even damage wraiths directly. Since many other areas of Necromancy involve dealing with ghosts, this is the most common path for necromancers to start with.</p>","details":"<p><strong>Note:</strong> If a Kindred uses a Sepulchre Path power in the presence of something of great importance to the ghost the power affects, the chances for success in the summoning increase dramatically (reduce the difficulty by 2). This might be the bathtub in which the ghost&rsquo;s mortal body was drowned, the rusted-out wreck of the car where the ghost&rsquo;s physical body was trapped alive, or something unrelated to the ghost&rsquo;s demise, such as a favorite book or a child-ghost&rsquo;s beloved nursery.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepath","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":0,"isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6fvqbb4wn0f","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Sepulchre Path","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670841064343,"modifiedTime":1674221170384,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"kDPkbKXedWaSixl1","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
