{"name":"Fame","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 114","description":"<p>You enjoy widespread recognition in mortal society, perhaps as an entertainer, writer, or athlete. People may enjoy just being seen with you. This gives you all manner of privileges when moving in mortal society, but can also attract an unwanted amount of attention now that you&rsquo;re no longer alive. The greatest weapon fame has to offer is the ability to sway public opinion &mdash; as modern media constantly proves. Fame isn&rsquo;t always tied to entertainment: A heinous criminal in a high-profile trial probably has a certain amount of fame, as do a lawmaker and a scientist who has made a popularized discovery.<br><br>This Background is obviously a mixed blessing. You can certainly enjoy the privileges of your prestige &mdash; getting the best seats, being invited to events you&rsquo;d otherwise miss, getting appointments with the elite &mdash; but you&rsquo;re sometimes recognized when you&rsquo;d rather not be. However, your enemies can&rsquo;t just make you disappear without causing an undue stir, and you find it much easier to hunt in populated areas as people flock to you (reduce the difficulties of hunting rolls by one for each dot in Fame). Additionally, your Storyteller might permit you to reduce difficulties of certain Social rolls against particularly star-struck or impressionable people.</p>","details":"<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 85px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 16.782%;\"><col style=\"width: 83.218%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">●</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">You&rsquo;re known to a select subculture&nbsp;&mdash; local club-goers, industry bloggers,&nbsp;or the Park Avenue set, for instance.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">●●</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">Random people start to recognize&nbsp;your face; you&rsquo;re a minor celebrity&nbsp;such as a small-time criminal or a&nbsp;local news anchor.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">●●●</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">You have greater renown; perhaps&nbsp;you&rsquo;re a senator or an entertainer who&nbsp;regularly gets hundreds of thousands&nbsp;of YouTube hits.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">●●●●</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">A full-blown celebrity; your name is&nbsp;often recognized by the average&nbsp;person on the street.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">●●●●●</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">You&rsquo;re a household word. People&nbsp;name their children after you.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"wod.types.background","level":"","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_14tdb2ntd4k","path":"Backgrounds","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1673844458648,"modifiedTime":1674221071549,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"kem1kyTF9BXEWH0K","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"True Love (4pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 493","description":"<p>You have discovered, perhaps too late, a true love. He or she is mortal, but is the center of your existence, and inspires you to keep going in a world of darkness and despair. Whenever you suffer, the thought of your true love gives you the strength to persevere. This Merit grants you one automatic success on all Willpower rolls, which can be negated only by a botch die. This can be a great gift but also a hindrance, for your true love may require protection and occasionally rescue.</p>","details":"<p>Supernatural</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_02lw4m6r7kvf","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/4 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674439934711,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"kgMG5tsMoakG9LEI","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Permanent Fangs (3pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 482","description":"<p>Your fangs do not retract, making it impossible for you to hide your true nature. While some mortals may think you&rsquo;ve had your teeth filed or are wearing prosthetics, sooner or later you&rsquo;re going to run into someone who knows what you truly are. You are also limited to a maximum Appearance rating of 3.</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_81150czgfr","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672365603221,"modifiedTime":1674221108716,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"kgiHEHJQInznFCLo","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Dementation","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/mainpower_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 148","description":"<p>Dementation is the Discipline that allows a vampire to focus and channel madness into the minds of those around him. Though it&rsquo;s the natural legacy of the Malkavians, practitioners of Dementation need not actually be mad to use the Discipline... but it helps.<br><br>Disturbingly, Dementation doesn&rsquo;t actually make their victims mad, but rather it seems to break down the doors to the hidden darkness of the target&rsquo;s mind, releasing into the open whatever is found there. The Malkavians claim that this is because insanity is the next logical step in mental evolution, a transhumanist advancement of what modern people consider consciousness. Other Kindred scoff that this reasoning is an outright justification for the chaos that Dementation brings. They don&rsquo;t scoff too loudly, however, lest the Malkavian advance their consciousness next.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.discipline","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_us1ho2ufuwm","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Dementation","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670227163337,"modifiedTime":1674221160562,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"kkOpbLuNrxFN39u5","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
