{"name":"● Elemental Strength","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 214","description":"<p>The vampire can draw upon the strength and resilience of the earth, or of the objects around him, to increase his physical prowess without the need for large amounts of blood.</p>","details":"<p>The player allocates a total of three temporary bonus dots between the character&rsquo;s Strength and Stamina. The number of successes on the roll to activate the power is the number of turns these dots remain. The player may spend a Willpower point to increase this duration by one turn. This power cannot be &ldquo;stacked&rdquo; &mdash; one application must expire before the next can be made.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"4","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_jxq3k0gu1p","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/Elemental Mastery","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439736507,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"l1wTWz1Gz6SNGtDr","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Mortuario (2 or 4pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 106","description":"<p>You died. Perhaps you were murdered, or simply had a car accident. Whatever the cause, you were gone. But your sire found you too useful, or couldn&rsquo;t let you go. You were Embraced using the Ferryman&rsquo;s Recall ritual (see p. 109). The Embrace left you with the scars of your death, eternal tracework reminders of your trip to the other side. It also left you with the taut, pallid complexion of the dead.<br><br>In addition to the traditional weakness of your Clan, you also suffer disfigurement from your time as a true corpse. While you are able to heal yourself just like any other vampire, the wounds do not heal cleanly. You retain the scars of every experience. Depending on the nature of the damage, this can make social dealings exceedingly difficult, and may decrease your Appearance dots over time (even to 0). However, your time across the Shroud also gave you a natural feel for necromantic blood magic. The difficulties of all Necromancy rolls are reduced by two. This trait costs 4 points for characters who already have an appearance of 0 (such as Samedi and the Harbingers of Skulls), or 2 points for any other Kindred. It is an incredibly rare condition even among the Giovanni, and essentially unknown outside the Clan.<br><br>Giovanni with this Merit generally arouse the superstition of their Clan, and are treated with a definite wariness, particularly by Anziani. Characters with the Mortuario Merit may not also possess the Sanguine Incongruity Merit or similar flaws such as Monstrous.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.LbgcRVS0cl7m6sm1"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1o80meebnjn","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Giovanni","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221085398,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"l7Au37CbI6172KGd","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"SMG, Large (Full-Auto)","type":"Ranged Weapon","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/rangedweapons.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 281","description":"Automatic Fire:The weapon unloads its entire ammunition clip in one attack against a single target. The attacker makes a single roll, adding 10 dice to her accuracy. However, the attack roll is at a +2 difficulty due to the weapon’s recoil. Extra successes add to the damage dice pool, which is still treated as equivalent to one bullet. An attacker using automatic fire may not target a specific area of the body.This attack is permissible only if the weapon’s clip is at least half-full to begin with.","details":"","isequipped":false,"ismagical":false,"isweapon":false,"attack":{"attribute":"dexterity","ability":"firearms","secondaryabilityid":"","accuracy":10,"isrollable":true},"damage":{"attribute":"","bonus":4,"type":"lethal","isrollable":true},"difficulty":"8","conceal":"T","istwohanded":false,"range":50,"rate":3,"mode":{"hasreload":false,"hasburst":false,"hasfullauto":true,"hasspray":false},"clip":{"value":0,"max":30}},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6yghfiu9569","path":"Items#/CF_SEP/Ranged Weapons","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674287371409,"modifiedTime":1674440442191,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"l8eqGxATAYzbpe4H","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
