{"name":"Hive-Minded (1 or 2pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 86","description":"<p>Your Animalism works on insects and other creepy-crawlies in addition to mammalian animals. If you select the two-point version of&nbsp; this merit, your Protean forms may take the form of an insectoid swarm rather than a single creature (though the swarm must be of a size equivalent to a wolf or a bat, as appropriate).</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1nj44zxegwk","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Gangrel","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221084087,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"mPeLPZAzg1ooj5wc","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Cold Read (3pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 142","description":"<p>Whenever you meet someone for the first time, you may spend a number of points of Willpower equal to your Perception. For each point spent, you may ask the Storyteller one question about the character. The Storyteller must either answer truthfully or let you take the Willpower point back to you to avoid answering the question.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.BlOhgF30DvaW07aL"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1bn0ry0013fi","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Malkavians","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221087765,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"mVjrnivw6qp8piY0","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Guilt-Wracked (4pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 486","description":"<p>You simply cannot come to grips with the fact that you must drink blood to survive. You suffer horrible guilt over each time you feed (roll Conscience, difficulty 7, or else frenzy every time you feed &mdash; characters with the Conviction Virtue cannot take this Flaw) and try to avoid doing so as much as possible. This means what you rarely have much blood in your system, leaving you vulnerable to both attacks and hunger-based frenzies.</p>","details":"<p>Mental</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.cZFEczCCHA4TOnSS"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ry8o03n5zsc","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/4 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221110453,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"mYSycvkly8bTe42S","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Chill of Oblivion","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 183","description":"<p>Performed over the course of 12 hours (reduced by one hour per success on the casting roll), this ritual infuses the necromancer or a willing subject with the chill of the grave. The ritual&rsquo;s material component is a one-foot (half-meter) cube of ice, which is slowly melted on the subject&rsquo;s chest (inflicting three health levels of bashing damage on mortal subjects). The subject must lie naked on bare earth for the entire duration of the ritual. Once the ritual is completed, its effects remain for a number of nights equal to the caster&rsquo;s Occult rating.<br><br>An individual affected by Chill of Oblivion treats aggravated damage from fire and high temperatures as if it were lethal damage. Furthermore, he may attempt to extinguish any fire by rolling Willpower (difficulty 9); each success reduces the fire&rsquo;s soak difficulty (see p. 297) by 1, and a fire with a soak difficulty of 2 dwindles to glowing embers.<br><br>However, this ritual has several drawbacks. First and foremost, the subject&rsquo;s aura is laced with writhing black veins that resemble those left by diablerie, and may well be mistaken for such by any observer who is not familiar with this ritual. The subject also radiates a palpable aura of cold that extends to about arm&rsquo;s length from him; this can be extremely disconcerting to mortals, though it causes no damage, and its game effects mirror those of the Flaws Touch of Frost (p. 494) and Eerie Presence (p. 495). Finally, the mystical nimbus of the ritual draws hostile ghosts to the subject, who may plague him with unwholesome acts.</p>","details":"<p>Casting times for necromantic rituals vary widely; see the description for particulars. The player rolls Intelligence + Occult (difficulty 3 + the level of the ritual, maximum 9). Success indicates the ritual proceeds smoothly, failure produces no effect, and a botch indicates something has gone horribly wrong.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"8","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_0bc6awa1kzcg","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 5 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670899739755,"modifiedTime":1674221176484,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"mg8IG8hb3SSi9qNR","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"Feature","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_w0eb6iidngo","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Cenotaph Path","color":"#000000","name":"The Cenotaph Path","children":[],"folderPath":["temp_444y5utucrj","temp_9pmdboh96h5","temp_odkmoq9z4sc"],"fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":null,"sorting":"a","contents":["ZXRY70yFgCWRLswc","RTEsWORHaRX3dxwo","zXJEI0JbWqYX0RPF","cbwyiWpFb4u0O5MH","voo80z8a3OyS3yn4","RvtxeeMMPoJtuZvn"],"version":"2.5.6"}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"iscreated":false,"version":"","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"","description":"","details":"","type":"","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674221167415,"modifiedTime":1674221167733,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"mi9ZCPgXPfZI8BDH"}
{"name":"Puppet","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 179","description":"<p>Used primarily to facilitate conversations with the recently departed, though also applied as a method of psychological torture, Puppet prepares a subject (willing or unwilling) as a suitable receptacle for ghostly possession. Over the course of one hour, the necromancer smears grave soil across the subject&rsquo;s eyes, lips, and forehead. For the remainder of the night, any wraith attempting to take control of the subject gains two automatic successes. The ritual&rsquo;s effects remain even if the soil is washed off.</p>","details":"<p>Casting times for necromantic rituals vary widely; see the description for particulars. The player rolls Intelligence + Occult (difficulty 3 + the level of the ritual, maximum 9). Success indicates the ritual proceeds smoothly, failure produces no effect, and a botch indicates something has gone horribly wrong.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"5","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_b17ggxg6joc","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 2 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670899739755,"modifiedTime":1674221173671,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"mlr7ZWVerdM7IHDe","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Oracular Ability (3pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 493","description":"<p>You can see and interpret signs and omens. You are able to draw advice from these omens, for they provide hints of the future and warnings of the present. When the Storyteller feels that you are in position to see an omen, you will be required to make a Perception + Awareness roll, with the difficulty relative to how well the omen is concealed. If successful, you may then roll Intelligence + Occult to interpret what you have seen; the difficulty is again relative to the complexity of the omen.</p>","details":"<p>Supernatural</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_tbkdk4lk1q","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674440157877,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"mn9crmPvhIhKZPOM","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●●  Psychic Projection","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 138","description":"<p>The Kindred with this awesome ability projects her senses out of her physical shell, stepping from her body as an entity of pure thought. The vampire&rsquo;s astral form is immune to physical damage or fatigue, and can &ldquo;fly&rdquo; with blinding speed anywhere across the earth &mdash; or even underground &mdash; so long as she remains below the moon&rsquo;s orbit.<br><br>The Kindred&rsquo;s material form lies in a torpid state while her astral self is active, and the vampire isn&rsquo;t aware of anything that befalls her body until she returns to it. An ephemeral silver cord connects the Kindred&rsquo;s psyche to her body. If this cord is severed, her consciousness becomes stranded in the astral plane (the realm of ghosts, spirits, and shades). Attempting to return to the vampire&rsquo;s physical shell is a long and terrifying ordeal, especially since there is no guarantee that she will accomplish the journey successfully. This significant danger keeps many Kindred from leaving their bodies for long, but those who dare can learn much.</p>","details":"<p>Journeying in astral form requires the player to expend a point of Willpower and make a Perception + Awareness roll. Difficulty varies depending on the distance and complexity of the intended trip; 5 is within sight, 7 is nearby or to a familiar location, and 9 reflects a trip far from familiar territory (a first journey from North America to the Far East; trying to shortcut through the earth). The greater the number of successes rolled, the more focused the character&rsquo;s astral presence is, and the easier it is for her to reach her desired destination.<br><br>Failure means the character is unable to separate her consciousness from her body, while a botch can have nasty consequences &mdash; flinging her astral form to a random destination on Earth or in the spirit realm, arriving in a place where the sun is active (necessitating a frenzy roll, although the sunlight doesn&rsquo;t do any damage), or hurtling toward the desired destination so forcefully that the silver cord snaps.<br><br>The player may spend a point of Willpower to activate this power, and an additional point of Willpower to gain the success necessary to perform the jaunt. This is an exception to the normal rule where a player may not spend more than a single point of Willpower per turn.<br><br>Each scene in Psychic Projection requires another point of Willpower and a new roll. Failure indicates that the vampire has lost her way and must retrace the path of her silver cord. A botch at this stage means the cord snaps, stranding the character&rsquo;s psychic form in the mysterious astral plane.<br><br>An astral form may travel at great speeds (the Storyteller can use roughly 1000 miles per hour or 1500 kilometers per hour as a general guide) and carries no clothing or material objects of any kind. Some artifacts are said to exist in the spirit world, and the character can try to use one of these tools if she finds one. The character cannot bring such relics to the physical world when she returns to her body, however.<br><br>Interaction with the physical world is impossible while using Psychic Projection. At best, the character may spend a Willpower point to manifest as a ghostlike shape. This apparition lasts one turn before fading away; while she can&rsquo;t affect anything physically during this time, the character can speak. Despite lacking physical substance, an astral character can use Auspex normally. At the Storyteller&rsquo;s discretion, such a character may employ some or all Animalism, Dementation, Dominate, Necromancy, Obtenebration, Presence, Thaumaturgy, and similar non-corporeal powers she has, though this typically requires a minimum of three successes on the initial Psychic Projection roll.<br><br>If two astral shapes encounter one another, they interact as if they were solid. They may talk, touch, and even fight as if both were in the material world. Since they have no physical bodies, astral characters seeking to interact &ldquo;physically&rdquo; substitute Mental and Social Traits for Physical ones (Wits replaces Dexterity, Manipulation supplants Strength, and Intelligence replaces Stamina). Due to the lack of a material form, the only real way to damage another psychic entity is to cut its silver cord. When fighting this way, consider Willpower points to be health levels; when a combatant loses all of her Willpower, the cord is severed.<br><br>Although an astrally projected character remains in the reflection of the mortal world, she may venture further into the spirit realms, especially if she becomes lost. Other beings with particular sensitivity to psychic activity, such as ghosts, werewolves, and even some magi, travel the astral plane as well, and can interact with a vampire&rsquo;s psychic presence normally (although the astrally projected character is not considered a &ldquo;ghost&rdquo; for powers such as Necromancy). The observing character notices the astrally projecting vampire with a Perception + Awareness roll (difficulty 8), requiring more successes than the Psychic Projection activation roll. Even those who do notice you won&rsquo;t be able to identify you; you are merely an immaterial shade hovering in the general area. Storytellers are encouraged to make trips into the spirit world as bizarre, mysterious, and dreamlike as possible. The world beyond is a vivid and fantastic place, where the true nature of things is stronger and often strikingly different from their earthly appearances.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"perception","dice2":"awareness","bonus":0,"difficulty":"-1","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_oqqyfie3wor","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Auspex","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1668764159874,"modifiedTime":1674221157928,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"mnjVrWwmsnINEPDd","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Rising Star (3pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 489","description":"<p>You&rsquo;re one of the up-and-comers in the city, a rising star in your Sect. Everyone wants to know you and be your friend, even as those in power groom you for positions of greater responsibility. You are at -1 difficulty on all Social rolls against any vampires in your Sect who aren&rsquo;t actively opposing your ascent.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_tbkdk4lk1q","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674440158279,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"mpDGmHqfDJZg4WQu","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
