{"name":"Impatient (1pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 485","description":"<p>You have no patience for standing around and waiting. You want to do things now &mdash; fuck those slowpokes trying to hold you back. Every time you are forced to wait around instead of acting, a Self-Control roll is required to see if you go tearing off on your own instead.</p>","details":"<p>Mental</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vpU7tfPjRILQuAc4"},"cf":{"id":"temp_jwd9ok2vgth","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221101731,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"nmsGS5gboJQb2S7P","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●● Cold of the Grave","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 169","description":"<p>The dead feel no pain, though most undead do. With this ability, the character can temporarily take on the unfeeling semblance of the dead, in order to protect herself from physical and emotional harm. When assuming the Cold of the Grave, the vampire&rsquo;s skin becomes unusually cold. When she speaks, her breath mists even in warm air &mdash; those with exceptional senses might even see a slight red tinge to the breath.<br><br>The power brings a sense of lethargy over the character, as a mortal might feel under the influence of a mildly unpleasant disease. It becomes difficult to rouse oneself to action, and very little seems important enough to really worry about. A corpse has no worries, after all.</p>","details":"<p>The player spends one Willpower point. For the remainder of the scene, the character takes no wound penalties, and the player gains an additional die to all dice pools that involve resisting emotional manipulation, such as Intimidation or Empathy. However, the player also loses a die from dice pools to emotionally manipulate others. The character is a cold fish to those she interacts with, and they do not respond readily to her. The Cold of the Grave does not protect the character against the depredations of the Beast. She may be emotionally cold on the surface, but if others taunt and anger her sufficiently, she is still subject to frenzy as normal.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":0,"isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.wvvCBIDykkBenEtI"},"cf":{"id":"temp_reojxpqrhd","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Corpse in the Monster","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670842147642,"modifiedTime":1674221167929,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"nvFksDuHEvCOuejx","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Allies","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 111","description":"<p>Allies are mortals who support and help you &mdash; family, friends, or even a mortal organization that owes you some loyalty. Although allies aid you willingly, without coaxing or coercion, they are not always available to offer assistance; they have their own concerns and can do only so much for the sake of your relationship. However, they might have some useful Background Traits of their own, and could provide you with indirect access to their contacts, influence, or resources.&nbsp;<br><br>Allies are typically persons of influence and power in your home city. They can be of almost any sort, depending on what your Storyteller will allow. You may have friends in the precinct morgue, at a prominent blog, among the high society of local celebrities, or at a construction site. Your Allies might be a clan of nomads who move their mobile home camp around the area, or they might be a family of generations of police officers. You may even count the mayor himself among your friends, depending on how many dots you spend on this Trait. Your Allies are generally trustworthy (though they probably don&rsquo;t know that you&rsquo;re a vampire, or even that vampires exist). However, nothing comes for free. If you wind up drawing favors from your friend in the Cosa Nostra, he&rsquo;ll probably ask you to do him a favor in kind in the future. This often leads to the beginning of a story.&hellip;</p>","details":"<p>Allies may be pooled among a coterie of characters.</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 16.782%;\"><col style=\"width: 83.218%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>●</td>\n<td>One ally of moderate influence and&nbsp;power</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>●●</td>\n<td>Two allies, both of moderate power</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>●●●</td>\n<td>Three allies, one of whom is quite &nbsp;influential</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>●●●●</td>\n<td>Four allies, one of whom is very &nbsp;influential</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>●●●●●</td>\n<td>Five allies, one of whom is extremely &nbsp;influential</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"wod.types.background","level":"","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_14tdb2ntd4k","path":"Backgrounds","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1673844458648,"modifiedTime":1674221071046,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"nwGimUXbgg5kHDAw","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Consumption (5pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 239","description":"<p>There is something hungry inside of you. But what is it? Portions of the Antediluvian? Your Vicissitude gone horribly wrong? Whatever it is, it is active, acting like a cancer, devouring you from the inside out. Your very blood is wrought with corrosive, flesh-eating bacteria. At the beginning of each evening, you suffer one health level of lethal damage that cannot be soaked nor healed with blood. The only way to counteract the effect is by ingesting one-tenth of your body-weight in flesh to supplement your depleted carcass. Whether you kill and devour the skin from humans or raid the biohazard containers of liposuction clinics for siphoned fat, you need your ration of human flesh in order to survive. If you try and ingest this macabre meal before damage is done, you&rsquo;ll simply vomit it out like any other food &mdash; this does not impart the benefits of the Eat Food Merit.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_axvc3n7d0wg","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Tzimisce#/CF_SEP/Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221097971,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"o1VCXdXB5rYryd0p","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Addiction (3pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 481","description":"<p>You suffer from an addiction to a substance, which must now be present in the blood you drink (or you automatically frenzy, as per the Prey Exclusion Flaw). This can be alcohol, nicotine, hard drugs, or simply adrenaline. This substance always impairs you in some fashion (see &ldquo;Poisons and Drugs,&rdquo; p. 301, for particulars).</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_81150czgfr","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672365603221,"modifiedTime":1674221107350,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"o6v2QHLY80jL8SCv","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Deceptive Aura (1pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 493","description":"<p>Your aura is unnaturally bright and colorful for a vampire. You register as a mortal on all attempts to read your aura.</p>","details":"<p>Supernatural</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1a3wwhsmx3r","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674439880371,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"oJpM9rN1R51SpMKK","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Addictive Blood (3pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 67","description":"<p>You don&rsquo;t just peddle narcotics; through the blessings of the Dark God, you are the perfect drug. Your blood is especially delicious to others, Kindred or kine. Whoever tastes your blood must, during any subsequent scenes that they meet you, drink again or spend a Willpower point to avoid the pangs of craving. These cravings add +2 difficulty to any Mental or Social rolls. Setites with this Merit find it much easier to blood bond an opponent, as once they have tasted the tainted vitae, they will do almost anything to drink it again.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PVnibxS2iQHyYlwD"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8mau8cmb57t","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Followers of Set","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221082909,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"oKbD3YKdwxADb75S","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
