{"name":"●● Aura of Decay","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 175","description":"<p>The necromancer can strengthen the feeling of entropy around her to the point where it breaks down nonliving objects and machines. It can gnarl wood, rust metal, crack silicon chips, and erode plastic, glass, and dead organic material. This power has a range of one yard or meter from the necromancer&rsquo;s body, but all those in the presence of the vampire can feel her corruption as an icy wind.</p>","details":"<p>No roll is required, but this power does cost at least one blood point. Objects subjected to this Aura of Decay break down and become useless after being targeted. How the object gives out, as well as the exact mechanism of failure, is up to the Storyteller. Corrosion, metal fatigue, or sheer brittleness are all suitably likely for any given item&rsquo;s demise, but the in-game effect of using a doomed item is as if the owning character rolled a botch. The speed at which an item breaks down depends on how many blood points are spent.<br><br></p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 102px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 38.2456%;\"><col style=\"width: 61.5789%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\"><strong>Blood Spent</strong></td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\"><strong>Time to Break Down</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">One</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">One week</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">Two</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">One day</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">Three</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">End of scene</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">Four</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">Five turns</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">Five</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17px;\">One turn</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>Note that since this power requires the expenditure of blood points, a character cannot cause an Aura of Decay while staked.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":0,"isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.h3miymUUqu7RKygI"},"cf":{"id":"temp_wle9pw2x1y","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/Vitreous Path","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670842147642,"modifiedTime":1674221171040,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"od5p9X5cNdT43Ve0","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Sabbat Survivor (1pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 488","description":"<p>You&rsquo;ve lived through at least one Sabbat attack or attempted recruitment. Your experience helps you anticipate situations where you might potentially be endangered by the Sabbat once again. You are at -1 difficulty on all Perception rolls when it comes to Sabbat-based matters. This Merit is generally taken by groups in conflict with the Sabbat, and comes into play most frequently as a means of avoiding ambushes.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1a3wwhsmx3r","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674439883179,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"omEcDoHlUBfcMlLD","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Stake","type":"Melee Weapon","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/meleeweapons.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 280","description":"May paralyze a vampire if driven through the heart. The attacker must target the heart\n(difficulty 9) and score three damage successes.","details":"","isequipped":false,"ismagical":false,"isweapon":false,"attack":{"attribute":"strength","ability":"melee","secondaryabilityid":"","accuracy":0,"isrollable":true},"damage":{"attribute":"strength","bonus":1,"type":"lethal","isrollable":true},"difficulty":"9","conceal":"T","istwohanded":false,"isnatural":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tyg371ggunf","path":"Items#/CF_SEP/Melee Weapons","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674289833148,"modifiedTime":1674440438440,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"ormE1YIoQ25priU3","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"SMG, Large (3-Round Burst)","type":"Ranged Weapon","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/rangedweapons.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 281","description":"Three-Round Burst: The attacker gains two additional dice on a single attack roll, and expends three shots from the weapon’s clip. Only certain weapons may perform this maneuver; see the Ranged Weapons Chart for particulars. Attacks are made at +1 difficulty due to recoil. As with automatic fire, the damage dice pool is based on one bullet from the weapon in question.","details":"","isequipped":false,"ismagical":false,"isweapon":false,"attack":{"attribute":"dexterity","ability":"firearms","secondaryabilityid":"","accuracy":2,"isrollable":true},"damage":{"attribute":"","bonus":4,"type":"lethal","isrollable":true},"difficulty":"7","conceal":"T","istwohanded":false,"range":50,"rate":3,"mode":{"hasreload":false,"hasburst":true,"hasfullauto":false,"hasspray":false},"clip":{"value":0,"max":30}},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6yghfiu9569","path":"Items#/CF_SEP/Ranged Weapons","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674287371409,"modifiedTime":1674440442096,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"osLRtgpTBKBOIoJz","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Pain Tolerance (2pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 238","description":"<p>Maybe you are a badass or shut off your nerves through Vicissitude. Maybe your sire put you through so many intricate hells that it would be tough for anyone else to compete. Maybe it just turns you on. Regardless, at Hurt or Injured, you suffer no wound penalties, though you still suffer full penalties at Wounded and below. You must have a Conviction or Courage rating of 3 or more to take this Merit.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_g4msmdkn9lw","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Tzimisce#/CF_SEP/Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221099165,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"ozii58GXqP6a6FsJ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Clan Friendship (4pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 489","description":"<p>One particular Clan (not your own) has a special liking for you. You might have done the Clan as a whole a favor at some point, or perhaps you&rsquo;re just a loud voice in support of their aims. Whatever the case, you&rsquo;re at -2 difficulty on all friendly Social rolls involving members of the Clan in question. Of course, the reaction your cozy relationship with another Clan is likely to draw from your own Clan leaders is an entirely different can of worms.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_02lw4m6r7kvf","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/4 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674439934419,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"pDKi4eowKspANzPZ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Blush of Health (2pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 480","description":"<p>You look more hale and healthy in appearance than other vampires, allowing you to blend with human society much more easily. You still retain the color of a living mortal, and your skin feels only slightly cool to the touch.</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_644ptrzk5eq","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/2 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672364948802,"modifiedTime":1674439884134,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"pDq9tjcpq8y48E7a","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Shaft of Belated Quiescence","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 237","description":"<p>This ritual turns an ordinary stake of rowan wood into a particularly vicious weapon. When the stake penetrates a vampire&rsquo;s body, the tip breaks off and begins working its way through the victim&rsquo;s flesh to his heart. The trip may take several minutes or several nights, depending on where the stake struck. The stake eludes attempts to dig it out, burrowing farther into the victim&rsquo;s body to escape surgery. The only Kindred who are immune to this internal attack are those who have had their hearts removed by Serpentis.</p>","details":"<p>The ritual takes five hours to enact, minus 30 minutes per success. The stake must be carved of rowan wood, coated with three blood points of the caster&rsquo;s blood, and blackened in an oak-wood fire. When the ritual is complete, the stake is enchanted to act as described above.<br><br>An attack with a Shaft of Belated Quiescence is performed as with a normal stake: a Dexterity + Melee roll (difficulty 6, modified as per the normal combat rules; the attack does not need to specifically target the heart) with a lethal damage rating of Strength + 1. If at least one health level of damage is inflicted after the target rolls to soak, the tip of the stake breaks off and begins burrowing. If not, the stake may be used to make subsequent attacks until it strikes deep enough to activate.<br><br>Once the tip of the stake is in the victim&rsquo;s body, the Storyteller begins an extended roll of the caster&rsquo;s Thaumaturgy rating (difficulty 9), rolling once per hour of game time. Successes on this roll are added to the successes scored in the initial attack. This represents the tip&rsquo;s progress toward the victim&rsquo;s heart. A botch indicates that the tip has struck a bone and all accumulated successes are lost (including those from the initial attack roll). Removing the part of the body where the tip impacted (such as a Tzimisce turning into blood or a vampire cutting off their arm) may stop the tip&rsquo;s progress, depending on the number of successes acquired and the Storyteller&rsquo;s discretion. When the shaft accumulates a total of 15 successes, it reaches the victim&rsquo;s heart. This paralyzes Kindred and is instantly fatal to mortals and ghouls.<br><br>Attempts to surgically remove the tip of the shaft can be made with an extended Dexterity + Medicine roll made once per hour (difficulty 7 for Kindred and 8 for mortals). The surgeon must accumulate a number of successes equal to those currently held by the shaft in order to remove the tip. Once surgery begins, however, the shaft begins actively evading the surgeon&rsquo;s probes, and its rolls are made once every 30 minutes for the duration of the surgery attempt. Each individual surgery roll that scores less than three successes inflicts an additional unsoakable level of lethal damage on the patient.<br><br>Shaft of Belated Quiescence may be performed on other wooden impaling weapons, such as spears, arrows, practice swords, and pool cues, provided that they are made of rowan wood. It may not, however, create a Bullet of Belated Quiescence.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"6","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SOFUQHVyXwWb4xVU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ux26or4j83","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 3 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671081485306,"modifiedTime":1674439753386,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"pE3uFyWPrzTu42DP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Bound (2pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 490","description":"<p>You are blood bound to another vampire. Your regnant may not necessarily treat you badly, but the fact remains that your will is not entirely your own. The knowledge gnaws at you, even as you find yourself lost in devotion to your vampiric master. Sabbat vampires cannot take this Flaw.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2wewy46vpbx","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/2 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221104409,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"pLq8VOMqGsqd7JyK","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Sleep Unseen (2pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 161","description":"<p>The power of Obfuscate usually requires you to concentrate at least a little. However, you are able to lock the power on, allowing you to sleep while remaining hidden. To do so requires the expenditure of another blood point, but it will last throughout the day&rsquo;s rest. Those with Auspex can still attempt to detect you, but mortals will be unaware of your sanctuary. This can be a useful trick for Kindred who like to travel.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.49Hb9rly0U2SqDLY"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2xwet9zo2o","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Nosferatu#/CF_SEP/Merit","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221091507,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"pPXpDmSlun46cfF1","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Long-Term Planning (4pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 123","description":"<p>You never leave anything to chance; every action is a carefully considered stratagem. Once per session you may declare an action you are about to take is actually &ldquo;all part of your plan&rdquo; and reduce its difficulty by two points. The Storyteller may veto the use of this ability on particular rolls. The player and Storyteller should keep a note of each of these occasions and decide how they are linking together into a grand scheme.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.BonXhY7P5YxFV8YT"},"cf":{"id":"temp_gevrsr5xe9","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Lasombra","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221086978,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"pnPm68GRH8JtcekG","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Widow's Spite","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 232","description":"<p>This ritual causes a pain, itch, or other significant (but not deadly) sensation in the subject. Similar in effect to legendary &ldquo;voodoo doll&rdquo; effects, this ritual is used more out of scorn or malice than actual enmity. In fact, it requires a wax or cloth doll that resembles the target, which bleeds when the power takes effect.</p>","details":"<p>The ceremonial doll must resemble, however rudely, the victim of the ritual. It produces no mechanical effect, other than a simple physical stimulus. The caster may determine where on the subject&rsquo;s body the pain or itch appears.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"4","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_q5ajxrpsb3","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 1 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671081485306,"modifiedTime":1674439750920,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"po4hGv0sb6INhMPL","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Magic Resistance (2pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 493","description":"<p>You have an inherent resistance to the rituals of the Tremere and the spells of the mages of other Clans. The difficulty of all such magic, both malicious and beneficent, is two higher when directed at you. You may never learn magical Disciplines such as Thaumaturgy and Necromancy.</p>","details":"<p>Supernatural</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_644ptrzk5eq","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/2 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674439884887,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"q34Dr0esijZgWcQP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Bind the Accusing Tongue","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 230","description":"<p>This ancient ritual is said to have been one of the first developed by the Tremere and a primary reason for the lack of cohesive opposition to their expansion. Bind the Accusing Tongue lays a compulsion upon the subject that prevents him from speaking ill of the caster, allowing the thaumaturge to commit literally unspeakable acts without fear of reprisal.</p>","details":"<p>The caster must have a picture or other image or effigy of the ritual&rsquo;s target, a lock of the target&lsquo;s hair, and a black silken cord. The caster winds the cord around the hair and image while intoning the ritual&rsquo;s vocal component. Once the ritual is complete, the target must score more successes on a Willpower roll (difficulty of the caster&lsquo;s Thaumaturgy rating + 3) than the caster scored in order to say anything negative about the caster. The ritual lasts until the target succeeds at this roll or the silk cord is unwound, at which point the image and the lock of hair crumble to dust.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"4","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_q5ajxrpsb3","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 1 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671081485306,"modifiedTime":1674439749746,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"qEOlnRfxRy0TUPYt","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"Feature","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6fvqbb4wn0f","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Sepulchre Path","color":"#000000","name":"The Sepulchre Path","children":[],"folderPath":["temp_444y5utucrj","temp_9pmdboh96h5","temp_odkmoq9z4sc"],"fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":null,"sorting":"a","contents":["kBHS9H9pK7TlpEsW","nXnGVQp7SgSH6e1u","uFFy6rUHLIUtM0OU","G71vCWBPHOw5Wy4g","ALEXxE8YMwfZBpb4","kDPkbKXedWaSixl1"],"version":"2.5.6"}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"iscreated":false,"version":"","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"","description":"","details":"","type":"","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674221170479,"modifiedTime":1674221170821,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"qeOpZU7DgwLSflXw"}
{"name":"Additional Discipline (5 pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 494","description":"<p>You can take one additional Discipline (Storyteller discretion) as if it were a Clan Discipline. All costs to learn that Discipline are paid out as if it were native to your Clan. A character cannot take this Merit more than once, and Caitiff vampires cannot take this Merit.</p>","details":"<p>Supernatural</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8gnmcy3mqaj","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/5 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674439988828,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"qmbMqV7pQDbFBhsK","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Former Ghoul (1pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 487","description":"<p>You were introduced to the Blood long before you were made Kindred. Your long experience as a ghoul gives you insight into and comfort with vampiric society. You are at -1 difficulty on all Social rolls when in the presence of other neonates (particularly those who haven&rsquo;t been educated by their sires), and have a -1 difficulty on all rolls relating to vampiric knowledge.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_1a3wwhsmx3r","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674439881134,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"r2r0WUTcPxMdWLXy","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●●  Possession","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 155","description":"<p>At this level of Dominate, the force of the Kindred&rsquo;s psyche is such that it can utterly supplant the mind of a mortal subject. Speaking isn&rsquo;t required, but the vampire must capture the victim&rsquo;s gaze. During the psychic struggle, the contestants&rsquo; eyes are locked on one another.<br><br>Once the Kindred overwhelms the subject&rsquo;s mind, the vampire moves his consciousness into the victim&rsquo;s body and controls it as easily as he uses his own. The mortal falls into a mental fugue while under possession. She is aware of events only in a distorted, dreamlike fashion. In turn, the vampire&rsquo;s mind focuses entirely on controlling his mortal subject. His own body lies in a torpid state, defenseless against any actions made toward it.<br><br>Vampires cannot possess one another in this fashion, as even the weakest Kindred&rsquo;s mind is strong enough to resist such straightforward mental dominance. Only through a blood bond can one vampire control another to this degree. Supernatural creatures also cannot be possessed in this way, although ghouls that have drunk from the vampire using Possession can.</p>","details":"<p>The vampire must completely strip away the target&rsquo;s Willpower prior to possessing her. The player spends a Willpower point, then rolls Charisma + Intimidation, while the subject rolls his Willpower in a resisted action (difficulty 7 for each). For each success the vampire obtains over the victim&rsquo;s total, the target loses a point of temporary Willpower. Only if the attacker botches can the subject escape her fate, since this makes the target immune to any further Dominate attempts by that vampire for the rest of the story.<br><br>Once the target loses all her temporary Willpower, her mind is open. The vampire rolls Manipulation + Intimidation (difficulty 7) to determine how fully he assumes control of the mortal shell. Similar to the Animalism power Subsume the Spirit, multiple successes allow the character to utilize some mental Disciplines, noted on the chart below. (Vampires possessing ghouls can use the physical Disciplines the ghoul possesses, but not the mental ones.)<br><br></p>\n<table border=\"1\"><colgroup><col><col></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Successes</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1 Success</td>\n<td>Cannot use Disciplines</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2 Successes</td>\n<td>Can use Auspex and other sensory<br>powers</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3 Successes</td>\n<td>Can also use Presence and other<br>powers of emotional manipulation</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4 Successes</td>\n<td>Can also use Dementation,<br>Dominate, and other powers<br>of mental manipulation</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5 Successes</td>\n<td>Can also use Chimerstry,<br>Necromancy, Thaumaturgy,<br>and other mystical powers</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>The character may travel as far from his body as he is physically able while possessing the mortal. The vampire may also venture out during the day in the mortal form. However, the vampire&rsquo;s own body must be awake to do so, requiring a successful roll to remain awake (see p. 262). If the vampire leaves the mortal shell (by choice, if his body falls asleep, through supernatural expulsion, after sustaining significant injury, etc.), his consciousness returns to his physical form in an instant.<br><br>Once freed from possession, the mortal regains mental control of herself. This can happen in an instant, or the victim may lie comatose for days while her psyche copes with the violation.<br><br>The vampire experiences everything the mortal body feels during possession, from pleasure to pain. In fact, any damage the victim&rsquo;s body sustains is also applied to the character&rsquo;s body (though the Kindred may soak as normal). If the mortal dies before the vampire&rsquo;s soul can flee from the body, the character&rsquo;s body falls into torpor. Presumably this is in sympathetic response to the massive trauma of death, though some Kindred believe that the vampire&rsquo;s soul is cast adrift during this time and must find its way back to the body.<br><br>The Kindred can remain in the mortal&rsquo;s body even if his own torpid form is destroyed, though such a pathetic creature is not likely to exist for long. At each sunrise, the vampire must roll Courage (difficulty 8) or be expelled from the body. If forced from the mortal body, the vampire tumbles into the astral plane, his soul permanently lost in the spirit world. A vampire trapped in a mortal body may not be &ldquo;re-Embraced.&rdquo; If the Embrace occurs to such a creature, he simply meets Final Death.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"charisma","dice2":"intimidation","bonus":0,"difficulty":"7","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4wvty5nf9hd","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Dominate","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670227736590,"modifiedTime":1674221161710,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"rG958Qv987D6NwR1","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Thaumaturgical Countermagic","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/mainpower_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 228","description":"<p>This is less of a path than it is a separate Discipline, as the power to resist Thaumaturgy can be taught independently of Thaumaturgy, even to those Kindred who are incapable of mastering the simplest ritual. Though the techniques of Thaumaturgical Countermagic are not officially taught outside Clan Tremere, unofficial methods are likely to exist. Any non-Tremere who displays the ability to resist Thaumaturgy quickly becomes the subject of potentially fatal scrutiny from the entirety of Clan Tremere.</p>","details":"<p>Thaumaturgical Countermagic is treated as a separate Discipline, although it uses the usual rules for Thaumaturgy (including experience costs and the fact that it is limited to only five levels). It cannot be taken as a character&rsquo;s primary path, and a rating in it does not allow the character to perform rituals.<br><br>The use of Thaumaturgical Countermagic is treated as a free action in combat and does not require a split dice pool. To oppose a Thaumaturgy power or ritual, a character must have a Thaumaturgical Countermagic rating equal to or greater than the rating of that power or ritual. The player spends a blood point and rolls the number of dice indicated by the character&rsquo;s Thaumaturgical Countermagic rating (difficulty equal to the difficulty of the power in use). Each success cancels one of the opposing thaumaturge&rsquo;s successes.<br><br>Thaumaturgical Countermagic is only at full effectiveness when used against Thaumaturgy. It works with halved dice pools against Necromancy and other mystical Disciplines, and is completely ineffective against non-vampiric magics and powers.<br><br>Thaumaturgical Countermagic can be learned by characters who are unable to learn Thaumaturgy (e.g., those with the Merit Magic Resistance). Any non-Tremere character with a rating in this power automatically gains the Flaw Clan Enmity (Tremere), receiving no freebie points for it. This power cannot be taken during character creation and cannot be spontaneously developed. Whether the character has Thaumaturgy as an in-Clan power or not, it costs the same as any other non-Clan Discipline to learn.<br><br></p>\n<table border=\"1\"><colgroup><col><col></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>&bull;</td>\n<td>Two dice of countermagic. The character can attempt to cancel only those powers and rituals that directly affect him, his garments, and objects on his person.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&bull;&bull;</td>\n<td>Four dice of countermagic.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&bull;&bull;&bull;</td>\n<td>Six dice of countermagic. The character can attempt to cancel a Thaumaturgy power that affects anyone or anything in physical contact with him.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&bull;&bull;&bull;&bull;</td>\n<td>Eight dice of countermagic.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&bull;&bull;&bull;&bull;&bull;</td>\n<td>Ten dice of countermagic. The character can now attempt to cancel a power or ritual that targets anything within a radius equal to his Willpower in yards or meters, or one that is being used or performed within that same radius.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"wod.types.discipline","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"-1","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.RrV8F2Uee4MMSwwn"},"cf":{"id":"temp_zl2ebio1fjp","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgical Countermagic","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439740274,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"rONLEBJNR8uO4Oym","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Mistaken Identity (1pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 490","description":"<p>You look similar to descriptions of another Kindred, which cause cases of mistaken identity. This can prompt numerous awkward or even dangerous situations, especially if your &ldquo;twin&rdquo; has a terrible reputation or is wanted for some crime.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_jwd9ok2vgth","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221102035,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"rRdXwDHMlWwdHyGp","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Soft-Hearted (1pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 485","description":"<p>You cannot stand to watch others suffer. You avoid any situation that involves causing someone physical or emotional pain, unless you make a Willpower roll (difficulty 8). You must have a Humanity rating of 7 or above to take this Flaw &mdash; vampires on Paths of Enlightenment can only take this Flaw with Storyteller approval.</p>","details":"<p>Mental</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vpU7tfPjRILQuAc4"},"cf":{"id":"temp_jwd9ok2vgth","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221103121,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"rYrgXy18f610sRUg","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Boon (1-6pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 488","description":"<p>Someone owes you a favor. The vampire in your debt might be the lowliest neonate in the city or might be the Prince herself; it all depends on how many points the Merit costs. You only have that single favor owed you (unless you take the Merit multiple times), so using it properly is of paramount importance. Depending on status and other factors, the vampire who owes you a favor may well resent his debt, and might go out of his way to &ldquo;settle&rdquo; it early &mdash; even going so far as to create situations from which he must &ldquo;rescue&rdquo; you and thus clear the slate.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_qs8e891clo","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/Multi-pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674440017253,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"raxWhbPFNHgk8lXu","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●● Cauldron of Blood","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 214","description":"<p>A thaumaturge using this power boils her subject&rsquo;s blood in his veins like water on a stove. The Kindred must touch her subject, and it is this contact that simmers the subject&rsquo;s blood. This power is always fatal to mortals, and causes great damage to even the mightiest vampires.</p>","details":"<p>The number of successes gained determines how many blood points are brought to boil. The subject suffers one health level of aggravated damage for each point boiled (individuals with Fortitude may soak this damage using only their Fortitude dice). A single success kills any mortal, though some ghouls with access to Fortitude are said to have survived after soaking all of the aggravated damage.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"8","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_v3rmtx67pm","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Blood","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670930910577,"modifiedTime":1674439742870,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"rcGU7pKl1SbcIDWY","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Vengeful (2pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 486","description":"<p>You have a score to settle, incurred either during your mortal days or after the Embrace. You are obsessed with taking your revenge on an individual or group, and it is your overriding priority in any situation where you encounter the object of your revenge. You may temporarily resist your need for vengeance by spending a Willpower point.</p>","details":"<p>Mental</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vuUhXjpBnaswkR2e"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2wewy46vpbx","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/2 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221106659,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"rih1HRrgAXhvmLsa","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"The Grave's Decay","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/mainpower_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 171","description":"<p>This path is derived from the observation of the working of time on all things mortal. Stone crumbles and the corpse rots away to nothing, a process of endless fascination to the lost Cainites known as Cappadocians. Indeed, for the undying, the process of decay is a fascinating disease that afflicts everyone and everything save them. Under this path, a practitioner of Necromancy channels that force.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.disciplinepath","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":0,"isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.MUktEl9CqDxIAKM7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_29xrm8dfvtq","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Grave's Decay","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670841064343,"modifiedTime":1674221169328,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"rj9UWT3YpnDLROxg","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"Feature","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_kwv40m9392i","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/5 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000","name":"5 pt. Flaws","children":[],"folderPath":["temp_zbxadbcq32d","temp_hv8df9kilvf"],"fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":null,"sorting":"a","contents":["nH01pbPqbAXDaz9s","fkSw9LD0ovMd3U5m","2exDK3mkHtpVc5C6","RsJaB5ZARpJDPNtL","Ec0GcYdwg7VlXk0L"],"version":"2.5.6"}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"iscreated":false,"version":"","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"","description":"","details":"","type":"","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674221112111,"modifiedTime":1674221112417,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"rpysUfAEgGTFbA21"}
{"name":"False Reflection (3pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 161","description":"<p>Even when using their Obfuscate abilities, Nosferatu still show up in their true form when noticed by machines, such as cameras or video surveillance. With this ability, the Nosferatu can extend their power to recorded images and media. However, as with Mask of the Thousand Faces, the original image isn&rsquo;t actually changed; it is just that people see it the way the Nosferatu wants it seen. Unfortunately, computers are not so easily fooled: if the image is used for facial recognition software (for instance), the computer will see the Nosferatu&rsquo;s real face and fail to find a match. The Nosferatu has best take care how this power is used, as it may wear off in time. Some archived photos have given librarians a nasty surprise, years after going into storage.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.49Hb9rly0U2SqDLY"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2xwet9zo2o","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Nosferatu#/CF_SEP/Merit","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221090726,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"rqqBVcIuAFQ8ZzsO","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Uppity (2pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 491","description":"<p>You are proud of your new status in the Sect &mdash; so proud that you&rsquo;ve shot your mouth off to other Kindred and made some enemies. Wiser vampires laugh at you and chalk your rudeness up to youth, but others find you arrogant and insulting. These enemies will take action to embarrass or harm you. Furthermore, you are at +2 difficulty on all Social rolls against any vampires you have alienated through your yammering &mdash; and you may not know who they are.<br><br>At Storyteller discretion, you may also be required to make a Willpower roll (difficulty 6) to keep your mouth shut any time the opportunity presents itself for<br>you to brag about your pack, your Clan, or your status.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2wewy46vpbx","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/2 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221106562,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"rwvhWOJr0vFpHguE","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Victim of the Masquerade (2pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 486","description":"<p>The Camarilla&rsquo;s propaganda machine did too good a job on you. Even after your Embrace you refused to believe you were a vampire. You remain convinced that there is some logical explanation for your condition, and spend as much time as you can searching for it. You also have problems feeding, and may insist on trying to eat regular food. None of these habits makes you particularly pleasant company for other Kindred. This Flaw must be roleplayed at all times, and is generally taken by Camarilla vampires.</p>","details":"<p>Mental</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vuUhXjpBnaswkR2e"},"cf":{"id":"temp_2wewy46vpbx","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/2 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221106757,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"rxcRkgFWJijGccq0","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Calm Heart (3pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 485","description":"<p>You are naturally calm and do not easily fly off the handle. You receive two extra dice when attempting to resist a frenzy. Brujah may not take this Merit.</p>","details":"<p>Mental</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_tbkdk4lk1q","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672390956649,"modifiedTime":1674440156283,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"ry5dLpQH14whw2cH","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"● Heightened Senses","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 134","description":"<p>This power increases the acuity of all of the vampire&rsquo;s senses, effectively doubling the clarity and range of sight, hearing, and smell. While her senses of taste and touch extend no farther than normal, they likewise become far more distinct; the vampire could taste the hint of liquor in a victim&rsquo;s blood or feel the give of the board concealing a hollow space in the floor. The Kindred may magnify her senses at will, sustaining this heightened focus for as long as she desires. At the Storyteller&rsquo;s option, this may make hunting easier.<br><br>Occasionally, this talent provides extrasensory or even precognitive insights. These brief, unfocused glimpses may be odd premonitions, flashes of empathy, or eerie feelings of foreboding. The vampire has no control over these perceptions, but with practice can learn to interpret them with a fair degree of accuracy.<br><br>Expanded senses come at a price, however. Bright lights, loud noises and strong smells present a hazard while the vampire uses this power. In addition to the possibility for distraction, an especially sudden or potent stimulus (like the glare of a spotlight or a clap of thunder) can blind or deafen the Kindred for an hour or more.</p>","details":"<p>It takes a reflexive action to activate this ability, but no roll or other cost is required. In certain circumstances, dice rolls associated with using the character&rsquo;s sense (such as Perception + Alertness) decrease in difficulty by a number equal to the character&rsquo;s Auspex rating when the power is engaged.<br><br>The Storyteller may also use this power to see if the character perceives a threat. In this case, the Storyteller privately rolls the character&rsquo;s unmodified Auspex rating, applying whatever difficulty he feels best suits the circumstances. For example, sensing that a pistol is pointed at the back of the character&rsquo;s head may require a roll of difficulty 5, while the sudden realization that a rival for Primogen is planning her assassination may require a 9. Note that even this &ldquo;precognition&rdquo; comes only as a result of interpreting details the Kindred is able to notice. It&rsquo;s not an all-purpose insight or miraculous revelation.<br><br>At the character&rsquo;s discretion, she may selectively heighten one specific sense, rather than leaving them all on. In these cases, the difficulty to perceive stimuli using that sense drops by one, but the difficulty to avoid distraction or temporary bedazzlement increases by one.<br><br>This power does not let characters see in pitch darkness, as does Eyes of the Beast (p. 199), but it does reduce difficulty penalties to act in such darkness from +2 to +1, and the character may make ranged attacks in pitch darkness if she can hear, smell, or otherwise detect her foe.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_oqqyfie3wor","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Auspex","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1668764159874,"modifiedTime":1674221157526,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"s0kwpgoWU2AEYbN6","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Former Prince (3pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 492","description":"<p>Once, you held near-absolute power in a city, but those nights are gone now. Perhaps you stepped down, perhaps you were deposed, or perhaps your city fell to the Sabbat; it matters little in your reduced state. What does matter is that the Prince in the city where you now dwell is aware of your prior employment, and has concerns that you might be trying to make a comeback. The machinery of the Camarilla in the city where you now make your home is subtly stacked against you, and if the Prince sees an opportunity to get rid of you he just might take it. This Flaw can only be taken by Camarilla vampires.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_81150czgfr","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221107843,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"s1FQODFajA6ZVp1i","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"King or Queen of Shadow (4pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 122","description":"<p>It is hard to hold onto your Humanity within the Sabbat, or even simply as a vampire. Your ability to empathize with the kine makes it more difficult. However, you have found a way to draw strength from that empathy. Any degeneration checks you make while on Path of Humanity reduce their difficulty by two.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.BonXhY7P5YxFV8YT"},"cf":{"id":"temp_gevrsr5xe9","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Lasombra","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221086878,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"s4iUA8C8pVF3TF8C","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
