{"name":"Broken Bond (4pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 489","description":"<p>You were once blood-bound but have secretly slipped the leash, and you are free to act as you will once more. Your regnant has no idea that you are not in fact bound, and continues to treat you as if you were. At Storyteller discretion, the experience of having been bound once may render you immune to ever being enthralled again. Sabbat vampires cannot take this Merit.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_02lw4m6r7kvf","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/4 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674439934320,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"sPdQQ9EBJUdzzN0I","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Eyes of Shadow (1-4pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 121","description":"<p>There is something about your eyes that makes you look dark and dangerous. Making eye contact with you is like staring into the Abyss. It may not be obvious why, but anyone you talk to gets a chill when they meet your gaze. The difficulty for any Intimidation roll is reduced by the number of points in this Merit (to a minimum of 2).</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.BonXhY7P5YxFV8YT"},"cf":{"id":"temp_gevrsr5xe9","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Lasombra","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221086589,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"sQmjuaM2giErWzKn","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●● Strike True","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 224","description":"<p>The vampire makes a single attack, guided by the unholy power of her Blood. This attack strikes its foe infallibly.</p>","details":"<p>By invoking this power, the player need not roll to see if the vampire&rsquo;s attack hits &mdash; it does, automatically. Only Melee or Brawl attacks may be made in this manner. These attacks are considered to be one-success attacks; they offer no additional damage dice. Also, they may be dodged, blocked, or parried normally, and the defender needs only one success (as the attacks&rsquo; number of success is assumed to be one). Strike True has no effect if attempted on multiple attacks (dice pool splits) in a single turn from one character.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"5","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.xs9y10bdAQRkgcNU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4yk16ojy6jl","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Mars","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439745664,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"sUWHH5LxUb2VqwOf","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Incoherent (5pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 163","description":"<p>Human speech is impossible for you. It might be that your mouth is too misshapen after the Embrace, or that years of living in the sewers have made you forget how to communicate. While you can understand what is being said to you, you cannot respond. Telepathy works on you as normal, and you have no problem communicating with animals, but human speech is barred to you.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vHJSI1w1uvu5im25"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ak5eyy1egoa","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Nosferatu#/CF_SEP/Flaw","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221089838,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"sjkTuLeB4vI5oPJt","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Hidden Diablerie (3pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 493","description":"<p>The tell-tale black streaks of diablerie do not manifest in your aura.</p>","details":"<p>Supernatural</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_tbkdk4lk1q","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674440157056,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"snjl1rTyHKzHay4p","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●● Wooden Tongues","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 214","description":"<p>A vampire may speak, albeit in limited fashion, with the spirit of any inanimate object. The conversation may not be incredibly interesting, as most rocks and chairs have limited concern for what occurs around them, but the vampire can get at least a general impression of what the subject has &ldquo;experienced.&rdquo; Note that events which are significant to a vampire may not be the same events that interest a lawn gnome.</p>","details":"<p>The number of successes dictates the amount and relevance of the information that the character receives. One success may yield a boulder&rsquo;s memory of a forest fire, while three may indicate that it remembers a shadowy figure running past, and five will cause the rock to relate a precise description of a local Gangrel.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"5","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_jxq3k0gu1p","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/Elemental Mastery","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439736606,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"sns9VLeyNJrRBz0M","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Glowing Eyes (3pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 481","description":"<p>You have the stereotypical glowing eyes of vampire legend, which gives you a -1 difficulty on Intimidation rolls when you&rsquo;re dealing with mortals. However, the tradeoffs are many; you must constantly disguise your condition (no, contacts don&rsquo;t cut it); the glow impairs your vision and puts you at +1 difficulty on all sightbased rolls (including the use of ranged weapons); and the radiance emanating from your eye sockets makes it difficult to hide (+2 difficulty to Stealth rolls) in the dark.</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_81150czgfr","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672365603221,"modifiedTime":1674221107941,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"ssljhPJTUEvdikCl","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Neptune's Might","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/mainpower_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 218","description":"<p>Vampires are rarely associated with the ocean in most mythologies, and most Kindred have nothing to do with water in large quantities simply because they have no reason to do so. Nevertheless, Neptune&rsquo;s Might has enjoyed a small, but devoted, following for centuries among Camarilla thaumaturges. This path is based primarily around the manipulation of standing water, although some of its more disturbing effects depart from this principle.<br><br>Once a character reaches the third level of Neptune&rsquo;s Might, the player may choose to specialize in either fresh water or salt water. Such specialization lowers all Neptune&rsquo;s Might difficulties by one when dealing with the chosen medium but raises them by one when dealing with the opposite. Blood is considered neither fresh nor salty for this purpose, and difficulties in manipulating it are unaffected.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.disciplinepath","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":0,"isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_8yl7px52c34","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/Neptune's Might","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671009392920,"modifiedTime":1674439739658,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"sw0R6AzpLyBNlclK","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●●  Horrid Reality","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 145","description":"<p>Rather than create simple illusions, the vampire can now project hallucinations directly into a victim&rsquo;s mind. The target of these illusions believes completely that the images are real; a hallucinatory fire can burn him, an imaginary noose can strangle him, and an illusory wall can block him. This power affects only one person at a time; though others can see the illusion, it doesn&rsquo;t impact them in the same way. Other people can try to convince the victim that his terrors are not real, but he won&rsquo;t believe them. Note that targets with enough dots in Auspex can still attempt to roll for Seeing the Unseen (p. 142).</p>","details":"<p>A Horrid Realty illusion costs two Willpower points to set in motion and lasts for an entire scene (though its effects may last longer; see below). If the vampire is trying to injure his victim, his player must roll Manipulation + Subterfuge (difficulty of the victim&rsquo;s Perception + Self-Control/Instinct). Each success inflicts one health level of lethal damage on the victim that cannot be soaked &mdash; the Cainite assaults the victim&rsquo;s mind and perceptions, not his body. If the player wishes to inflict less damage or change it to bashing, he may announce a maximum amount of damage before rolling the dice. Secondary effects (such as frenzy rolls for illusory fire) may also occur.<br><br>The victim heals all his damage instantaneously if he can be convinced that the damage he took was illusory, but convincing him may take some doing, such as with at least two successes on a Charisma + Empathy roll (difficulty equal to the Manipulation + Subterfuge of the Cainite using Horrid Reality). The target must be convinced of the attack&rsquo;s illusory nature within 24 hours of its taking place, or it becomes too well established in his memory, and he will have to heal the damage using blood (if a vampire) or over time (if mortal).<br><br>This power cannot actually kill its victims (though a target with a heart condition may well die from fright). A victim &ldquo;killed&rdquo; by an illusory attack loses consciousness or enters torpor.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"manipulation","dice2":"subterfuge","bonus":0,"difficulty":"-1","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_jgyzexzzmb","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Chimerstry","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670226749831,"modifiedTime":1674221159436,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"sxo1dROxtMyyZnQ1","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●● Mask of a Thousand Faces","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 185","description":"<p>The vampire can influence the perception of others, causing them to see a face different from his. Although the Kindred&rsquo;s physical form does not change, any observer who cannot sense the truth sees whomever the vampire wishes her to see.<br><br>The vampire must have a firm idea of the visage he wishes to project. The primary decision is whether to create an imaginary face or to superimpose the features of another person. Manufactured features are often more difficult to compose in believable proportions, but such a disguise is easier to maintain than having to impersonate someone else. Of course, things get simpler if the Kindred borrows the face but doesn&rsquo;t bother with the personality.</p>","details":"<p>The player rolls Manipulation + Performance (difficulty 7) to determine how well the disguise works. If the character tries to impersonate someone, he must get a good look at the subject before putting on the mask. The Storyteller may raise the difficulty if the character catches only a glimpse. The chart below lists the degrees of success in manufacturing another appearance. Vampires wishing to mask themselves as a person more attractive than they are must pay additional blood points equal to the difference between the vampire&rsquo;s Appearance rating and the Appearance of the mask (which means that younger vampires may need to take longer in order to spend the blood necessary).<br><br></p>\n<table border=\"1\"><colgroup><col><col></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Successes</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1 Success</td>\n<td>The vampire retains the same height and build, with a few slight alterations to his basic features. Nosferatu can appear as normal, albeit ugly, mortals.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2 Successes</td>\n<td>He looks unlike himself; people don&rsquo;t easily recognize him or agree about his appearance.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3 Successes</td>\n<td>He looks the way he wants to appear.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4 Successes</td>\n<td>Complete transformation, including gestures, mannerisms, appearance, and voice.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5 Successes</td>\n<td>Profound alteration (appear as the opposite sex, a vastly different age, or an extreme change of size).</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>Actually posing as someone else carries its own problems. The character should know at least basic information about the individual; especially difficult deceptions (fooling a lover or close friend) require at least some familiarity with the target in order to succeed.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"manipulation","dice2":"performance","bonus":0,"difficulty":"7","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_va4nd0abdk","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Obfuscate","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670294183933,"modifiedTime":1674221177496,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"t1n2r0I9dZqvJkoR","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Inbred (1-5pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 107","description":"<p>Inbreeding, a common occurrence among the incestuous Giovanni Clan, can take many forms. The Inbred Flaw covers all manner of physical, mental, and emotional defects. A one-point Inbreeding is something simple and unobtrusive, such as eyes too close together or an underbite (+1 difficulty on Appearance rolls). A three-point Inbreeding is more severe: a congenital health condition (for mortals) or a crippling physical deformity (+2 difficulty on appropriate Strength, Dexterity, or Stamina rolls). Five-point Inbreedings are grossly disabling or emotionally crippling &mdash; everything from uselessly atrophied legs to a permanent Derangement &mdash; decided on mutually by the player and Storyteller. Inbred conditions may or may not be immediately discernible, though their point cost should be relative to their magnitude, as decided by the Storyteller.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1o80meebnjn","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Giovanni","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221085298,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"t4FjCc4lqPDKAfPA","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
