{"name":"Mute (4pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 483","description":"<p>You cannot speak. You may communicate with the Storyteller and describe your actions, but cannot talk to player or Storyteller characters unless everyone concerned purchases a commonly understood sign language (via the Language Merit) or you write down what you wish to say</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ry8o03n5zsc","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/4 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672365603221,"modifiedTime":1674221110803,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"tTy33sbotu0opUyz","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Repelled by Crosses (3pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 495","description":"<p>You are repelled by the sight of ordinary crosses, believing them to be symbols of holy might. When confronted by a cross, you must make a Willpower roll (difficulty 9) or flee from the symbol for the duration of the scene. If you botch the roll, not only must you attempt to flee, but the touch of the cross can cause aggravated damage (one health level of damage per turn that the cross touches your skin). This damage cannot be soaked, even if the vampire possesses Fortitude.</p>","details":"<p>Supernatural</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_81150czgfr","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221108966,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"thuYSMkb2DPvxXtm","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Contagious (5pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 163","description":"<p>Your body has died on the inside, filling you with noxious bacteria, spores, and even fungi. Mortals that touch you or on whom you feed must make a Stamina roll (difficulty 9) not to fall ill. The illness puts them in bed with fever and sickness, and each week they may attempt the Stamina roll again. The Storyteller might reduce the difficulty if the target is receiving proper medical attention. On a success they recover, but if they fail, they remain feverish. At the end of each month the victim remains ill, they lose a point of Stamina; if they are reduced to zero Stamina they die. If the Nosferatu knows of their contagion and infects someone maliciously, the Storyteller might call for a Humanity (or appropriate Path of Morality) degeneration roll if they die. Supernatural creatures generally have the ability to heal or cure such sickness in themselves, and vampires are immune to these germs of the dead.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vHJSI1w1uvu5im25"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ak5eyy1egoa","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Nosferatu#/CF_SEP/Flaw","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221089528,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"tjg93TodiACFKYfC","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Ritual of Xipe Totec","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 182","description":"<p>To perform the ritual, the Kindred removes his victim&rsquo;s top layer of skin with an obsidian dagger, taking care to damage the skin as little as possible in the process. The victim must survive this process (though she may well die of blood loss shortly after the ritual if not seen to properly). He then drains the victim&rsquo;s blood into a large ceremonial golden bowl. There the blood is mixed with octli, amaranth flower, and other ingredients. When imbibed by the necromancer, this mixture causes him to sweat a glistening sheen of blood (equal to one blood point). The Kindred then dons the skin of his victim, which on a successful roll absorbs the Kindred vitae and begins to heal, forming a second skin over the vampire&rsquo;s own. The victim needs to be of similar stature &mdash; otherwise, the features become distorted and the disguise is rendered useless. This power also has no effect on supernatural creatures (although it can affect ghouls).<br><br>Under normal visual scrutiny, the ruse is flawless. Of course, it imparts none of the victim&rsquo;s knowledge or mannerisms (and does nothing to mask the Kindred&rsquo;s own undead nature). Therefore, it works best for situations in which contact with friends and family may be minimized. To preserve the skin&rsquo;s condition, the Kindred must bathe it in a blood point&rsquo;s worth of vitae nightly. When the necromancer removes the skin (which causes one level of unsoakable lethal damage to the user and must be done with the same knife used to flay the victim in the first place), it is ruined in the process.</p>","details":"<p>Casting times for necromantic rituals vary widely; see the description for particulars. The player rolls Intelligence + Occult (difficulty 3 + the level of the ritual, maximum 9). Success indicates the ritual proceeds smoothly, failure produces no effect, and a botch indicates something has gone horribly wrong.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"7","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2r4138smwse","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 4 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670899739755,"modifiedTime":1674221175937,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"to74se8CqY1MthuO","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Mole (3pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 489","description":"<p>You have an informer buried in one of your Sect&rsquo;s enemy organizations who funnels you all sorts of information as to what her peers are up to. What you do with the information is up to you, but abusing the knowledge might be a good way to get your informer killed. The other side has spies too&hellip;.</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_tbkdk4lk1q","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674440157659,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"tso7vxAgUGagosVQ","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●● Blood Rage","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 213","description":"<p>This power allows a vampire to force another Kindred to expend blood against his will. The caster must touch her subject for this power to work, though only the lightest contact is necessary. A vampire affected by this power might feel a physical rush as the thaumaturge heightens his Physical Attributes, might find himself suddenly looking more human, or may even find himself on the brink of frenzy as his stores of vitae are mystically depleted.</p>","details":"<p>Each success forces the subject to spend one blood point immediately in the way the caster desires (which must go towards some logical expenditure the target vampire could make, such as increasing Physical Attributes or powering Disciplines). Note that blood points forcibly spent in this manner may exceed the normal &ldquo;per turn&rdquo; maximum indicated by the victim&rsquo;s Generation. Each success gained also increases the subject&rsquo;s difficulty to resist frenzy by one. The thaumaturge may not use Blood Rage on herself to circumvent generational limits.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"5","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_v3rmtx67pm","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Blood","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670930910577,"modifiedTime":1674439742578,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"ttzNJof2E7H66XmV","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"● Silence of Death","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 203","description":"<p>Many Assamites claim never to have heard their targets&rsquo; death screams. Silence of Death imbues the vampire with a mystical silence that radiates from her body, muting all noise within a certain vicinity. No sound occurs inside this zone, though sounds originating outside the area of effect may be heard by anyone in it. Rumors abound of certain skilled Assamite viziers who have the ability to silence a location rather than a circumference that follows them, but no proof of this has been forthcoming.</p>","details":"<p>This power (which costs one blood point to activate) maintains a 20-foot (6-meter) radius of utter stillness around the Kindred for one hour.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.aJQ4CALXjDITPxbR"},"cf":{"id":"temp_g4q0cu2l6d","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Quietus","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670332666414,"modifiedTime":1674221181880,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"tvArOg0MyOyyglt8","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●● Permanency","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 145","description":"<p>This power, also used in conjunction with Ignis Fatuus or Fata Morgana, allows a mirage to persist even when the vampire cannot see it. In this way, Ravnos often cloak their temporary havens in false trappings of luxury, or ward off trespassers with illusory guard dogs.</p>","details":"<p>The vampire need only spend a blood point, and the illusion becomes permanent until dissolved (including &ldquo;programmed&rdquo; illusions like those created by Apparition).</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepower","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_jgyzexzzmb","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Chimerstry","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670226749831,"modifiedTime":1674221159339,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"u3tA2tsOI9FXkmhI","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●● Compel Soul","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 161","description":"<p>With this power, a vampire can command a ghost to do his bidding for a while. Compulsion of the soul is a perilous undertaking and, when used improperly, can endanger vampire and wraith alike.</p>","details":"<p>The vampire locates and approaches the intended ghost or calls it to his presence with Summon Soul. As with the previous power, he must have the ghost&rsquo;s name and an object it handled in life. His player then spends one blood point and rolls Manipulation + Occult in a resisted roll against the ghost&rsquo;s Willpower (difficulty 6 for both rolls).<br><br>If the vampire wins, the number of net successes determines the degree of control he has over the ghost (as described below). Moreover, the vampire&rsquo;s control keeps ghosts that have been called with Summon Soul from returning to their original locations at the end of the scene. If the ghost wins, the vampire loses a number of Willpower points equal to the ghost&rsquo;s net successes. On a tie, the roll becomes an extended contest that continues each turn until one side wins. If the vampire botches at any point, the ghost is immune to any use of the vampire&rsquo;s Necromancy for the rest of the scene. If the ghost botches, it must obey as if the vampire&rsquo;s player had rolled five net successes.<br><br></p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 14.4066%;\"><col style=\"width: 85.5934%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Successes</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1 Success</td>\n<td>The ghost must perform one simple task for the vampire that does not place it in certain danger. It must attend to this task immediately, although it can delay the compulsion and pursue its own business at a cost of one Willpower point per scene. The ghost may not attack the vampire until this task is complete. It is possible to issue the task of answering one question, in which case the ghost must answer truthfully and to the best of its knowledge.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2 Successes</td>\n<td>The vampire may issue two orders or ask two questions as outlined for one success. Alternatively, the vampire may demand a simple task with a real possibility of danger, as long as the danger is not certain. The ghost may delay this compulsion with Willpower.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3 Successes</td>\n<td>The vampire may issue three orders as outlined for one success. Alternatively, he may demand the ghost fulfill one difficult and dangerous task or a simple assignment that has an extended duration of up to one month. The ghost may delay such orders with Willpower.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4 Successes</td>\n<td>The vampire may issue four orders, as outlined for one success, or assign two tasks, as for two successes. Alternatively, the vampire may command the ghost to perform one complex assignment that puts the ghost at extreme risk, or perform any number of non-threatening tasks as the vampire&rsquo;s slave for up to one month (or, if the necromancer spends a permanent point of Willpower, for a year and a day). It is possible for ghosts to delay individual tasks, but not put off enslavement.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5+ Successes</td>\n<td>The vampire may issue multiple orders that have a sum complexity or danger of five successes&rsquo; worth. Instead, the vampire may order the ghost to perform any one action that it is capable of executing within one month. Such a task can place the ghost in immediate peril of destruction, or even force it to betray and assault loved ones. It is not possible for ghosts to delay a task of this magnitude with Willpower &mdash; they must obey.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"manipulation","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"6","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6fvqbb4wn0f","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Sepulchre Path","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670842147642,"modifiedTime":1674221170050,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"uFFy6rUHLIUtM0OU","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
