{"name":"Class 5 (full riot gear)","type":"Armor","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/armor.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 280","description":"Armor adds its rating to the character’s soak dice pool against bashing damage, lethal damage, and aggravated damage from fangs and claws. It does not protect against fire or sunlight. However, armor also subtracts a number of dice from dice pools related to bodily coordination and agility (most Dexterity-based dice pools). This is reflected in the penalty listing. Attackers may make targeting rolls to hit unprotected portions of a defender and thus ignore the armor (Storyteller assigns difficulty penalty — typically +1 or +2).","details":"","isequipped":false,"ismagical":false,"isweapon":false,"soak":{"bashing":5,"lethal":5,"aggravated":5,"chimerical":{"bashing":0,"lethal":0,"aggravated":0}},"dexpenalty":3,"forms":{"hashomid":true,"hasglabro":false,"hascrinos":false,"hashispo":false,"haslupus":false}},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_626ifvdetzi","path":"Items#/CF_SEP/Armor","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674291929378,"modifiedTime":1674440436418,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"wCYhl1Q7zgnxLS27","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"The Path of Technomancy","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/mainpower_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 224","description":"<p>The newest path to be accepted by the Tremere hierarchy as part of the Clan&rsquo;s official body of knowledge, the Path of Technomancy is a relatively recent innovation, developed in the latter half of the 20th century. The path focuses on the control of electronic devices, from cellphones to laptops, and its proponents maintain that it is a prime example of the versatility of Thaumaturgy with regards to a changing world. More conservative Tremere, however, state that mixing Tremere magic with mortal science borders on treason or even blasphemy, and some European Regents have gone so far as to declare knowledge of Technomancy grounds for expulsion from their chantries. The Inner Council did approve the introduction of the path into the Clan&rsquo;s grimoires, but has yet to voice any opinion on the conservative opposition to Technomancy.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.disciplinepath","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":0,"isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_w0iir3wpc8q","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Technomancy","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671075738475,"modifiedTime":1674439747065,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"wUzBnLqcQuAAdTtL","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"● Contradict","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 221","description":"<p>The vampire can interrupt a subject&rsquo;s thought processes, forcing the victim to reverse his current course of action. An Archon may be caused to execute a prisoner she was about to exonerate and release; a mortal lover might switch from gentle and caring to sadistic and demanding in the middle of an encounter. The results of Contradict are never precisely known to the thaumaturge in advance, but they always take the form of a more negative action than the subject had originally intended to perform.</p>","details":"<p>This power may be used on any subject within the character&rsquo;s line of sight. The player rolls as per normal. The target rolls Perception + Subterfuge (difficulty equal to the number of successes scored by the caster + 2). Two successes allow the subject to realize that she is being influenced by some outside source. Three successes let her pinpoint the source of the effect. Four successes give her a moment of hesitation, neither performing her original action nor its inverse, while five allow her to carry through with the original action.<br><br>The Storyteller dictates what the subject&rsquo;s precise reaction to this power is. Contradict cannot be used in combat or to affect other actions (at the Storyteller&rsquo;s discretion) that are mainly physical and reflexive.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"4","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.9E6akUkM8fmk95bk"},"cf":{"id":"temp_lcnzlnkbov","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Corruption","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439744487,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"wX2wDO7ZEv9t6fh8","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Contacts","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 112","description":"<p>You know people all over the city. When you start making phone calls around your network, the amount of information you can dig up is impressive. Rather than friends you can rely on to help you, like Allies, Contacts are largely people whom you can bribe, manipulate, or coerce into offering information. You also have a few major Contacts &mdash; associates who can give you accurate information in their fields of expertise. You should describe each major contact in some detail before the game begins.<br><br>In addition to your major contacts, you also have a number of minor contacts spread throughout the city. Your major contact might be in the district attorney&rsquo;s office, while your minor contacts might include beat cops, DMV clerks, club bouncers, or members of an online social network. You don&rsquo;t need to detail these various &ldquo;passing acquaintances&rdquo; before play. Instead, to successfully get in touch with a minor contact, you should roll your Contacts rating (difficulty 7). You can reach one minor contact for each success. Of course, you still have to convince them to give you the information you need, assuming they can get it.<br><br><br></p>","details":"<p>Contacts may be pooled within the characters&rsquo; coterie.</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 16.782%;\"><col style=\"width: 83.218%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>●</td>\n<td>One major contact</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>●●</td>\n<td>Two major contacts</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>●●●</td>\n<td>Three major contacts</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>●●●●</td>\n<td>Four major contacts</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>●●●●●</td>\n<td>Five major contacts</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"wod.types.background","level":"","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_14tdb2ntd4k","path":"Backgrounds","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1673844458648,"modifiedTime":1674221071348,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"wjT558KGZONucOFO","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Eat Food (1pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 480","description":"<p>You have the capacity to eat food and even savor its taste. While you cannot derive any nourishment from eating regular foods, this ability will serve you well in pretending to be human. Of course, you can&rsquo;t digest what you eat, and there will be some point during the evening when you have to heave it back up.</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1a3wwhsmx3r","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672364948802,"modifiedTime":1674439880759,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"woyy0nGYhfQjJOwG","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●● Gift of Life","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 170","description":"<p>With the Gift of Life, the character can experience the best and most positive things about being alive. The overwhelming hunger for blood temporarily abates, allowing the character to consume and enjoy food and drink. She can also enjoy sex as she wishes, and the sun does not burn her. The Gift of Life comes with a dark, terrible cost, however. Its use is almost sure to result in the death of a mortal, as the vampire must expend an enormous quantity of vitae in order to initiate it. The Discipline&rsquo;s effects last until the midnight after the character uses the power, so it is in her best interests to use it just after midnight.occ</p>","details":"<p>The player spends 12 blood points, burning as much blood as possible each turn until she meets that level. She then rolls Stamina + Occult (difficulty 6) and needs only one success for the power to work. A botch has catastrophic effects. The character might be instantly killed or might inadvertently Embrace her victim, for example. If it takes longer than one turn to spend the necessary blood to enact this ability, it does not take effect until all 12 points have been spent. However, the blood must be spent continuously &mdash; the vampire cannot burn five, run off and feed, then burn seven more an hour later. On the other hand, she may feed as she activates the power &mdash; in one turn she might burn one blood point while drinking three. Since few Kindred above the Seventh Generation can easily expend such an amount of blood, the most efficient way to activate this power is to have a human nearby who can be sacrificed to power the transformation.<br><br>After her transformation, the character gains many traits of an ordinary human. She is largely immune to the scorching effects of the sun (Fortitude difficulties to soak damage from direct sunlight are halved, and she takes no damage if she is sufficiently covered), and she can experience and enjoy many of the fine things about human life. She retains a few of her vampiric benefits, however. Fortitude and Auspex abilities remain in place if she has either of those Disciplines, and the Storyteller may allow her to retain other Disciplines as well if he deems them dramatically appropriate. She also retains a vampire&rsquo;s benefits when it comes to handling bashing damage. However, she is still vulnerable to holy artifacts, human faith, and being staked. Her blood remains vitae, not human blood. Use of this ability &mdash; which creates a mockery of human life &mdash; may interfere with a character&rsquo;s Path advancement, at the Storyteller&rsquo;s discretion.<br><br>The vampire is no more vulnerable to fire than any other mortal while in this half-alive state, but she still suffers somewhat from the Beast. Frenzy and R&ouml;tschreck difficulties are halved (round up). She can remain active during the day without Humanity or Path-based dice pool caps, although she is certainly tired during the day, since that is not her usual time of activity.<br><br>Her Beast exacts a dangerous retribution when her day of &ldquo;life&rdquo; is done. Although its influence is greatly suppressed during this power&rsquo;s duration, the Beast has its way with the vampire for the next six nights, as all difficulties to resist frenzy increase by three. The wise necromancer hides herself away somewhere during that period, but, depending on morality and temperament, enforced isolation might drive her to frenzy on its own.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"stamina","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"6","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_reojxpqrhd","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Corpse in the Monster","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670842147642,"modifiedTime":1674221168230,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"wvvCBIDykkBenEtI","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"● Tremens","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 164","description":"<p>Tremens allows a necromancer to make the flesh of a corpse shift once. An arm might suddenly flop forward, a cadaver might sit up, or dead eyes might abruptly open. This sort of thing tends to have an impressive impact on people who aren&rsquo;t expecting a departed relative to roll over in his coffin.</p>","details":"<p>To use Tremens, the necromancer spends a single blood point, and the player must succeed on a Dexterity + Occult roll (difficulty 6). The more successes that are achieved, the more complicated an action can be effected in the corpse. One success allows for an instantaneous movement, such as a twitch, while five allow the vampire to set up specific conditions under which the body animates (&ldquo;The next time someone enters the room, I want the corpse to sit up and open its eyes.&rdquo;). Under no circumstances can Tremens cause a dead body to attack or cause damage.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"dexterity","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"6","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9h9qdp1h3gj","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Bone Path","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670842147642,"modifiedTime":1674221165795,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"x7TyMvPCvX2P7IOL","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"The Lure of Flames","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/mainpower_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 218","description":"<p>This path grants the thaumaturge the ability to conjure forth mystical flames &mdash; small fires at first, but skilled magicians may create great conflagrations. Fire created by this path is not &ldquo;natural.&rdquo; In fact, many vampires believe the flames to be conjured from Hell itself. The Lure of Flames is greatly feared, as fire is one of the surest ways to bring Final Death upon a vampire. See &ldquo;Fire&rdquo; (p. 297) for more information on how vampires suffer from flame.<br><br>Fire conjured by The Lure of Flames must be released for it to have any effect. Thus, a &ldquo;palm of flame&rdquo; does not burn the vampire&rsquo;s hand and cause an aggravated wound (nor does it cause the caster to frenzy) &mdash; it merely produces light. Once the flame has been released, however, it burns normally and the character has no control over it.</p>","details":"<p>The number of successes determines how accurately the vampire places the flame in his desired location (declared before the roll is made). One success is all that is necessary to conjure a flame in one&rsquo;s hand, while five successes place a flame anywhere in the Kindred&rsquo;s line of sight. Less successes mean that the flame appears somewhere at the Storyteller&rsquo;s discretion &mdash; as a rough rule of thumb, the thaumaturge can accurately place a flame within 10 yards or meters of themselves per success.<br><br>Individual descriptions are not provided for each level of this path &mdash; fire is fire, after all (including potentially causing frenzy in other vampires witnessing it). The chart below describes the path level required to generate a specific amount of flame. To soak the damage at all, a vampire must have the Fortitude Discipline. Fire under the caster&rsquo;s control does not harm the vampire or cause him to frenzy, but fires started as a result of the unnatural flame affect the thaumaturge normally.<br><br>&bull; Candle (difficulty 3 to soak, one health level of aggravated damage/turn)<br><br>&bull;&bull; Palm of flame (difficulty 4 to soak, one health level of aggravated damage/turn)<br><br>&bull;&bull;&bull; Campfire (difficulty 5 to soak, two health levels of aggravated damage/turn)<br><br>&bull;&bull;&bull;&bull; Bonfire (difficulty 7 to soak, two health levels of aggravated damage/turn)<br><br>&bull;&bull;&bull;&bull;&bull; Inferno (difficulty 9 to soak, three health levels of aggravated damage/turn)</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepath","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":0,"isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_eeozm8f716","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Lure of Flames","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1671008999967,"modifiedTime":1674439741914,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"xVT3QKVwjHQyqeFf","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Insight","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 177","description":"<p>This ritual allows a necromancer to stare into the eyes of a corpse and see reflected there the last thing the dead man witnessed. The vision appears only in the eyes of the cadaver and is visible to no one except the necromancer using Insight. The player rolls as normal as the vampire stares into the target&rsquo;s eyes for five minutes. The number of successes on the roll determines the clarity of the vision. A botch shows the necromancer his own Final Death, which can provoke a R&ouml;tschreck roll (see p. 299).<br><br>This power cannot be used on the corpses of vampires who have reached Golconda, or on bodies in which both eyes are missing or advanced decomposition has already occurred.<br><br></p>\n<table border=\"1\"><colgroup><col><col></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Successes</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1 Success</td>\n<td>A basic sense of the subject&rsquo;s death</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2 Successes</td>\n<td>A clear image of the subject&rsquo;s death and the seconds preceding it</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3 Successes</td>\n<td>A clear image, with sound, of the minutes preceding death</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4 Successes</td>\n<td>A clear image, with sound, of the half-hour before the subject&rsquo;s demise</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5 Successes</td>\n<td>Full sensory perception of the hour leading up to the target&rsquo;s death</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","details":"<p>Casting times for necromantic rituals vary widely; see the description for particulars. The player rolls Intelligence + Occult (difficulty 3 + the level of the ritual, maximum 9). Success indicates the ritual proceeds smoothly, failure produces no effect, and a botch indicates something has gone horribly wrong.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"4","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_b85pvhs6pai","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 1 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670899739755,"modifiedTime":1674221172672,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"xWiYoX4Uxic7P1Cr","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Dangerous Secret (1-5pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 161","description":"<p>You have come to know something you really wish you hadn&rsquo;t discovered. Worse yet, the people you have the dirt on know that you know. It might be that you have discovered the Prince&rsquo;s haven, or that there are infernalists hiding in the diocese. Whatever it is, you are not sure whom you can tell, and if you do, you will only make the&nbsp; subjects of the secret more enthusiastic about getting rid of you. You may even be implicated in the secret and risk going down with them. The more potent the Flaw, the more powerful the people in question are, and the more they want it silenced.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vHJSI1w1uvu5im25"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ak5eyy1egoa","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Nosferatu#/CF_SEP/Flaw","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221089631,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"xftphUFn6veycFaE","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"● Eye's of the Sea","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 219","description":"<p>The thaumaturge may peer into a body of water and view events that have transpired on, in, or around it from the water&rsquo;s perspective. Some older practitioners of this art claim that the vampire communes with the spirits of the waters when using this power; younger Kindred scoff at such claims.</p>","details":"<p>The number of successes rolled determines how far into the past the character can look.<br><br></p>\n<table border=\"1\"><colgroup><col><col></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Success</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Result</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1 Success</td>\n<td>One day</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2 Successes</td>\n<td>One week</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3 Successes</td>\n<td>One month</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4 Successes</td>\n<td>One year</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5 Successes</td>\n<td>10 years</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>The Storyteller may require a Perception + Occult roll for the character to discern very small details in the transmitted images. This power can only he used on standing water; lakes and puddles qualify, but oceans, rivers, sewers, and wine glasses do not.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"4","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.RFll2tsRz778pPrL"},"cf":{"id":"temp_8yl7px52c34","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/Neptune's Might","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439739152,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"xiARwxMz9odLIuJ4","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Spirit Mentor (3pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 493","description":"<p>You have a ghostly companion and guide. The identity and exact powers of this spirit are up to the Storyteller, but it can be called upon in difficult situations for help and guidance.</p>","details":"<p>Supernatural</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.54P0qFftbsAnSyDQ"},"cf":{"id":"temp_spg1pw8bbx","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/3 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674439887124,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"xruzZjzRGCFbkVgG","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●● Comrades at Arms","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 224","description":"<p>This ability extends the power of the previous abilities in the path. It allows any of the earlier effects to be applied to a group such as a pack or War Party.</p>","details":"<p>The player chooses one of the lower-level powers in the path, invoking it as normal. Afterward, he touches another character and (if the roll for Comrades at Arms is successful) bestows the benefit on her as well. The same power may be delivered to any number of packmates, as long as the rolls for Comrades at Arms are successful and the thaumaturge pays the appropriate blood costs.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"8","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4yk16ojy6jl","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Mars","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439745956,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"xs9y10bdAQRkgcNU","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"New Kid (1pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 490","description":"<p>You&rsquo;re the latest in the city to be Embraced or have yet to prove yourself to your Sect, and everyone knows it. That automatically puts you at the bottom of the social totem pole. Other neonates take every opportunity to demonstrate your inferiority, or rival packs constantly test your worthiness to the Sabbat. Even if someone else is added to the ranks of the unliving, you&rsquo;re still regarded as something as a bit of a geek by your peers &mdash; a distinction that can have dangerous consequences if bullets start flying. All Social-related rolls are at +1 difficulty when you are dealing with other neonates. (Ancillae and elders lump you in with all the other neonates under their general disdain.)</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_jwd9ok2vgth","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/1 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221102231,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"xsjKLDshNRJXRxZR","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"Feature","flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_02lw4m6r7kvf","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/4 pt. Merits","color":"#000000","name":"4 pt. Merits","children":[],"folderPath":["temp_zbxadbcq32d","temp_d2jpx7vmusf"],"fontColor":"#FFFFFF","icon":null,"sorting":"a","contents":["sPdQQ9EBJUdzzN0I","pDKi4eowKspANzPZ","yHRk6QBzrpn69JSH","fcSpMrNUql6UaW3K","kgMG5tsMoakG9LEI"],"version":"2.5.6"}},"img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","system":{"iscreated":false,"version":"","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"","description":"","details":"","type":"","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674439934816,"modifiedTime":1674439935175,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"y47pXZB2JLfbxPDK"}
{"name":"Huge Size (4pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 480","description":"<p>You are abnormally large in size, at least 6&rsquo;10&rdquo; and 300 pounds in weight (well over two meters tall and over 130 kgs). Aside from making you extremely noticeable in public, this extra mass bestows an additional Bruised health level. Characters with this Merit may also gain bonuses to push objects, open barred doors, avoid being knocked down, etc.</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_02lw4m6r7kvf","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Merits#/CF_SEP/4 pt. Merits","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672364948802,"modifiedTime":1674439934514,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"yHRk6QBzrpn69JSH","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Broken Antitribu (3pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 26","description":"<p>You are one of those most pitiful things &mdash; an Assamite <em>antitribu </em>who still labors under the Tremere Curse. You have pledged yourself to the Sabbat, but you cannot perform diablerie and can only partake of Kindred vitae already transubstantiated through the Vaulderie. As a result, the difficulty of all Social rolls against other Sabbat members is at +2.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_naefi5ko57","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Assamite","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221080740,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"yJGgGPOh5qI84F6m","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Fourteenth Generation (2pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 481","description":"<p>You were created five or fewer years ago by a member of the Thirteenth Generation. Though you have 10 blood points in your body, only eight of them may be used to heal wounds, power Disciplines, raise Attributes, etc. You can still use the final two blood points for other purposes, though. The blood point costs of nightly rising, creating and sustaining ghouls, and creating blood bonds remains the same as for other vampires. You cannot raise any Discipline above four dots.<br><br>Taking this Flaw precludes you from taking the Generation Background, and you may not start with Status, either. You are likely a Clanless Caitiff, for your blood is probably too thin to pass down the distinguishing characteristics of a Clan. Most Fourteenth-Generation vampires should also take the Thin Blood Flaw (p. 483).</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2wewy46vpbx","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/2 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672365603221,"modifiedTime":1674221105220,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"yLQriaFFW0mGTnRR","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Call of the Hungry Dead","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/ritual_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 177","description":"<p>Call of the Hungry Dead takes only 10 minutes to cast and requires a hair from the target&rsquo;s head. The ritual climaxes with the burning of that hair in the flame of a black candle, after which the victim becomes able to hear snatches of conversation from across the Shroud. If the target is not prepared, the voices come as a confusing welter of howls and unearthly demands; he is unable to make out anything intelligible, and may go briefly mad.</p>","details":"<p>Casting times for necromantic rituals vary widely; see the description for particulars. The player rolls Intelligence + Occult (difficulty 3 + the level of the ritual, maximum 9). Success indicates the ritual proceeds smoothly, failure produces no effect, and a botch indicates something has gone horribly wrong.</p>","type":"wod.types.ritual","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"intelligence","dice2":"occult","bonus":0,"difficulty":"4","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_b85pvhs6pai","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Rituals#/CF_SEP/Level 1 Rituals","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670899739755,"modifiedTime":1674221172477,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"yLtHvRSxrGCz91Hh","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Enemy (1-5pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 490","description":"<p>You have an enemy, or perhaps a group of enemies, who seek to harm you. The power of the enemy depends upon how many points the player wishes to spend (five points indicate the wrath of a Methuselah or other potent supernatural foe).</p>","details":"<p>Social</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PObtkAVWkJjHBqr7"},"cf":{"id":"temp_d9j4thjusi","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/Multi-pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221113910,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"yPMhnF7lftVp3gXG","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
