{"name":"●●● Encrypt/Decrypt","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 225","description":"<p>Electronic security is a paramount concern of governments and corporations alike. Those thaumaturges who are techno-savvy enough to understand the issues at stake have become quite enamored of this power, which allows them to scramble a device&rsquo;s controls mystically, making it inaccessible to anyone else. Encrypt/Decrypt also works on electronic media; a DVD under the influence of this power displays just snow and static if played back without the owner&rsquo;s approval. Some neonates have taken to calling this power &ldquo;DRM.&rdquo;</p>","details":"<p>The character touches the device or data container that he wishes to encrypt. The player rolls normally. The number of successes scored is applied as a difficulty modifier for anyone who attempts to use the protected equipment or access the scrambled information without the assistance of the character. The caster can dispel the effect at any time by touching the target item and spending a point of Willpower.<br><br>This power may also be used to counter another thaumaturge&rsquo;s use of Encrypt/Decrypt. The player rolls at +1 difficulty; each success negates one of the &ldquo;owner&rsquo;s.&rdquo;<br><br>The effects of Encrypt/Decrypt last for a number of weeks equal to the character&rsquo;s permanent Willpower rating.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"6","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.20G6Olc0WGsmZpYU"},"cf":{"id":"temp_w0iir3wpc8q","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of Technomancy","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439746764,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"ybBYaSfAzBm9lk3p","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Necromancy - Path of the Four Humors ●● Kiss of the Dark Mother","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 173","description":"<p>Kiss of the Dark Mother allows the necromancer who uses it to mix her vitae with black bile, turning it into a noxious poison. The necromancer forces it into her mouth as saliva might once have come; the vitae tastes acrid and bitter, as though it had been scorched. Once the necromancer coats her teeth and lips with it, she can inflict terrible damage with her bite.</p>","details":"<p>The player spends one blood point; activating this power is a reflexive action, but it must be done before making a bite attack. If the bite hits, the aggravated damage inflicted by a single bite is doubled before soak is calculated. This power does not affect the character&rsquo;s ability to drain blood from the target, nor does it increase the amount of damage done by blood loss. The necromancer&rsquo;s bite remains potent until this ability is discharged by a successful hit or she spends one turn cleansing the dark blood from her mouth.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":0,"isrollable":false,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.OtFLkBWzSfaQtOuG"},"cf":{"id":"temp_67skqbr92vb","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Necromancy#/CF_SEP/Necromancy Paths#/CF_SEP/Path of the Four Humors","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670842147642,"modifiedTime":1674221164019,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"ydXqZbl0ktAq63Uy","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Secret Stash (2-5pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 122","description":"<p>You have several resources, sleeper agents, or followers hidden away for a rainy day. For each level of this Merit you have one unassigned background point &ldquo;sitting in storage&rdquo; (2 gives you one point, 3 gives you two points, and so on). At any time, you may spend as many of them as you like to increase your level in Allies, Contacts, Herd, Influence, Mentor, Resources, or Retainers. Once spent, the points remain assigned permanently, but until then they cannot be affected by anything. This allows the vampire to create a new resource in an instant, without requiring the expenditure of experience points or awaiting a downtime. The vampire is not really gaining new levels, but revealing levels he has had all along.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.BonXhY7P5YxFV8YT"},"cf":{"id":"temp_gevrsr5xe9","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Lasombra","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221087078,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"yeVvi9jgHtuubJvz","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●● The Lure of Flames","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 218","description":"<p>This path grants the thaumaturge the ability to conjure forth mystical flames &mdash; small fires at first, but skilled magicians may create great conflagrations. Fire created by this path is not &ldquo;natural.&rdquo; In fact, many vampires believe the flames to be conjured from Hell itself. The Lure of Flames is greatly feared, as fire is one of the surest ways to bring Final Death upon a vampire. See &ldquo;Fire&rdquo; (p. 297) for more information on how vampires suffer from flame.<br><br>Fire conjured by The Lure of Flames must be released for it to have any effect. Thus, a &ldquo;palm of flame&rdquo; does not burn the vampire&rsquo;s hand and cause an aggravated wound (nor does it cause the caster to frenzy) &mdash; it merely produces light. Once the flame has been released, however, it burns normally and the character has no control over it.</p>","details":"<p>The number of successes determines how accurately the vampire places the flame in his desired location (declared before the roll is made). One success is all that is necessary to conjure a flame in one&rsquo;s hand, while five successes place a flame anywhere in the Kindred&rsquo;s line of sight. Less successes mean that the flame appears somewhere at the Storyteller&rsquo;s discretion &mdash; as a rough rule of thumb, the thaumaturge can accurately place a flame within 10 yards or meters of themselves per success.<br><br>Individual descriptions are not provided for each level of this path &mdash; fire is fire, after all (including potentially causing frenzy in other vampires witnessing it). The chart below describes the path level required to generate a specific amount of flame. To soak the damage at all, a vampire must have the Fortitude Discipline. Fire under the caster&rsquo;s control does not harm the vampire or cause him to frenzy, but fires started as a result of the unnatural flame affect the thaumaturge normally.<br><br>&bull; Candle (difficulty 3 to soak, one health level of aggravated damage/turn)<br><br>&bull;&bull; Palm of flame (difficulty 4 to soak, one health level of aggravated damage/turn)<br><br>&bull;&bull;&bull; Campfire (difficulty 5 to soak, two health levels of aggravated damage/turn)<br><br>&bull;&bull;&bull;&bull; Bonfire (difficulty 7 to soak, two health levels of aggravated damage/turn)<br><br>&bull;&bull;&bull;&bull;&bull; Inferno (difficulty 9 to soak, three health levels of aggravated damage/turn)</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"0","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_eeozm8f716","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Lure of Flames","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439741814,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"ynIfGPMHsykX0PRP","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Obvious Predator (2pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 48","description":"<p>Your innate Brujah rage always percolates below the surface no matter how hard you try to project an image of calm. Mortals find you intrinsically menacing, and instinctively fear you for the violence you promise to unleash.&nbsp;</p>","details":"<p>The difficulty of all Social rolls made against mortals other than Intimidation rolls increases by 2.</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"2","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_xu302tg7wm7","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Brujah","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221081848,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"yqny47UV8AI91OcU","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Brahmin (1pt. Merit)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 182","description":"<p>As a member of the Brahmin jati, you are a priest, artist, teacher, or other pillar of society. Perhaps you keep the lore of the Clan, or perhaps you act as an advisor to other Ravnos in need of wisdom. Once per session, if you fail an Academics or Expression roll, you may immediately reroll it.<br><br>You do not have to purchase this Merit to be a member of the Brahmin jati, but only members of the Brahmin jati may have this Merit.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.merit","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.iGFbYRukWee1s96g"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ah1xgfy02pt","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Ravnos","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221092491,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"z1c6Qko4V6XuKnGm","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Fifteenth Generation (4pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 481","description":"<p>Your vitae is so weak that only six of your 10 blood points can be used for Disciplines, healing or raising Attributes. For these functions, you must expend two blood points to obtain the effect a normal vampire would achieve with one. (The cost for nightly rising remains a single blood point.) What&rsquo;s more, you cannot create or sustain ghouls, create a blood bond, or sire a vampiric childe. You can use the remaining four blood points to survive through the day and wake up each night, nothing more.<br><br>You cannot raise any Discipline above three dots.<br><br>The weakening of the Curse of Caine has compensations, though (which distinguish this Flaw from the Thin Blood Flaw itself). Sunlight does lethal damage to you, instead of aggravated damage as it does to other vampires. You can hold down mortal food and drink for an hour or so; other vampires vomit immediately if they try (unless they have the Eat Food Merit). Strangest of all, once in a while you might actually have a child the normal, human way... though it will hardly be a normal, human child.</p>","details":"<p>Physical</p>","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"4","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ry8o03n5zsc","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Flaws#/CF_SEP/4 pt. Flaws","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672365603221,"modifiedTime":1674221110229,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"zIg8gSHkU2ZXV5w5","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●●●● Valediction","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 228","description":"<p>Many Sabbat rightfully fear this power, though very few have ever seen it used. It levies a punishment for breaking one of Caine&rsquo;s greatest commandments &mdash; the ban against diablerie. As most Sabbat attain their power and station through some measure of diablerie, they must reconcile their beliefs with the admonitions of Caine, and this power engenders a great sense of humility.</p>","details":"<p>When this power takes effect, the subject immediately reverts to her original Generation. This change may entail losing points in certain Traits due to generational maximums. This power lasts for one week, after which any Traits reduced to higher-Generation maximums return to normal. It takes three turns to speak the full verse that implements this power&rsquo;s effects.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"5","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"8","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,"spendglamour":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_cnqt60rshz","path":"Disciplines#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy#/CF_SEP/Thaumaturgy Paths#/CF_SEP/The Path of the Father's Vegeance","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1670931559691,"modifiedTime":1674439747979,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"zLeChDr3fyZSMX8g","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"Chandala (1pt. Flaw)","type":"Feature","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/feature.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.5","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"Lore of the Clans 182","description":"<p>Being a member of the lowest jati, the Chandala, is a mixed bag. You are responsible for the disposal of corpses, as well as many other foul tasks, but at the same time, you are often ignored. Your Social rolls against other Ravnos are made at a +2 difficulty.<br><br>You do not have to take this Flaw to be a member of the Chandala jati, but only members of the Chandala jati may have this Flaw.</p>","details":"","type":"wod.types.flaw","level":"1","value":0,"max":5,"isrollable":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ah1xgfy02pt","path":"Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Clan - Merits & Flaws#/CF_SEP/Ravnos","color":"#000000"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"worldofdarkness","systemVersion":"2.2.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1672474316434,"modifiedTime":1674221092598,"lastModifiedBy":"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc"},"_id":"zUU0GMx54Wg5U2FH","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"CZyj5tVpsqRvDFFc":3}}
{"name":"●●● Tread Upon the Grave","type":"Power","img":"systems/worldofdarkness/assets/img/items/power_vampire.svg","system":{"iscreated":true,"version":"2.2.0","parentid":"","worldanvil":"","reference":"V20 167","description":"<p>The extended awareness granted with the Cenotaph Path allows the necromancer to find locations where the Shadowlands and the living world come close. Often, the necromancer experiences a chill or shiver when stepping into an area where the Underworld lies near the living one. With practice, the vampire can tell exactly where such locations are.<br><br><br></p>\n<p>Experienced necromancers learn that certain locations are susceptible to ghostly influence; these haunted areas often become homes of a sort for ghosts. A knowledgeable vampire can thus discover places where the dead are likely to congregate, the better to snare them with other Necromancy powers.</p>","details":"<p>The player simply declares intent to sense the Shroud in an area and makes a Willpower roll (difficulty 8). Success reveals whether the location is highly attuned to the Shadowlands, about average (not particularly close to the world of the dead), or far removed from the realm of death. A failing attempt at using the power has no adverse effect, though it may be attempted only once per scene (so the necromancer must either wait for a time or move to a different area before attempting Tread Upon the Grave once more). A botch stuns the necromancer into inaction for a full turn and costs him a temporary Willpower point, as he is overcome by shivers and a sense of overwhelming despair.<br><br>With three or more successes, the necromancer can determine whether the Shroud&rsquo;s strength has been artificially altered in the area.</p>","type":"wod.types.disciplinepathpower","level":"3","value":0,"max":5,"dice1":"willpower","dice2":"","bonus":0,"difficulty":"8","isrollable":true,"isactive":false,"spendwillpower":false,"spendrage":false,"spendgnosis":false,"spendblood":false,